INSERT INTO `article_details` VALUES (4, 4, 'en', 'euromillions_lottery_tickets_amp_results_online', 'Euromillions - Lottery Tickets &amp; Results Online', 'Euromillions is Europes largest lottery with jackpots reaching up to a staggering and unprecedented €185,000,000. As the name suggests, when Euromillions lottery came into existence in February 2004,  it was only available to the residents of European countries, namely Austria, Belgium, France, Luxemburg, Portugal, Spain, Switzerland and the UK.     An online system however has since been set up wherein carefully selected and reliable buyers resell tickets they have purchased in physical outlets online at a price of €5 so that residents of non European countries also have the opportunity to win. The Euromillons draws take place every Tuesday and Friday at 9.00 pm and players have the opportunity to purchase tickets up to two hours before the draw takes place on live television.     Because Euromillions is not specific to any one country like many other lotteries are the value of the prizes is a great deal higher than that of National lotteries and when a jackpot is not won the money rolls over onto the next week, again making the prizes very substantial indeed and the game more appealing to players. Another rewarding aspect of Euromillions is that the money won is tax-free so that winners never have to fork out any of their earnings to the government.    Once 18 years or above players can buy as many tickets for each draw as they wish and can do so in any recognised National lottery agent or online at Euromillions.com. Players fill out the payslip by choosing five numbers from 1 to 50 plus two lucky stars from 1 to 9 inclusively. A lucky dip has also been made available for people who choose not to select their own numbers or for those people in a hurry, wherein a machine randomly quick picks the required amount of numbers and lucky stars.     <h2>Buy Euromillions Tickets</h2>    <center><a rel="nofollow" href="