INSERT INTO `article_details` VALUES (8, 8, 'en', 'what_is_the_euromillions_lottery', 'What is the Euromillions Lottery?', '<p>Everyone wants to get rich quickly these days and the easiest way to become a multi-millionaire is to play a lottery game. Euromillions is one of the most reputable lottery games and has the largest jackpots, and now you can play from almost anywhere in the world  outside of Europe.</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Euromillions origins</strong>\r\n\r\n<p>The launch of Euromillions lottery was planned to take place in the year 1994 but facing opposition from political parties the Euromillions Lottery didn''t  come to life until February 7th 2004 with its first draw taking place on February 13th  2004 in Paris. In the beginning, only France, UK, and Spain participated in EuroMillions but after a few months Switzerland, Portugal, Austria, Ireland, Belgium, and Luxembourg all joined the lottery system and it has been running with more and more success  ever since.</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Introduction to Euromillions</strong>\r\n\r\n<p>participating European countries. However now even non-European players are also able to play via the internet. Tickets can be purchased online through reputable resellers who buy the tickets from physical outlets in their country and sell them to you online. Tickets cost just €2 per draw and €5 online. Draws take place on Tuesday and Friday evenings at 9.30 pm with tickets on sale up to two hours prior to the draw.</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>Why choose Euromillions?</strong>\r\n\r\n<p>You may wonder why you should choose the Euromillions lottery when there are numerous other lottery games available. The first and most important reason to choose Euromillions is the size of the jackpot available to you. Since the game is open to multiple nations the number of entrants is higher than any other lottery, and thus the prize fund is invariably higher too.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another noteworthy benefit of playing the Euromillions Lottery is that when no jackpot winner is declared the prize fund will rollover to the next draw. This can happen up to 11 times and some have been lucky enough to win a jackpot of €185, 000, 000. In addition, the prizes won in EuroMillions are tax-free and thus players are not obliged to hand over  any of their winnings to the government..</p>', 'What is the Euromillions Lottery?', 'Euromillions Lottery, Euromillions, Lottery', 'What is the Euromillions Lottery? Learn about the biggest lottery in Europe here at Euromillions.com', 1, 1318333846, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'What is Euromillions?', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1318333846, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
