Euromillionscom/204411286236724" title="Euromillions on Facebook">Euromillions on Facebook</a><p>', 'About the Euromillions lottery | Euromillions.com', 'How Euromillions Works, How to Play Euromillions, About Euromillions, Euromillions Lottery', 'About Euromillions.  Euromillions.com gives you all the answers to how Europes biggest lottery works.', 1, 1358264567, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'About Euromillions', '', '</br></br></br></br>\r\n<text>This page gives easy access to information about the history of Euromillions as well as the rules and terms and\r\n conditions. </br>\r\nYou can learn how to play and find the contact details of Euromillions.com</text></br>', NULL, NULL, 1319484256, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `article_details` VALUES (32, 21, 'en', 'split_jackpot', 'Split Jackpot', '<p>After three draws and no jackpot winners last week''s €47 million jackpot has been snapped up. In a lucky turn of events the prize is being claimed by two individual tickets. Both winners will have to share the prize with one another, but we can''t imagine them unhappy with over €23 million each! The Euromillions continues to change lives with it''s prizes as there were lots of lower tier winners too.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The numbers drawn were 02, 19, 33, 37, 46 with lucky stars 05 and 08. Already these numbers have made many people happy! Six players have won a second-tier prize of €318, 132 -5 matching numbers 1 lucky star. Seven more matched 5 main numbers with no lucky stars for €90, 000!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eighty nine people won €3575 as a fourth tier prize with four main numbers and two lucky stars. Many smiles all round as over one thousand people picked up a cool €238 by matching 4 numbers and 1 lucky star. Of special note is the UK Millionaire raffle winner who is picking up a massive £1 million.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our big jackpot winners have yet to reveal themselves, but we are certain the two jackpot winning tickets are in Spain and the UK. However these tickets could just as easily belong to a syndicate, and even if there is a winner they may not go public with the information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Keep it www.euromillions.com for more news and information on these winners as it develops.</p>', 'Split Jackpot', 'Split jackpot, two euromillions winners', 'After three draws and no jackpot winners last week''s €47 million jackpot has been snapped up. In a lucky turn of events the prize is being claimed by two individual tickets.', 1, 1320326795, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'split-jackpot', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1319555212, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
