INSERT INTO `article_details` VALUES (98, 35, 'en', 'history_of_euromillions', 'History of Euromillions', '<h3>The Beginning of the Euromillions</h3></br>\r\n<p>\r\nThe initial plans were laid out in 1994 in anticipation of a common European currency to be launched soon. The plans were delayed until the Euro was launched in January 2002. The first draw of the Euromillions was held on February 13th 2004. This Friday the 13th proved to be a lucky one for the first pan-European lottery. Initially organized by the three national lottery organizations of England, Spain and France, the Euromillions grew to become the biggest European lottery and one of the most famed worldwide.</p><p>\r\nToday, thirteen European countries are officially hosting the Euromillions. The thirteen countries are: Andorra, Austria, Belgium, France, Ireland, Isle of Man, Liechtenstein, Luxembourg, Monaco, Portugal, Spain, Switzerland and the United Kingdom. Players outside of the countries can participate as well. The Euromillions tickets are worldwide available through official resellers like Euromillions.com.\r\n</p>\r\n</br>\r\n<p>\r\nIn it''s inception the Euromillions was created to keep up with other European National lotteries, however it soon started to set the pace for others to follow. Today the Euro Millions is condiered to be the biggest European lottery with eleven participating countries and Jackpot sizes regularly surpassing the one-hundred million mark.</p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\nHistorically, the idea of a lottery goes back to 200 BC. The first known lottery was held in China under the reign of the Han Dynasty. The legend says the funds were used to save a struggling city and to build parts of the Great Wall of China.</p></br>\r\n<img src="http://euromillions.com/images/lottery%20scroll.jpg" width="550" alt="antique lottery scroll" /></br>\r\n<p>lottery scroll dated 1566</p></br>\r\n<p>The roots of lottery in Europe can be found in ancient roman history. The tradition of selling lottery tickets was established under Cesar Augustus. The income of the first state-run lotteries was used to rebuild and maintain the Roman Empire. Since then, lottery systems have evolved. The concept of the Euromillions, a lottery with participants all over the continent, set an example for other lotteries to follow. From the small beginnings, with only France, England and Spain participating, it grew to be the biggest lottery in Europe in less than 10 years.</p>\r\n</br>\r\n<h3>Jackpot History</h3>\r\n</br>\r\n<p>In its history, the Euromillions featured some of the highest lotto jackpots ever won in lotto history. Below you can find a list of the biggest Euromillions Jackpots ever won.</p></br>\r\n\r\n<table class="zebraTable"><colgroup> <col width="100"></col> <col width="121"></col> <tbody>\r\n<tr height="20">\r\n<td width="146" height="20">\r\n<h3>Date</h3>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="151">\r\n<h3>Jackpot</h3>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="105">\r\n<h3>Winner Country</h3>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr height="28">\r\n<td width="146" height="28">\r\n<p>29 July   2005</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="221">\r\n<p>115.000.000 €</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="305">\r\n<p>Ireland</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr height="27">\r\n<td width="146" height="27">\r\n<p>3   February 2006</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="221">\r\n<p>183.000.000 €</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="305">\r\n<p>France and Portugal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr height="27">\r\n<td width="146" height="27">\r\n<p>31   March 2006</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="221">\r\n<p>75.000.000 €</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="305">\r\n<p>Belgium</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr height="27">\r\n<td width="146" height="27">\r\n<p>17   November 2006</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="221">\r\n<p>183.000.000 €</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="305">\r\n<p>Various</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr height="27">\r\n<td width="146" height="27">\r\n<p>9   February 2007</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="221">\r\n<p>100.000.000 €</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width="305">\r\n<p>Belgium</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr he