INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (48, 36, 'en', 'generous_winners_bring_christmas_joy_to_sick_kids', 'Generous Winners Bring Christmas Joy To Sick Kids', '<p>The Euromillions lottery has rolled over for the fourth time, making Friday''s jackpot a tempting €46 million. If there''s no jackpot winner on Friday the Jackpot will statistically be more likely to continue until it breaks €100 million. Nevertheless there were still a huge 1,977,204 cash prize winners ranging from €3 to €372,197 with the numbers 7, 12, 18, 33, 37 and Lucky Stars 1 and 11.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Euromillions winners in the UK continue their festive generosity with a visit to St Andrews hospice in Grimsby to donate a selection of gifts for sick children. This heart warming act comes from Lee and Susan Mullen who won €5.4 million on the Euromillions in February of this year. The gifts they brought included a laser star projector, baby monitors, children''s high chairs and even presents for the dedicated team of nurses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Susan explaining her motivation said: “Lee and I have seen a dramatic change in our luck and good fortune this year, so when we heard about Winner Wonderland, we really wanted to help out”, “It has been fantastic meeting the patients and I hope everyone has a lovely Christmas”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“It is truly surreal that we can buy our children everything we want to for Christmas and we wanted to give something to those less fortunate who need the help”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While Euromillions winners give something back to these children just in time for Christmas there remains an unclaimed £1 million (€1 190 630) from the Millionaire Month raffle draw on the 25th November. Today it is confirmed that the ticket was purchased in North Ayreshire and naturally both ourselves and official lottery organisers are urging the Euro Millions tickets holders of the area to double check the <a href="http://euromillions.com/uk-millionaire-raffle-month-draw-november-25th/">Millionaire Month Raffle Results</a>.</p>', 'Fourth Euromillions Rollover and More Generous Winners', 'Euromillions Rollover, Euromillions Online, Euromillions Winner', 'While Friday''s jackpot stands at a staggering €46 million we look at the continued generosity of our winners', 2, 1324464801, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'News December 14th 2011', '', '<p>We take a closer look at the continued generosity of a Euromillions winner and also appeal for an unknown winner to claim their prize.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1324052147, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (49, 37, 'en', 'one_lucky_winner_of_46_million', 'One Lucky Winner Of €46 million!', '<p>At this stage the only information we can confirm is that one ticket holder in Spain has matched all 5 main numbers and 2 lucky stars for a total prize of €46,576,447! We must now wait to see if this fantastic prize will be claimed and who will claim it. Hopefully the winner has been quick to check their ticket and is already preparing for what will no doubt be their best Christmas yet. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The numbers 2, 5, 10, 23, 31 and lucky stars 2 and 5 brought the 4 times rollover to an end just in time for the last 2 draws before Christmas. UK players still have the 20 guaranteed millionaires raffle draw that occurs on the 23rd to look forward to.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Friday''s draw also saw 13 prize winners match 5 numbers and 1 star for €142,015, and 19 people managed to match 5 for €32 389. In fact a total of 3,393,591 tickets won a cash prize; a relatively large number of winners for this Friday''s draw.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This win brings Tuesday''s jackpot back down to €15 million which is always a handsome sum to claim from your €2.35 ticket cost. With just two more chances to win big in time for Christmas many players will be buying their tickets already.</p>', 'Friday''s Draw Produces Jackpot Winner', 'Euromillions jackpot winner, euromillions winner', 'The four times rolled over jackpot is finally won by 1 ticket from Friday''s draw', 2, 1324464972, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Fourth Rollover Jackpot Won December', '', '<p>The enormous €46 million jackpot will not be rolling over for a fifth time.</p>', 'Spanish Flag', NULL, 1324213535, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (50, 38, 'es', 'ganancia_del_bote_de_46_000_000', 'Ganancia del bote de €46 000 000', '<p>En el sorteo Euromillones del viernes 16 de diciembre de 2011 un billete en España, Madrid, ha acertado todos los números con la combinación ganadora del sorteo. ¡Este sorteo ponía en juego un bote de 46 millones de euros y el afortunado ganador se los llevó a su casa! La combinación ganadora del sorteo del viernes 16 de diciembre era: 02 - 05 - 10 - 23 - 31 / 02 05. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p> Ya que el bote fue ganado el 16 de diciembre, el sorteo del martes 20 de diciembre de 2011 proponía el bote inicial de la lotería Euromillones que representa 15 millones de euros. En este sorteo la combinación ganadora fue 01 - 09 - 12 - 14 - 48 / 01 - 07 y ningún participante acertó los 5 números y los dos números estrella con la combinación ganadora. Por lo tanto, el próximo sorteo, que tendrá lugar el viernes 23 de diciembre, pondrá en juego el bote de 29 millones de euros.</p>', 'Ganancia del bote de €46 000 000', 'resultado euromillones, ganancia de bote, euromillones', 'El sorteo del viernes 16 de diciembre ponía en juego un bote de €46 millones. Un boleto en Madrid acertó todos los números y el jugador en cuestión ganó la increíble suma. ', 2, 1324497736, 8, 'Ido S', 'sorteo-16-diciembre-2011', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1324497736, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (51, 39, 'en', 'final_draw_before_christmas', 'Final Draw Before Christmas', '<p>3 days left till Christmas and excitement is running high all over the world: shoppers busily looking for the perfect gift, families gathering to eat one big meal and children eagerly awaiting Santa. Have you imagined being a Euromillions winner on the 25th? For many that dream is a possibility, and this Friday marks the final opportunity to land in some big money.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The live draw this Friday will be for €29,000,000; a lifetimes supply of the best Christmases you could hope for that can be won in just a few days time. With countless more winning sizeable prices, there''s no need to wonder why tickets are going quickly. In the run up to Christmas 44 people have won tens and hundreds of thousands! One lucky Spanish winner has already taken a cheque for €46,000,000 this holiday season.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even more fantastic gifts await players in the UK this Christmas, as Camelot will be giving 25 presents of £1,000,000 (€1,200,918) to 25 UK ticket holders. The UK Millionaire Raffle will be making 25 people guaranteed millionaires just in time for the special day. It''s enough to make anybody in the UK think about buying a ticket. <a href="http://euromillions.com/secret-millionaire-christmas-gifts">Euromillions Winners</a> have already come forward to claim  the <a href="http://euromillions.com/millionaire-month">Millionaire Month</a> prizes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What''s going to be on your mind over the next 3 days? On Christmas day it could be of what exciting thing you''ll be spending your Euromillions prize on in 2013,  what could be better? Tickets can still be purchased for the Euromillions draw until tomorrow evening CET, our countdown on the homepage will keep track of when the last ticket can be purchased from the site.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Wishing everyone luck with the Christmas Euromillions draw.</p>', 'Euromillions Christmas Draw', 'Euromillions Christmas, UK Millionaire Month', 'With only 3 days left for Christmas we take a look at what is on offer on the final draw before the 25th', 2, 1324636532, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Christmas Euromillions 2012', '', '<p>Purchased your ticket for the Christmas draw yet? With a jackpot of €25 million and lots of other high cash prizes there''s a lot on offer for Christmas Euro Millions players.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1324554722, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (52, 40, 'en', 'xmas_free_play_lotto_game_comes_to_an_end', 'Xmas Free Play Lotto Game Comes To An End', '<p>The day before Christmas Eve sees the end of our <a href="http://euromillions.com/christmas-giveaway">Xmas Free Play</a> lotto game. The results are final and the game is closed. The game on Euromillions.com saw many entrants trying their hand every day at our lotto game for free to win real prizes. Some have won El Gordo tickets and many more now have an extra free €10 with which to buy Euromillions tickets here onsite.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Winners of the <a href="http://euromillions.com/ElGordo-Christmas-Prizes">El Gordo tickets</a> will receive outstanding odds to win some big cash prizes. A full El Gordo ticket is valued at €200! Thousands of full ticket holders will win thousands of euros, and thousands more will win €200. The odds of winning one of these many cash prizes with an El Gordo ticket is an awesome 1 in 6. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many other winners of the free play game will be able to play 4 free Euromillions tickets here on site with a €10 bonus. Tonight on the 23rd of December they''ll be in with a chance of winning €25,000,000!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our team will be contacting everyone who has won a prize in the Xmas Free Play game by email in time for Christmas day, and the winners of the €10 bonus will have received the money already.</p>', 'Xmas Free Play Lotto Ends', 'Euromillions Lotto, Free Lotto Online, Lotto Prizes', 'Our Christmas Free Play game comes to an end and there have been many winners', 2, 1324721463, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Xmas game ends', NULL, '<p>We take a look at what the lucky players of our Xmas Free Play Lotto have won themselves in time for Christmas day.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1324658602, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (53, 41, 'en', 'christmas_rollovers', 'Christmas Rollovers', '<p>The last three Euromillions draws have seen no jackpot winners however the draw on the 23rd saw 4 people receive €594,784 just in time for Christmas day. On the 27th there was also a second place winner who is holding a ticket worth €1,090,269! Other Christmas Euromillions winners include five winners of €75,685, and a full 20 winners of €39,652.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With no Christmas Euromillions jackpot winners the jackpot has rolled over three times. These three Euromillions Rollovers have brought a €50,000,000 prize for Friday''s New Years Eve draw and ticket sales are soon to shoot through the roof accordingly! Tuesday''s result of 19, 21, 25, 26, 44 and lucky stars 3 and 7 has not only given us some winners of thousands of euros but set us up for the biggest Euromillions jackpot in months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2012 is rapidly approaching and while this year hundreds of people have become millionaires already there''s still a chance for every player out there to win big. Who knows Friday''s jackpot of over €50 million could be the start of an epic rollover the likes of which haven''t been seen since Colin and Christine Weir won €185 million earlier in the year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the rollover is going to enter such stratospheric heights it won''t be until 2012. Buy your tickets for Friday''s draw now to have a chance at the massive €50,000,000 prize and you''ll also have the chance to win one of the many prizes claimed by Euromillions players regularly.</p>', 'Euromillions Christmas Rollovers', 'Euromillions Results, Euromillions Rollover', 'The Christmas Euro Millions draws brought no jackpot winners but after three consecutive rollovers the New Years eve top prize will be huge!', 2, 1325249566, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Christmas 2012 Rollovers', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1325090657, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (54, 42, 'en', 'online_lotto_play_set_to_expand_in_the_u_s', 'Online Lotto Play Set To Expand In The U.S', '<p>Things are set to change radically with the U.S Justice Department ruling that it''s now legal for tickets to be sold directly online by state lottery organisations -as opposed to through online ticket brokers. With this new ruling comes the possibility of a whole new way for American lottery players to take the chance of a lifetime.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Next year the state of Illinois is set to test online ticket sales with it''s residents. Illinois has been keen to push for online ticket sales, as it was through their correspondence with the Justice Department that the ruling has come into play. A 40 year old federal law that had been prohibiting wagering over telecommunications systems was under scrutiny by the state of Illinois. The new ruling came in the form of a <a target="_blank" href="http://www.justice.gov/olc/2011/state-lotteries-opinion.pdf">memo</a> from the Justice Department during their communications. This new ruling clarifies that states may indeed use the internet to sell tickets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>States like New York could pursue virtual ticket systems that allow tickets to be played from phones and other online mobile devices. “All state lotteries are looking at how we can expand our base and sell tickets” said a spokeswoman for the Michigan lottery, internet sales are “definitely in the mix for everyone”.</p>\r\n\r\n<P>With a huge collective deficit of $31.9 billion over the next fiscal year, every state will be excited about the new rulings. These states will be keen to become part of the $4 billion a year industry of online gambling in the U.S, especially in light of the fact that this has grown from $2.4 billion since 2003.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This new ruling has completely opened up the online gambling world to every state lottery association, as it will now allow them the freedom to bring other revenue generating games to the internet. Professor of business studies at Buffalo State College in New York Joseph Kelly said of this ruling that “It could be very important for the states.”</p>', 'Online Lotto Play Opens Up In America', 'Megamillions, Powerball, Online Lotto', 'New rulings in the U.S Justice Department could bring high online ticket sales of the Megamillions and Powerball', 2, 1325261753, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'New U.S Justice Department Ruling', '/Images/news/us_flag.jpg', '<p>Thanks to the 33 member Multi-State Lottery Association the games of Megamillions and Powerball in the U.S boast jackpot values of over €300,000,000. Will new rulings lead to huge online ticket sales?</p>', NULL, NULL, 1325260481, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (55, 43, 'en', 'happy_new_year', 'Happy New Year', '<p>It''s that time again, a year has gone by and a new one is about to start. We at Euromillions.com would like to take the opportunity to thank all of you who are playing the lottery through us. The Euromillions.com team are getting into the spirit of 2012 as we are entering the new year with a HUGE jackpot soon to be claimed. Don''t miss out!\r\n</p>\r\n<p><strong>Happy & Prosperous 2012!</strong></p>', 'Happy New Year', 'Happy New Year, 2012', 'Euromillions.com wishes everybody a Happy New Year, 2012 is here and presents us with another 104 massive jackpots to be won.', 2, 1325367951, 7, 'Henrik Hedlund', 'Happy New Year', '', NULL, '2012', NULL, 1325367832, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (56, 44, 'en', 'the_unusual_stories_behind_two_millionaire_raffle_winners', 'The Unusual Stories Behind Two Millionaire Raffle Winners', '<p>While on Christmas day many found new socks and festive woolly  jumpers wrapped up under their tree, one couple from Cumbria had a winning Euromillions ticket worth £1,000,000 (€1,199,156), but it wasn''t Santa''s doing. The ticket was of course a winner of the Millionaire Raffle draw held on the 23rd, a draw that created 20 winners of £1,000,000 on that one night. The tickets remained unchecked for two days after Karen Shaw (44) purchased the tickets and placed them in an envelope under the tree.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“We eventually all sat down around 4pm on Christmas Day to open the presents and I remembered the tickets” said Karen. After the family of husband Anthony (43), children Karl (20) and Sara (22) had finished opening their presents they decided to check their tickets. Karl had been checking the latest <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euromillions result</a> on his mobile phone when he exclaimed “You had better check it, I think it''s a winner”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Anthony and Karen intend to buy both of their children property of their own. “Anthony and I have always wanted to go on an Alaskan cruise, so we can plan that now” said Karen “And of course we will also treat the rest of the family”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The second winners to come forward are Judy and Frank Whitmore of Tockwith North Yorkshire, who had an unusual place to keep their winning ticket safe. Between the draw on the 23rd and the couple claiming their win on the 28th their ticket lived for 5 days in a sacred antique teapot. “The tea-pot is a family heirloom it was Frank''s great-great-grandmother''s” said Judy “It''s sacred to us, our little teapot”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The couple who have been married 43 years aren''t particularly keen to travel abroad, and were also loathe to go on a Christmas spending spree after their win. Judy was keen to tell press “We are not rich. We are normal, everyday people who like taking the dog for a walk and the countryside”. All Frank had to say of the win was “It means freedom to us – your ulcers disappear”. Frank plans to trade in his Vauxhall Meriva for a new Toyota Rav4, and  while the modest pair don''t plan any foreign travelling they are planning a short break in which the avid walkers may venture to the north of Scotland.</p>', 'UK Millionaire Month Winners Come Forward', 'Euromillions, Millionaire Raffle, Millionaire Month', 'This Christmas saw a lot of Euromillion''s prizes being won. Today we have the happy and unusual stories of two of these prizes', 2, 1325532634, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Millionaire Month Christmas Winners', '', '<p>The UK Millionaire Month created 50 millionaires in the UK with the raffle draws this festive season. We take a closer look at the heart warming and slightly unusual tales of two of these winners.</p>', 'Euromillions Prize Winners', 'Frank and Judy Whitmore with their antique teapot', 1325525179, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (57, 45, 'en', 'unclaimed_millionaire_raffle_tickets', 'Unclaimed Millionaire Raffle Tickets', '<p>The UK Millionaire Month Raffle draw on the 23rd of December has been one of the most exciting Euromillions events all year, with UK lotto organisers Camelot promising to create 25 millionaires on that one night. At the moment 22 of these 25 people have come forward to claim their £1,000,000 (€1,198,516) prize, however 3 guaranteed millionaires have yet to come forward. Camelot have even got the beautiful Holly Vallance dressed as Sofia Lauren in the classic movie “The Millionairess” to help promote the urgency of finding these winners as soon as possible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Holly has said "It was a dream come true for me to be able to recreate a scene from The Millionairess to celebrate the fact that 25 lucky Brits won £1million pounds this Christmas. I urge players to check their tickets to see if their dreams came true this Christmas too."</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It''s highly probable that the holders of these tickets are unaware of the Millionaire Raffle code printed on their ticket, and tossed it when they hadn''t won anything on the Euromillions draw. So players in the UK who purchased a Euromillions ticket for the draw on the 23rd of December are urged to double check their Millionaire Raffle codes to see if they are one of the lucky 3 who have yet to claim.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The following raffle codes are all winners from the 23rd:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><ul>\r\n<li>DXM829056</li>\r\n<li>DXN996670</li>\r\n<li>DXP982073</li>\r\n<li>FXS834119</li>\r\n<li>FXT562624</li>\r\n<li>FXV030572</li>\r\n<li>FXV864819</li>\r\n<li>FXW306769</li>\r\n<li>FXX376497</li>\r\n<li>FXX429386</li>\r\n<li>FXX659215</li>\r\n<li>FXX968168</li>\r\n<li>FYC052196</li>\r\n<li>FYC521328</li>\r\n<li>FYD286530</li>\r\n<li>FYD394832</li>\r\n<li>FYD990218</li>\r\n<li>FYF634659</li>\r\n<li>FYF871693</li>\r\n<li>FYF922410</li>\r\n<li>FYG118887</li>\r\n<li>FYK281299</li>\r\n<li>FYK507977</li>\r\n<li>FYK815210</li>\r\n<li>FYM293284</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>If any of these codes match the code on your Euromillions entry then you are a winner of a guaranteed £1,000,000.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the event that these prizes are not claimed within 180 days, the entire prize amount plus any interest the money has generated in that time will be donated to good causes within the UK. In the case of one Euromillions ticket purchased in the Vale Of Whitehorse on the 1st of July, winnings of €190,643 plus interest have already been donated to charity. The ticket had matched 5 main numbers and 1 lucky star, but as of Wednesday the time in which the prize could be claimed has expired and some people less fortunate are going to benefit from the cash.</p>', 'Unclaimed Millionaire Raffle Tickets In The UK', 'Millionaire Raffle, Euromillions Winners, Unclaimed Euromillions Prizes', 'With an estimated jackpot tonight of a tremendous €58 million there''s an urgent plea for some unclaimed millions', 2, 1325618488, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Unclaimed Millionaire Month Tickets', '', '<p>In 2011 the Euromillions lottery has created a great many winners. However some people still have no idea they are the owners of some tickets worth millions!</p>', 'Holly Vallance helps find Euromillions Winners', 'Holly Vallance dressed as Sofia Lauren from the Millionairess.', 1325616833, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (58, 46, 'en', 'fridays_euromillion_jackpot', 'Friday''s Euromillion Jackpot', '<p>This Friday everyone has an equal chance of becoming the sole winners of a tremendous €73,000,000, and thanks to Euromillions.com this jackpot is available worldwide. The rollovers have been ongoing for over 2 weeks now and this fifth one has brought one of the biggest jackpot prizes in months. This enormous cash prize will see ticket sales for the Euromillions shoot directly upwards, and these figures will continue to rise rapidly if nobody claims the jackpot this Friday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Despite the lack of a jackpot winner on Tuesday the cash prizes were still plentiful for many, in fact the total number of prize winning tickets is reportedly over 1.76 million.  Making things even more interesting was the value of the 2nd and 3rd tier prizes for Tuesday''s draw. In the second tier, 2 people matched 5 main numbers and 1 lucky star to win a life changing €604,877 each. However it''s the value of the 3rd place prize that has shocked many, giving one player a huge €403,251.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 3rd prize being so high is almost unprecedented, as in the previous draw the 3rd prize had only been €113,858, and only €72,685 in the draw before that. These high cash prizes are certainly a consolation when the jackpot has not been won, and many people would just as soon watch the jackpot remain untouched until it breaks the €100 million mark.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other big cash prize winners from Tuesday include 33 people who won €6,110, and 742 who will receive a prize of €237. If the jackpot is not claimed on Friday then there will still be many winners of big cash prizes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To help you choose this Fridays winning numbers it''s worthy of note that the numbers most overdue for an appearance are 13, 08, 35, 32 and 46. The most overdue lucky stars are 06 and 04. Nobody can be certain what numbers are going to be drawn on Friday though but we wish everyone playing their tickets with Euromillions.com the very best of luck with their entries</p>', 'Fifth Rollover creates jackpot of €73 Million', 'Euromillions Rollover, Euromillions Online, Friday''s Jackpot', 'Without a jackpot winner on Tuesday the Euromillions has rolled over for the fifth time creating a huge jackpot for Friday', 2, 1325764587, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Friday Rollover Jackpot 6th', '', '<p>Anticipation of Friday''s draw is running high, as one of the highest Euromillions jackpots in months is up for grabs!</p>', 'Euromillions Ticket', 'Possibly Friday''s winning Euromillions ticket', 1325764338, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (59, 47, 'en', 'friday_6th_jackpot_claimed_by_two_winners', 'Friday 6th Jackpot Claimed By Two Winners', '<p>Yesterday''s <a href="http://euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> jackpot on the 6th of January of a staggering €73,113,564 was one of the largest prizes in months and all over the world millions of people tried their luck to secure this much coveted prize! With many hopeful of winning this mountain of cash it''s only fitting that the wealth should be shared between two winners!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While the winners have yet to identify themselves we can confirm that the tickets are from France and Spain, and can be redeemed for a sizeable cash prize of €36,556,782. In recent weeks there have been stories of many unclaimed lottery tickets but in this instance it would be a crime if these prizes couldn''t find their way to their rightful owners.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Euromillions prize fund for this week was tremendous; a total of 9 people who had matched 5 main numbers and only 1 Lucky Star are in for a prize of €220,936! In third place there were 26 winners who are all due €25,493. For 4 main numbers and 2 Lucky Stars a payout of €1,556 is on it''s way to a 213 people who are no doubt very happy to see such cash in the first week of 2012.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There''s no doubt that yesterday''s draw has changed the lives of a great many people, and put big smiles on the faces of many many more. In fact a total of 3,697,302 tickets are valid to claim some sort of cash prize! This figure is more than double the amount of cash prize winners in previous draws, and it goes to show the power of a quintuple rollover! To find out if you''re a winner check out the latest <a href="http://www.euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euromillions Result</a></p>\r\n</p>', 'Friday 6th Jackpot Claimed By Two Winners', 'Euromillions Jackpot, Friday''s Jackpot Winner, Euromillions Winners', 'Multiple winning tickets for one of the biggest jackpots in months!', 2, 1325946161, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Friday 6th January Winners', '', '<p>The Euromillions in 2012 is off to a flying start with an enormous jackpot being claimed by not one but two lucky winners!</p>', 'Jackpot winning ticket', 'A possibly jackpot winning ticket being filled out', 1325945421, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (60, 48, 'en', 'french_winner_claims_prize', 'French Winner Claims Prize', '<p>The lucky French winner of half of Friday''s jackpot is confirmed to be of the Calvados region in France. The €36,556,782 prize makes this ticket holder the 12th biggest Euromillions prize winner in France. If the Calvados region rings a bell to you it''s possibly because on the 13th of September 2011 there was a <a href="http://euromillions.com/french-euromillions-winner-collect-winnings" target="_blank">Euromillions winner</a> of €162,256,622 there, this winner however calmly waited almost a month before stepping forward.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another big French winner who holds a ticket worth  €27,094,319 from the draw on December 2nd has still to come forward! The player has less than 24 days to claim this enormous cash sum. The broker who sold the ticket, Patrice Goeury has said "It may be a casual player who has not checked his schedule”, “Or a very wise winner, who for tax reasons or organization prefers to take the time to receive his winnings”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Spanish winner who has yet to validate his ticket joins another lucky <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/186/euromillions-winner-friday-16th" target="_blank">Spanish Euromillions winner</a>, who on the 18th December 2011 was holding a ticket worth €46 million. Make no mistake December was an excellent month for the Euromillions in both France and Spain and we hope to have more details about the latest two winners soon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Meanwhile in the UK the hunt is on for a Euromillions ticket holder in Wealdon, England. A ticket puchased there for the draw on the 25th November has matched the UK Millionaire Raffle code VVT537436 but the winner has yet to claim their £1,000,000 -€1,210,811. A spokesman for UK lottery organisers Camelot have issued this statement, “We’re desperate to find this mystery ticket-holder and unite them with their winnings – this amazing prize could really make a huge difference to somebody’s life. Try checking in the pockets of clothing, in wallets, bags and down the back of the sofa.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With huge cash prizes going unclaimed and many more finding their way into the bank accounts of lucky Euromillions entrants our attention turns to the €15,000,000 up for grabs in this Tuesday''s draw. Have you got your ticket yet?</p>', 'More details on Friday''s Jackpot winner', 'Euromillions Winners, Unclaimed Euromillions Prizes', 'More details emerge regarding the French winner of half of Friday''s jackpot.', 2, 1326111552, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Quintuple Rollover Prize Winner Information', '', '<p>One of Friday''s quintuple rollover jackpot winners has come forward to validate his ticket and claim his riches.</p>', 'Two Euromillions Tickets', 'Two winning Euromillions tickets for Friday''s jackpot', 1326111124, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (61, 49, 'en', 'camelot_reports_on_sales_increase', 'Camelot Reports On Sales Increase', '<p align="justify">Families all over Britain facing the effects of the global financial troubles are purchasing more and more lottery tickets in the optimistic expectations of a big jackpot win changing their lives. New sales figures have come to light yesterday following <a target="_blank" href="http://www.camelotgroup.co.uk/">Camelot Group</a>''s strategy to grow sales responsibly by encouraging people to play but still spend relatively small amounts. </p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">The new figures revealed by Camelot display an increase in sales of one fifth to £3.2 billion (€3.8 billion) in the six months ending September 24th. This is one of Camelot''s most successful interim periods and places them 7th on the list of most profitable lottery organisers in the world. 2700 people have been made millionaires or multi-millionaires since the creation of the lottery in 1994 so it''s little wonder it''s popularity is increasing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">Camelot is also responsible for selling the winning <a href="http://euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> ticket to Colin and Christine Weir, winners of £161 million (€194,817,818.47); the biggest jackpot ever won in the UK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">With this big rise in sales Camelot have also reported on an increase in money donated to good causes. Good causes have received £918.3 million (€1.1 billion) up from £784.8 million(€948 million) in the previous year. It warms the heart to know that while only a lucky few win the jackpot, there are millions of others less fortunate that still benefit from the ticket sales.</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">Since the beginning of the lottery in 1994 Camelot have distributed over £27 billion (€32.6 billion) to good causes and £40 billion (€48 billion) in prize winnings.</p>', 'Big Increase In Camelot''s Sales', 'Camelot, Lottery Sales Increase,', 'As the recession hits the UK a big rise in lottery ticket sales is reported', 2, 1375789282, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Camelot Sales Increase', '', '<p>Yesterday UK lottery organisers Camelot released a sales report with startling new figures that show the continuing strength of the game of Euromillions</p>', 'Camelot''s Rising Sales', 'A graph displaying the rising ticket sales of Camelot', 1326199101, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (62, 50, 'en', 'tuesdays_euromillions_winners', 'Tuesday''s Euromillions Winners', '<p>By many standards this Tuesday''s Euromillions numbers are a little unusual. 4, 9, 10, 30, 40 and Lucky Stars 2 and 9. While three multiples of 10 might seem likely number choices for many to choose, there was no jackpot winners and the prize remains to roll over to Friday''s draw.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However such common multiples of 10 have produced 3 second prize winners. These ticket holders have matched 5 numbers and 1 lucky star and earned themselves €350,739 each, a prize that hopefully won''t see them upset at having missed the jackpot by 1 lucky star. Five people have landed in the third prize tier by matching all their main numbers only, and the prize for each of them will be a life altering €70,148.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even more thousands of Euro''s will be due to 50 lucky players who matched 4 of their main numbers and the two stars. All fifty of these players will be receiving a tidy €3,654 each, certainly not an amount to be sniffed at for their relatively small ticket price.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tonight''s numbers have made a total of 1,851,066 cash prize winners. While almost one million of those winners will only receive €4 there were still 981 winners of €159 and 1673 winners of €93, which are again significant prizes given the tiny stake these players have put forward.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Friday''s jackpot will be a rollover above €20,000,000 and it may have your name written on it. Got your numbers ready to play? Then purchase your ticket now in anticipation of Friday''s draw!</p>', 'Tuesdays Euromillions Winners', 'Tuesdays Euromillions Winners, Euromillions Winners, Rollover', 'Tonights draw sees over 1.8 million Euromillions winners, find out more here', 2, 1326230663, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Tuesday 10th January 2012 winners', '/images/news/euromillions_1.jpg', '<p>Some unusual numbers see a jackpot rollover for this Tuesday''s draw</p>', 'A Euromillions Ticket', 'Not a jackpot winning ticket for Tuesday''s draw', 1326230506, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (63, 50, 'es', 'sorteo_del_martes_10012012', 'Sorteo del martes 10/01/2012', '<p>En el sorteo del martes 10 de enero de 2012 la lotería Euromillones proponía un bote de 15 millones de euros, además de las 12 otras categorías de premio. La combinación ganadora del sorteo es <strong>04 - 09 - 10 - 30 - 40 / 02 - 09</strong> y ningún participante acertó todos los números con esta combinación. Por lo tanto, se trata de una renovación del bote en el próximo sorteo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> En total, en este sorteo del martes 10 de enero de 2012; la lotería Euromillones distribuyo premios a 1 851 066 personas. 3 personas acertaron 5 números communes más un número estrella con la combinación ganadora del sorteo, lo que implica una ganancia de €350 739 para cada uno.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>El próximo sorteo Euromillones tendrá lugar el viernes 13 de enero de 2012 y el bote se estima en €28 millones. Ya se pueden comprar entradas para los próximos sorteos Euromillones.</p>', 'Sorteo del martes 10/01/2012', 'Euromillones, Sorteo Euromillones, Resultado Euromillones.', 'El sorteo Euromillones del martes 10 de diciembre de 2012 ponía en juego un bote de €15 000 000. Obtenga información acerca del último sorteo.', 2, 1326282463, 6, 'David Bonnici', 'Tuesday 10th January 2012 winners', '/images/news/euromillions_1.jpg', '<p>Último Sorteo Euromillones</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bote: 15 000 000€</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Combinación ganadora:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>04 - 09 - 10 - 30 - 40 / 02 - 09</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ganadores: 1 851 066</p>', 'Boleto Euromillones', 'Ningún ganador para el sorteo de este martes', 1326281724, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (64, 51, 'en', 'ladbrokes_in_trouble_with_irish_family', 'Ladbrokes In Trouble With Irish family', '<p>A side bet made on Friday by Ann O''Brien and 9 other members of her family on the <a href="http://euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> has sparked a row between the family and the betting giant. The family from Ballynanty in Limerick have placed some bets that may not be honoured.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Shortly after 8pm on Friday each member of the family placed a €2 bet in their local bookies at Thomondgate. They each made the same bet: the numbers 1, 6 and 12 appearing as main numbers in <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/200/friday-6th-january-winners">Friday''s draw</a>. The total amount of winnings from the bet should be €15,000 according to Ann but the bookmaker is refusing to pay out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The draw was held at 8.30pm live in Paris and sure enough the main numbers drawn were  1, 6, 10, 12 and 31. The numbers chosen were of special significance to the family who had attended an anniversary church service that very day together. “The numbers were significant to us and they came up, but when we went to claim the money they would not pay us the money” says Ann, all Ladbrokes would do is refer her to the customer service department.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A Ladbrokes spokesperson from the UK head office has stated that the company does not accept bets on the Euromillions in store, but that they do accept such wagers made on the website. There is a disclaimer on the site stating as such but with the bet already taken by staff members in store Ann O''Brien is naturally not going to back down.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Spokesperson goes on to say that the staff in store should not have accepted the bet: “If the bets were accepted it was a misunderstanding.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“They have offered us our original stake back, but what i''m saying is that they should honour the bet, because a bet is a bet and we want our bet to be honoured” says Ann.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ultimately if these three numbers had been placed on a <a href="http://euromillions.com/42/euromillions-tickets">Euromillions ticket</a> here at Euromillions.com the family would have no problem cashing in. As it stands there looks set to be a continued skirmish between the family and the bookmaker over this issue.</p>', 'Ladbrokes In Trouble With Irish Family', 'Euromillions, Euromillions Bet, Limerick Family Disappointed', 'A Euromillions bet made on Friday may not be honoured by a UK betting company', 2, 1326444656, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Ladbrokes In Trouble', '', '<p>Popular UK betting company Ladbrokes may be in hot water with 10 individual members of an Irish family.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1326385035, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (65, 52, 'de', 'nicht_eingeforderte_preis_freitag_13_januar', 'Nicht eingeforderte Preis Freitag 13. Januar', '<p>Ein Spieler aus der vermeintlich unglücklichen Ziehung am letzten Freitag dem 13. ist im Besitz eines gewinnbringenden Euromillions Ticket im Wert von € 179.575,26 EUR. Die Zahlen, gezogen an diesem verhängnisvollen Tag, lauten 13, 14, 21, 27, 39 und Lucky Stars 6 und 8. Der bis jetzt unbekannte Gewinner des großen Geldpreises, hat erfolgreich alle 5 Hauptnummern und eine der Lucky Stars Nummern richtig getippt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Der/Die Ticketinhaber(in) könnte noch abwarten, bevor er/sie sich bezüglich des Gewinns meldet, aber sie sollten sich bewusst sein, dass sie nur bis 23:00 Uhr GMT am Mittwoch 11. Juli Zeit haben, sonst wird der Gewinn für sie unerreichbar. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sollte der Gewinn nicht bis zu diesem Zeitpunkt beansprucht werden, dann wird das Geld und die entsprechenden Zinserträge zu den anderen € 27 Milliarden Euro stoßen, die bereits für einen guten Zweck innerhalb des Vereinigten Königreichs generiert wurden. So oder so wird das Geld jemanden den Tag verschönern. Alles was wir über den Sieger wissen ist, dass das Ticket in St. Helens, England erworben wurde. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ein Sprecher der Nationalen Lotto Organisation in Großbritannien sagte: „ Wir sind verzweifelt auf der Suche nach dem unbekannten Ticketbesitzer um Ihn mit dem Gewinn zu vereinigen. Der unglaubliche Gewinn könnte einen gewaltigen Unterschied im Leben des Ticketinhabers bedeuten. Wir drängen alle nochmals dazu auf ihre alten Tickets zu überprüfen und überall nach verlorenen Tickets zu suchen.“ </p>\r\n\r\n<p>„ Überprüfen Sie in den Taschen der Kleidung, in Geldbörsen, Taschen und auf der Rückseite des Sofas – jemand da draußen könnte buchstäblich auf einem Vermögen sitzen!“</p>\r\n\r\n<p>„ Wir haben den Champagner auf Eis und drücken die Daumen, dass der glückliche Gewinner sich meldet und seinen Gewinn abholt!“</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Wir bei Euromillions.com wollen auch das Geld in den Händen ihrer rechtmäßigen Besitzer sehen. Allerdings freuen wir uns mit Vorfreude, und mit dem Ticket in der Hand, auf den großen € 33 Millionen Jackpot heute Abend. Machen Sie sich keine Sorgen einen möglichen riesigen Geldpreis zu verpassen, wenn Ihre Zahlen kommen, denn mit Euromillions.com können Sie Ihr Ticket nicht verlieren. Es sind nur mehr ein paar Stunden, also gehen Sie und kaufen Sie Ihre Tickets jetzt. </p>', 'Nicht eingeforderte Preis Freitag 13. Januar', 'Nicht eingeforderte, Freitag 13. Januar, Ergebnisse', 'Ein Spieler aus der vermeintlich unglücklichen Ziehung am letzten Freitag dem 13.', 1, 1328722179, 9, 'Jenny Zimmerman', 'Nicht eingeforderte Preis', '', '<p>Ein Spieler aus der vermeintlich unglücklichen Ziehung am letzten Freitag dem 13. ist im Besitz eines gewinnbringenden Euromillions Ticket im Wert von € 179.575,26 EUR</p>', NULL, NULL, 1326409200, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (66, 53, 'en', 'friday_13th_euromillions_winners', 'Friday 13th Euromillions Winners', '<p>Friday the 13th, a day and date that may forever live in infamy as one of the unluckiest days in our calender. Unless you''re Spanish in which case it''s probably Tuesday the 13th you fear the most! This irrational fear is also known as friggatriskaidekaphobia and for some reason this day seems to attract huge Euromillions ticket sales. Or maybe the €29,204,007 prize was what drew in the crowds....</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Could a jackpot winner really have been expected on such a fateful day? In place of 1 jackpot winner however 10 people have disproved the superstition by matching 5 main numbers and 1 Lucky Star to win the second place prize of €213,060. A huge amount of second prize winners by any standard, and it is matched only by the amount of third prize winners. For 10 people who matched 5 main numbers only, a prize of $71,020 will be due. Surely the opinion of Friday the 13th will be forever altered for those 20 people.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many more thousands of Euro''s should be claimed by 110 people who have matched 4 main numbers and 2 Lucky Stars, their prize of €3228 will go a long way to improve their supposedly unlucky day. The last of the significant prize amounts was for €162 and should be received by 1919 winners who have matched 4 main numbers and 1 Lucky Star.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The whole Friday the 13th superstition is in fact completely blown out of the water, as an enormous 4,110,658 tickets can claim a prize from tonight''s draw. Thankfully there will be another two occurences of Friday the 13th this year so you haven''t yet missed your chance to play a Euromillions ticket on this ''unlucky'' day and date.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With Tuesday''s prize set to push as high as €35 million, will it continue to rollover or will someone be quick to snap it up? One thing''s for certain, regardless of the day, you have to be in it to win it and for over 4 million people today was definitely a day worth purchasing a Euromillions ticket.</p>', 'Friday 13th Euromillions Winners', 'Euromillions, Friday the 13th', 'Although there was no jackpot winners one would be hard pressed to call this Friday the 13th an unlucky day', 2, 1326715761, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Friday 13th January 2012 winners', '', '<p>Some may call it the unluckiest day, but was this Friday the 13th really that unlucky? Given today''s Euromillions result we submit that it was not</p>', NULL, NULL, 1326489902, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (67, 54, 'en', 'life_of_lottery_winners_chris_colin_weir', 'Life of Lottery Winners Chris & Colin Weir', '<p>In July 2011 a prize of €185,000,000 was claimed by Scottish couple Colin and Christine Weir. After winning the highest <a href="http://euromillions.com/">Euromillions</a> prize the couple came forward publicly. Six months into their huge Euromillions win and we take a look at the life of the biggest Euromillions winners to date. What plans do they have for their money and just how much his life changed for this loveable couple?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In an interview with local newspaper the <a href="http://www.largsandmillportnews.com/news/largs/articles/2011/11/18/419848-exclusive--theres-no-place-like-home-for-the-weirs/">Largs & Millport Weekly News</a>, Colin and Christine Weir reveal what''s going on in the house that Euromillions built.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many who win the lottery might be tempted to search out greener pastures, a life of nothing but blue skies and sunny days, for Colin and Christine Weir however Largs is where their heart is. They have purchased their dream home ''Knock House'' on the outskirts of their little Scottish town and they''re determined to remain part of the same community. With millions of euros at their disposal from the interest on their prize alone, the Weirs will never have to work again, so what is life at the stately Knock House like for the couple?</p>\r\n\r\n<img src="/images/news/knockhouse.jpg" align="left" />\r\n\r\n<p>Knock House (pictured) is a beautiful (if somewhat understated) 3 storey home with it''s own adjoining estate. Contrary to newspaper reports the house does not have its own cinema or swimming pool, though the pool could be a future option given Chris'' love of swimming. The house was valued at offers over £1,100,000, however the savvy couple snapped it up for £850,000 which could easily be one of the interest payments on their fortune from just one month! In terms of luxury the house boasts its own rambling gardens, small forest, green houses, stables and a walled garden. The walled garden itself is a listed part of land as it was once part of Knock Castle, a historical site just next door to the Weirs.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Colin and Christine Weir Speak About Their Win</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>For the first time the Weirs talk publicly about their incredible stroke of luck, “We certainly regard it as providential. I am a bit of a fatalist. However, I am not entirely sure what the reason is for being so lucky” Colin said. Chris talks a little more in depth saying “I believe that things do happen for a reason, and we also believe that with great wealth comes great responsibilities”. The couple are very keen to give as much as they can back to the community, having already donated a large sum to save the Waverley Paddle Steamer, Chris says “The Waverley is so iconic, it is high up our list of causes to help. The Waverley on the Clyde is something that goes back to our childhoods”.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The Weirs On Their Charitable Intentions</h3>ser\r\n\r\n<p>The couple look set to give aid to many different causes. They are willing to give millions but point out that giving away such huge sums of money isn''t so straightforward: “If you simply give a million pounds to anyone there is a 50% tax to be paid on it” says Colin, “We will set up a charitable foundation, spotlighting local charities that need funds”. Chris chips in “It takes a long time to set up a charitable foundation. We have to do it slowly because in order to help charities and local organisations we have to look at the tax implications for them” she adds “If we throw money at them just now they could be landed with a tax bill. “We have to set up the right structure first so that we can deal with the tax” says Colin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><blockquote>"We will set up a charitable foundation, spotlighting local charities that need funds"<span style="color:#000;font-size: 12px"> - Chris Wier</span></blockquote></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Expressing their noble intentions Colin has said “Through what we read in the Largs and Millport Weekly News we have concentrated on local organisations. For example, we read about the fund-raising campaign for Haylie House”, a local residential care home that could really benefit from their donation. To make things easier the money will no doubt be managed by an outside source as Colin says “We know how much we want to invest in a foundation and we have people who will sit on it with us to decide the good causes”</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>The Weirs Discuss New Responsibilities In Life</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>It seems that in becoming the 22nd richest people in Scotland, with a fortune that rivals that of David and Victoria Beckham, the Weirs haven''t forgotten their roots. So far, the Weirs have not let their new found riches go to their head, and will see that they don''t forget where their heart and home is. The renovations on their home are even handled by local tradesmen. While in their renovations some security measures have had to be implemented, the couple express that they feel safe and secure living in Largs. Colin does joke however “At one point I was going about with Chris and a lady from Camelot and people thought I had two female bodyguards!”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While one would expect a certain amount of relaxation following this enormous win there are actually many things to be done. Colin is currently overseeing maintenance work on the house and surrounding estate and Chris -who had been previously active in the mental health profession- is continuing her work with mental health charities. As Colin looks out over his grand estate he quips “We have come out of retirement into full time jobs!”. With regards to his responsibilities though Colin -ever the joker- continues “I have responsibilities”, he points to his much loved 18 year old cat Nala, “I have to take Nala for a walk, she prances about and I follow with a glass of red wine in hand”.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>On Travelling The World With €185,000,000</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The jet setting international life style may be the dream of many potential Lotto winners but having just returned from a European cruise on the Queen Elizabeth Chris says “Holidays are only holidays if you do them occasionally”. She goes on however to say that “I would love to go to China and Japan, but I have travelled a lot in the States and two places I would like to visit are Chicago and Seattle”. On the subject of travelling Colin jokes that he''d be just as happy to visit “Fuey” -a local Chinese restaurant. In all seriousness though he does fancy seeing the temples in Cambodia, but concludes with an old Scottish phrase “East, west, hame''s the best!”</p>\r\n\r\n<img src="/images/news/largstown.jpg" align="right" />\r\n\r\n<p>All in all the biggest cash prize winners of the Euromillions to date seem to have kept their feet firmly on the ground, local ground at that. From a moral stand point they cannot be faulted as their charity efforts will improve the community around them, meaning that the Scottish couple won''t be the only ones benefiting from their extraordinary luck.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Discussing Public Reaction To Their Win</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Some might shy away from becoming local celebrities in fear that it may ruin their privacy and friendships. Initially the most popular rumour was that the Weirs had fled the country to Spain after being harassed by countless begging letters! In truth the couple had gone somewhere much closer to home: Brighton, England.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<blockquote>"There was the idea that we were holed up somewhere because we were terrified of begging letters"<span style="color:#000;font-size: 12px"> - Chris Wier<span></blockquote>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“The truth is we had business decisions to make and we like Brighton”. Make no mistake begging letters were sent in their hundreds but the Weirs had cannily paid tribute to their local post office, who did not deliver any that were not addressed correctly, and the more genuine ones were handled by the professionals at Camelot.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When asked if they feel they are treated differently by the people of Largs Chris quickly answers “I don''t think so. We''re no different as people. People still say congratulations, that''s where it begins and ends and we have not found people intrusive. Obviously some people ask us how it feels. Most people don''t want to bother you and those you know us say ''hiya''”. €185,000,000 would be enough to alter how your friends behave toward you but so far that has been a part of the Weir''s lives that haven''t changed “Our friends have been wonderful. We know the people we are friends with. They are the same people we have always been friends with” says Chris.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Of course as you might come to expect from this couple by now they haven''t forgotten the people who have always been there for them, in fact it has been a priority to look after family and friends. “That has been one of the most pleasurable things” admitted Chris “My parents are still alive and my family would have done the same for us if the boot had been on the other foot”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not everyone has been so polite about their big win however and amongst accusations from some  that €185 million is too much for any one couple to win, and that the prize would have been better split between 100 different winners. The Weir''s response is quite simply that it isn''t possible because the nature of the game is such that it''s designed to have a massive jackpot, which attracts the ticket buyers in the first place. Colin said “There is no option in the lottery game”.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>The Weirs On Their Lack Of Anonymity</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The big question on many minds though is “Why did the Weir''s go public with their win”? Chris is keen to point out that at no time did Camelot actually suggest they go public as the winners. Colin''s stance was “You can''t hide that some of money. People would think you were money laundering”. Chris wholeheartedly agrees saying “You can''t hide it. If you were going to be anonymous you are not telling friends and family. I don''t think anyone would want to make their life like that. You would be spinning stories for the rest of your lives. For people to remain anonymous about winning the lottery.....they must be telling some tall tales”. Anonymity would be even more difficult for the Weir''s given their charitable intentions for the money. They point out that when it comes to giving huge sums of money to people and causes there had to be some way to verify that the money is legitimate.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<img align="left" src="/images/news/weirshappy.jpg" />\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Colin talks about how even before the breakthrough of social media on the world wide web with things like Facebook etc people couldn''t remain anonymous, and that it would be impossible in today''s world. He goes on to say “Being anonymous was a non starter. We didn''t want to go away and live on a small island with no contact with the people who are important to us”. The couple state almost simultaneously “We couldn''t have stayed in Largs and kept it quiet”.</p>\r\n\r\n<br />\r\n<h4>Colin & Christine Weir, The Humble Multi-Millionaires</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Far from the money going to their heads the Weirs seem to be taking it all in their stride. Purchases with their money include an Arthur Montford style jacket and a tractor which Chris describes as “more like a large lawnmower than you sit on”. The couple also wanted to take a step into the 21st century by making a computer one of their first purchases to take down to Brighton with them. Colin an avid football fan of Barcelona and local teams Partick Thistle and Largs Thistle said he would love to buy a season ticket for Barcelona''s Nou Camp stadium but he did not fancy having to climb the stairs with his arthritic legs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In reference to his generous donation to the SNP party and their invite from Alex Salmond to join him for dinner Colin said “We go back a long way”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Seven months ago when the Weir''s walked into their local RS McColls newsagent on Moorburn road they had no idea that they were about to buy a whole new quality of life. Fortunately though it seems that while life has gotten better for them, the money hasn''t changed them as people. So far they have maintained their respect and love for the town they call home and the people therein. They are determined to make their small town on the coast of Scotland a better place to live, and we believe there hasn''t been a sweeter sentiment expressed by any other Euromillions winner to date.</p>', 'Life of Lottery Winners Chris & Colin Weir', 'euromillions winners, winners, lottery, chris, colin, weir, scotland, largs', 'Six months into their huge Euromillions win and we take a look at the life of the biggest Euromillions winners to date.', 2, 1326716289, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Life of Lottery Winners Chris & Colin Weir', '', '<p>Imagine how life would change 6 months into winning €185,000,000. For one lucky Scottish couple that dream is a reality, and in a recent interview we find out more about the new lives of Colin and Christine Weir</p>', 'Chris & Colin Weir', 'Lottery Winners', 1326714123, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (68, 55, 'es', 'proximo_sorteo_martes_17012012', 'Próximo Sorteo: Martes 17/01/2012', '<p>El sorteo del Viernes 13 de enero de 2012 ponía en juego un bote de 28 millones de euros y nadie acertó toda su selección con la combinación ganadora. Por lo tanto, se trata de una tercera renovación consecutiva de bote que será puesta en juego en el próximo sorteo Euromillones, este martes 17 de enero. Para este sorteo, el bote que pone en juego la lotería se estima en €35 millones.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>La <a href="http://euromillions.com/es/renovacion-del-bote-euromillones" title="Información acerca de la renovación del bote Euromillones">renovación del bote Euromillones</a> es la clave de la lotería ya que permite ofrecer botes increíbles. Lo que atrae a más jugadores y lo que aumenta la suma de los premios ya que dependen del número de entradas que recibe un sorteo. La lotería Euromillones propone un sorteo cada martes y cada viernes, por lo tanto, existe la posibilidad de directamente comprar entradas para los 10 próximos sorteos Euromillones. También se puede volver a jugar las mismas selecciones de manera automática en todos los sorteos que se vienen, sin tener que preocuparse más por los números.</p>', 'Próximo Sorteo: 17/01/2012', 'Euromillones, Sorteo Euromillones, Resultado Euromillones.', 'El próximo sorteo Euromillones tendrá lugar este martes 17 de enero de 2012 y pone en juego la suma de 35 millones de euros.', 2, 1326731877, 8, 'Ido S', 'Sorteo martes 17/01/2012', NULL, 'El sorteo de este martes pondrá en juego un bote de €35 000 000 y ya se pueden comprar entradas.', NULL, NULL, 1326731877, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (69, 56, 'en', 'tuesday_17th_january_euromillions_winners', 'Tuesday 17th January Euromillions Winners', '<p>The third rollover this month might pave the way for a massive jackpot in a few weeks, but only time will tell. This Tuesday''s draw has given us a total of 1,849,517 winners which is roughly the average amount of cash prize winners in any Euromillions draw.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A lucky number 7 people matched 5 main numbers and 1 Lucky Star to claim the second place prize which sits at €156, 265.91. A further 9 people will boast to claiming the second place prize of €40,513.38, by only matching 5 main numbers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>people have managed to net themselves €3,798.13 by matching 4 main numbers and 2 Lucky Stars. A huge amount of 851 people have correctly matched 4 main numbers and 1 Lucky Star to gain a big return on investment of €187.45. An even larger amount of people (1492) have won a cash prize of €106.92 by matching 4 main numbers with no Lucky Stars.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Just over double the amount of winners in 7th place will still be happy to take home €54.39 by matching 3 main numbers and 2 Lucky Stars. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The bulk of the winners -all 1,845,015 of them- will still receive a good return for their ticket cost winning at least €4 each. This Tuesday''s rollover leaves us with Friday''s jackpot just shy of €50 million Euro; an estimated €48,000,000 will be up for grabs and tickets are sure to go quickly, so make sure you''re equipped to win it by purchasing your ticket now.</p>', 'Tuesday 17th January Euromillions Winners', 'Tuesday 17th, Euromillions Result, Euromillions Winners', 'A third rollover will see this Friday''s jackpot at €48,000,000 ', 2, 1326836192, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Tuesday 17th January Euromillions Winners', '/images/news/euromillions_1.jpg', '<p>Plenty of prize winners with this Tuesday''s draw, but with no jackpot winner the prize will rollover for the third time</p>', 'Euromillions Prize Winners', 'An average number of Euromillions Winners', 1326836192, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (70, 57, 'en', 'welsh_cage_fighter_wins_euromillions', 'Welsh Cage Fighter Wins Euromillions', '<p>A professional cage fighter who only 5 years ago was battling for his life after a near fatal motorcycle accident has scooped a clean £1,000,000 (€1.2000,946) in the Euromillions <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-uk-millionaire-raffle">UK Millionaire Raffle</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Gavin Davies, 29, from Cimla, Neath in North Wales had spent 9 months in hospital in 2006 recovering from a motorcycle accident that could have almost killed him. He said “The last few years have been very up and down, but this win couldn''t have come at a better time.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The draw in question was actually for the 27th of December, but he had no idea he had won until now as he had forgotten to check his ticket. He may not have even checked his tickets if it hadn''t been for his grandparents who had urged him to check the <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">latest results</a>. The former martial arts teacher said “I was feeding our newborn son and as soon as I had got him to sleep, I decided to go out to the car to get my tickets which I had been keeping in the glove compartment”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“I had written down the number printed in the local paper, and checked them against my <a href="http://euromillions.com/">Euromillions tickets</a>. When I saw the match I couldn''t believe it” he said, “I went online to the <a href="http://www.national-lottery.co.uk/player/p/home.ftl">National Lottery website</a> to confirm it and I was jumping up and down with excitement as soon as I realised it was mine”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr Davies, who has just recently become a father, plans to make his first purchase a Lamborghini Spyder which retails at roughly £200,000 -€239,614. “I have always dreamed of owning a Lamborghini, and I will also be treating my partner to a new car as well as taking my mum and the rest of the family on a holiday”. The 29 year old cage fighter has sensible plans for the remainder of the money saying “The rest of the money will be spent on a property and on other investments for mine and my families future”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr Davies had purchased 4 tickets for the draw on the 27th and has also always had big ambitions which have now been fulfilled: “I always knew I would win the lottery one day, and now my dreams have come true”.</p>', 'Welsh Cage Fighter Wins Euromillions', 'Welsh Euromillions Winner, Euromillions, Millionaire Raffle', 'A millionaire raffle winner from December 2011 has come forward to claim his prize', 2, 1326884674, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Welsh Cage Fighter Wins Euromillions', '', '<p>Welsh Cage Fighter finally comes forward to claim a million he had won in 2011</p>', 'Euromillions Winner Gavin Davies', 'Winner of £1,000,000 Cage fighter Gavin Davies', 1326882469, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (71, 56, 'es', 'sorteo_martes_17_de_enero_de_2012', 'Sorteo martes 17 de enero de 2012', '<p>La tercera renovación de bote de esta semana ponía en juego un bote de €36 millones. En el sorteo de este martes 17 de enero de 2012 hubo 1 849 517 ganadores, lo que representa el promedio de ganadores de premio en un sorteo Euromillones.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nadie acertó todos los números con la combinación ganadora del sorteo. Por lo tanto, el bote se renovará en el próximo sorteo con un aumento considerable. Hubo 7 ganadores de la segunda categoría de premio, que representa 5 aciertos comunes más un número estrella. Este premio alcanza los 156 265 euros y hubo un ganador en España. Solamente 9 personas ganaron el tercer premio que representa, para este sorteo, 40 513 euros y se ganaba por hacer coincidir 5 números principales.</P>\r\n\r\n<p>El próximo sorteo Euromillones tendrá lugar el viernes 20 de enero de 2012 y pondrá en juego un bote estimado en €48 millones.</p>', 'Sorteo martes 17 de enero', 'euromillones, sorteo Euromillones, Resultado Euromillones.', 'El sorteo Euromillones del martes 17 de enero de 2012 ponía en juego un bote de €35 millones.  ', 2, 1331193377, 6, 'David Bonnici', 'Tuesday 17th January Euromillions Winners', '/images/news/euromillions_1.jpg', 'Último Resultado Euromillones:\r\n</br>\r\n</br>\r\n12 - 22 - 30 - 31 - 44 / 05 - 06\r\n</br>\r\n</br>\r\nGanadores: 1 849 517\r\n</br>\r\n</br>\r\nBote: €36 496 416\r\n</br>\r\n</br>\r\nNo hubo ganador de primera categoría así que el bote se renovará en el próximo sorteo Euromillones este viernes 20 de enero de 2012.', 'Boleto Euromillones', 'Boleto Euromillones', 1326901597, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (72, 58, 'en', 'more_information_on_french_winner_of_27_000_000', 'More Information On French Winner Of €27,000,000', '<p>On December 2nd a jackpot of €27,000,000 was claimed by a <a href="http://euromillions.com/jackpot-won-in-france-december" target="_blank">French winner</a> who might still be choosing to remain anonymous but has revealed a little more information on his ticket purchase. The numbers he had been using were the birthdays of his children and he had been playing them since 1987 on his favourite lottery games.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the year of 1987 he had missed out on winning 700,000 Francs (€106,714) on the one week he hadn''t played a ticket and his lucky numbers came up in a draw. Since then he has been playing his children''s birthdays as lottery numbers religiously for the past 25 years. The numbers have finally come around again in his favour, now though to the tune of €27 million, which he plans to share with 14 members of his family.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In other Euromillions news, two winners in the UK <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-uk-millionaire-raffle" target="_blank">Millionaire Raffle</a> have emerged from Aberdeen in Scotland. The first man known only as Mr M was one of the 25 guaranteed millionaires from the draw on Friday 23rd December. The second known as Mr R won his huge sum on the 30th of December. Both players will receive £1,000,000 -€1.2 million. A Camelot spokeswoman said “There must have been something special in the water in Aberdeenshire over Christmas”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Wales another Millionaire Raffle winner <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/210/welsh-cage-fighter-wins-euromillions" target="_blank">Gavin Davies</a> is still coming to terms with his big win. The Cage fight who lives with his partner and their month old baby son has been investing £25 a week in the lottery since he was 16 says “I want to turn £1 million to into £10 million”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The new millionaire who has already spent £150,000 on a Lamborghini Spyder is keen to create more wealth with his winnings but admits “I haven''t thought how and I''m open to advice”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A Spokesperson for Camelot said “Every winner over £500,000 is offered a financial panel”, and continued “They can sit down with an independent financial adviser, a banker and a legal adviser, at our cost, who will answer any questions they may have”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“That could be about inheritance tax, gifted tax, or about investment options. It is then up to the winner to contact these people if they want to have a relationship going forward”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These new insights into how Camelot aids UK winners of large sums in the Euromillions speaks volumes on how much the company cares for its winners and their future happiness with their new found fortunes.</p>', 'More Information On French Winner Of €27,000,000', 'Euromillions News, French Euromillions Winner, UK Millionaire Raffle', 'More information about a French winner, some Aberdeen Millionaire Raffle winners, and more news on Cage fighter Gavin Davies', 2, 1326988746, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'December 2011 French Winner More Information', '', '<p>More information about several Euromillions winners in today''s news.</p>', 'French Euromillions Winner', 'The Euromillions Winner From France', 1326988102, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (73, 59, 'en', 'englishman_wins_big_with_virtual_euromillions_ticket', 'Englishman Wins Big With Virtual Euromillions Ticket', '<p>Another Euromillions <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-uk-millionaire-raffle" target="_blank">Millionaire Raffle</a> winner has come forward to claim his prize. The ticket holder is from Derby and his ticket was entirely virtual. The man known only as “Mr B” has won £1,000,00 (€1.2 million) after purchasing his ticket online for the Euromillions draw on the 23rd of December 2011. His prize was won as part of the Millionaire Month held in the UK that created a total of 50 millionaires in one month over November and December.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A spokesperson from UK lottery organiser Camelot has said of the win “Well done to Mr B, he has banked this amazing prize with just a few simple clicks – he didn''t even have to pick up a ticket. If you play interactively, not only do we check your numbers, we also let you know you have won – it couldn''t be easier”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Playing Euromillions online is quickly becoming the most popular way to enter the game. With tonight''s jackpot at an enormous €48,000,000 there has never been a better time to start purchasing your tickets online. Why brave the winter''s cold and rain to enter tonight''s draw, when you can take the opportunity of a lifetime from the comfort of your own home?</p>', 'Englishman Wins Big With Virtual Euromillions Ticket', 'Euromillions, Euromillions Online, Play Euromillions Online', 'Another UK Millionaire Raffle winner claims his prize after purchasing his Euromillions ticket over the internet', 2, 1327058467, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Derby winner wins big with virtual ticket', '/images/news/euromillions_4.jpg', '<p>With more and more people playing online it''s little wonder the latest Euromillions winner is claiming his prize from a ticket purchased online</p>', 'Online Euromillions Ticket', 'A winner by purchasing his ticket online', 1327058467, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (74, 60, 'es', 'ganador_de_48_895_464_del_sorteo_del_viernes_20_de_enero_de_2012', 'Ganador de €48 895 464 del sorteo del viernes 20 de enero de 2012', '<p>El sorteo Euromillones del viernes 20 de enero de 2012 proponía un bote de 48 millones de euros. En total, en este sorteo participaron 3 384 129 entradas y una de estas acertó todos los números con la combinación ganadora del sorteo. La combinación ganadora del sorteo de este viernes 20 de enero de 2012 es: 02 - 10 - 22 - 27 - 28 / 06 - 08.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>El boleto que ha acertado todos los números con la combinación ganadora del sorteo se compró en el Reino Unido y el afortunado ganador se lleva la increíble suma de €48 895 464. Por lo tanto, el próximo sorteo Euromillones que tendrá lugar el martes 24 de enero de 2012 propondrá el bote inicial de 15 millones de euros.</p>', 'Ganador sorteo 20/01/2012', 'euromillones, resultados euromillones, bote euromillones.', 'El sorteo Euromillones del 20/01/2012 ponía en juego un bote de €48 000 000 y un boleto validado en el Reino Unido..', 2, 1331193356, 8, 'Ido S', 'Ganador del bote en el sorteo del 20 de enero de 2012', NULL, 'Último Resultado Euromillones:\r\n</br>\r\n</br>\r\n02 - 10 - 22 - 27 - 28 / 06 - 08\r\n</br>\r\n</br>\r\nGanadores: 3 384 129\r\n</br>\r\n</br>\r\nBote: €48 895 464\r\n</br>\r\n</br>\r\nHubo un ganador de primera categoría en el Reino Unido! Por lo tanto, el afortunado ganador se lleva la suma de €48 895 464.', NULL, NULL, 1327142403, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (75, 61, 'en', 'huge_rollover_jackpot_has_one_winner', 'Huge Rollover Jackpot Has One Winner', '<p>This Friday''s drawn numbers 2, 10, 22, 27, 28 and Lucky Stars 6 and 8 have all been successfully matched! The lucky ticket that has all 7 numbers is in the UK and the magnificent jackpot of €48,895,464 should be winging its way there as soon as the winner claims their prize. They will join a host of other big Euromillions winners in the UK, and their prize will make them the 7th richest Euromillions winner there.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Previously the UK has been host to such big winners as Colin and Christine Weir, winners of the largest ever jackpot of €185 million. As well as Dave and Angela Dawes who are currently enjoying their fortune of over €121 million. Hopefully the latest British winner is quick to come forward and make themselves known to the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A spokesperson for Camelot has said “This is fantastic news – we''re absolutely delighted to have yet another huge Euromillions win here in the UK. We can''t wait for the ticket holder to come forward”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“We have plenty of champagne on ice and look forward to welcoming the lucky ticket holder into The National Lottery millionaires'' club”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the second prize tier there were 3 winners of €619,952.38, a sizeable amount that will surely put big smiles on their faces. In fact there will be smiles on the faces of 457,870 ticket holders who can claim a cash prize. 12 of those winners matched 5 main numbers only and are entitled to a generous €51,662.70 each. Thousands more ticket holders (3572 to be precise) have made a big return on their investment by matching 4 main numbers and 2 Lucky Stars to win €3,923.75</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This Tuesday''s jackpot will be reset to the seemingly modest sum of €15,000,000 and we wish all our players good luck with their entry.</p>', 'Huge Rollover Jackpot Has One Winner', 'Euromillions, rollover, jackpot', 'Friday''s Euromillions rollover jackpot of €48,000,000 could soon be in the hands of 1 lucky winner', 2, 1327151447, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Friday 20th January 2012 winners', '/images/news/euromillions_1.jpg', '<p>The immense rollover jackpot of €48,000,000 could be claimed by 1 lucky winner. Have you checked your ticket yet?</p>', 'Winning Euromillions Ticket', 'Is your ticket the winner of €48,000,000?', 1327151447, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (76, 62, 'en', 'euromillions_jackpot_rule_changes', 'Euromillions Jackpot Rule Changes', '<p align="justify">As of the 17th of February 2012 a few amendments will be made to the <a href="http://euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> jackpot rules. This small amendment should be largely beneficial to Euromillions players as it guarantees further pay outs and limited rollovers when the Euromillions jackpot pool cap is reached. \r\n\r\nAt the moment the rules state that the jackpot cannot go any higher than $190 million, however right now it is possible for that jackpot to remain the same for as long as the rollovers continue. Also as it stands when that jackpot of €190 million is won, the maximum is increased by €5 million.</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">In the new rulings, when the <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-prize-structure">€190 million jackpot pool cap</a> is reached the first prize can only rollover for another two draws, and the actual maximum will be fixed indefinitely. Meaning that the Euromillions maximum jackpot will be permanently fixed at €190 million whether it is won or not. It has been stated though that if the jackpot reaches $195 million before the 17th of February using the current rulings then it will be fixed at that amount instead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">So after the 17th of February, if the jackpot hits it''s maximum and rolls over twice again after that, the third time it rolls over, the prize money will cascade down to the winners in the next tier, i.e. those players who have succeeded in matching 5 main numbers and 1 Lucky Star. This will certainly make the multi-rollovers a lot more interesting given that the odds of matching 5 main numbers and 1 Lucky Star are only 1 in 64,739,894 compared to the <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-odds">Euromillions odds</a> of matching all 7 numbers which are 1 in 116,531,800.</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">All in all, the new Euromillions rule changes will make the game more much exciting when a massive €190 million rollover comes around!</p>', 'Euromillions Jackpot Rule Changes', 'Euromillions Jackpot, Euromillions Rollover, Euromillions Rule Change', 'As of Friday the 17th of February the Euromillions will experience some small rules changes', 2, 1377240705, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euromillions Jackpot Rule Changes', '/images/news/euromillions_2.jpg', '<p align="justify"><h2>Discover the small rule changes that have made Euromillions a whole lot more exciting!</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1327336989, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (77, 63, 'en', 'state_of_illinois_now_set_to_sell_lottery_online', 'State Of Illinois Now Set To Sell Lottery Online', '<p>This year in March or April the state of Illinois in America plans to be the first state to make their lottery games available online. The move comes after enquires Illinois made regarding the <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/194/new-justice-department-ruling" target=_"blank">USA lottery</a> games and their availability online. The possibility to sell tickets online could help the cash-strapped state in their time of need by attracting up to 500,000 more ticket sales to Illinois'' Mega Moolah game, nevermind the possible increase in Mega Millions and Powerball ticket sales.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With consideration to the fact that the Mega Moolah jackpots exceed $100 million (€79,953,103) around 40 times a year, the online ticket sales are expected to quickly take off. The state of Illinois looks to benefit greatly from this increase in sales as every Mega Moolah ticket sold brings them 42 cents, which quickly adds up to bring in a lot of revenue. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tickets will only be available to Illinois residents over the age of 18, and payments will be accepted online via credit card. There has been a test program approved for offering this service online since 2009, but it wasn''t until near the end of last year that the Department Of Justice has approved of the sale of lottery tickets online on a federal level.  You can read more about the state of Illinois getting the all clear for the project <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/194/new-justice-department-ruling" target=_"blank">here</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While these tickets will only be available online to Illinois residents, we have made Euromillions tickets available online worldwide. Tonights jackpot is €15,000,000 and you could be in with a chance of winning it. Purchasing your ticket from where you''re sitting right now is as easy as 1, 2, 3. With only a few hours left till the draw, you can take your chance to win the millions today, and if your ticket loses, we''ll credit you the money back to have a second chance!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you''d love to enter to win this weeks USA Powerball jackpot of $120 million (€92,277,225.39), or the Mega Millions jackpot of $71 million (€54,607,299.73), then we recommend you purchase your Powerball ticket from anywhere in the world <a href="http://ads.playukinternet.com/tracking.php/text/3451/12885/3929003/8502" target=_"blank">here</a>, and your Mega Millions tickets <a href="http://ads.playukinternet.com/tracking.php/text/3451/12959/3929003/8503" target=_"blank">here</a>.</p>', 'State Of Illinois Now Set To Sell Lottery Online', 'Online Lottery, Lottery Online, American Lottery', 'After a new ruling from the State Department in America, one state is gearing up for some big ticket sales online', 2, 1327404454, 3, 'Alison Davis', 'State Of Illinois Gear Up To Sell Tickets Online', '', '<p>Soon the first American state will make it''s initial foray into online lottery ticket sales</p>', 'American Lotteries Online', 'Within months Americans will be able to buy lotto tickets online', 1327402842, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (78, 64, 'en', 'winners_of_fridays_euromillions_jackpot_go_public', 'Winners Of Friday''s Euromillions Jackpot Go Public', '<p>Over the weekend Catherine (35) and Gareth Bull (40) of Mansfield, Nottingham England had been sitting on a huge secret; their numbers had come in on the Euromillions and a fortune of £40,627,241 (€51,237,328) was going to soon be on it''s way. Their 9 and 10 year old sons Declan and Joel had a regular weekend of events, playing football with their friends and making a birthday trip to the cinema, all the while their parents spoke in whispers on their phones barely able to contain their delight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Come Monday as the children went to school, they still had no idea that their parents had beaten the 1 in 116,531,800 odds by matching all 7 numbers 2, 10, 22, 27, 28 and Lucky Stars 6 and 8. After this spectacular luck and huge cash windfall the family still plan not to ''splash the cash''. Gareth however does have his eyes on his own box at Old Trafford to watch his favourite team: Manchester United. Of course his plans also include picking up a new set of wheels in the form of a Range Rover Sport.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No enormous win would be complete without a plan to buy a villa abroad, and the couple also intend to take their children to Disney World in Florida. With holidays and foreign homes in mind already Catherine Bull has said that they have no intention to move away permanently “I like Mansfield, it''s a nice place to live. We have to be realistic though – it''s been a bizarre couple of days but we just have to take each day as it comes. But it''s really good news".</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Medical insurance worker Catherine wants to spend her money at home; “I''m not really a huge fan of shopping – I have clothes that have been in my wardrobe for years. I want a carpet for my landing because it''s terrible – nobody''s allowed upstairs. It bothers me. I get to the top of the stairs every day and I''m like ''I hate that carpet''”\r\n\r\n<p>The couple also have plans to look after their closest friends and family, as well as make donations to charities. Top on their charity list are those which help to fight against breast cancer, as Mr Bull''s mother successfully beat the disease and currently a friend of Catherine''s is battling it also. With as much money as Kylie Minogue, Mick Hucknall  or Pete Townshend it''s little wonder the couple are keen to be so generous.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The fateful ticket was purchased by Gareth while he was stopping at a shop with three colleagues to avoid the rain. The numbers were generated at random as he bought a Lucky Dip. At first glance he thought that only 2 Lucky Stars had been matched, but upon closer inspection he quickly realised he had all the numbers. At this point he raced to his wife to tell her the good news.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Catherine said: “He came into the bedroom as white as a sheet with the ticket shaking in his hand. I thought he was playing a joke on me at first but I couldn''t believe it when I saw the numbers online. Declan keeps telling us that we are just wasting our money on the lottery because all the tickets end up in the bin – but you have to be in it to win it.”</p>', 'Winners Of Friday''s Euromillions Jackpot Go Public', 'EUromillions Jackpot Winner, Friday''s Euromillions Jackpot WInner, Gareth Bull, Christine Bull', 'No longer a secret to the world, the Euromillions winners from the UK who have netted themselves over €50 million have come forward publicly', 2, 1327492324, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Winners of Jackpot Friday 20th January Go Public', '', '<p>No longer a secret to the world, the Euromillions winners from the UK who have netted themselves over €50 million have come forward publicly</p>', 'Euromillions Jackpot Winners Gareth and Catherine Bull', 'The winners of over €50 million, Gareth and Catherine Bull Of The UK', 1327492260, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (79, 65, 'en', 'lottery_jackpot_or_not', 'Lottery Jackpot? Or Not?', '<p>The £41 million (€40,953,812) jackpot won on Friday the 20th had been attributed to a man from Workington, West Cumbria. Les Smallwood, the former director of Workington, town had become subject of a rumour that the jackpot was his. Of course after it was reported that the real winners were <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/218/winners-of-fridays-euromillions-jackpot-go-public">Gareth and Catherine Bull</a> the rumours were quashed, for a few days however Mr Smallwood endured quite an experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Naturally the rumour spread like wildfire and his ''win'' had been the most popular gossip in the town of Workington for those few days. Mr Smallwood''s son Jordan faced a slew of congratulating Facebook messages and wall posts. Lauren Hunter wrote “Wow can''t believe what''s happened today! You''re so lucky. Just remember who''s the best sister and best niece ever”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A friend of Jordan eventually wrote “Has your pap actually won the lottery or is this one massive wind-up?”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr Smallwood eventually confirmed that he had not won the money. Many organisations had tried to contact him to verify the situation, and the eventual -and only- result, came in the form of a text message sent by Les to say “No I haven''t won. Wish I had”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Friday 27th''s Euromillions numbers failed to produce a jackpot winner therefore this Tuesday''s jackpot will be a triple rollover worth €33 million. With 4 people on Friday winning just shy of half a million, and another 16 winning €37,000 isn''t it time that you got your ticket?</p>', 'Lottery Jackpot? Or Not?', 'Jackpot Rumors, Gareth and Catherine Bull', 'Meet the man who''s whole village was alive with the rumor that he''d won €50 million, when he hadn''t', 2, 1327920716, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Les Smallwood, jackpot rumors', '', '<p>Les Smallwood, sadly not a Euro Millions Winner</p>', 'Euromillions Winner', 'Unfortunately not a Euromillions winner this time!', 1327919941, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (80, 66, 'en', 'unclaimed_euromillions_prize', 'Unclaimed Euromillions Prize', '<p>A player from the supposedly unlucky draw on the last Friday the 13th, is holding a winning <a href="http://www.euromillions.com/">Euromillions</a> ticket worth €179,575.26. The numbers drawn on that fateful date were 13, 14, 21, 27, 39 and Lucky Stars 6 and 8, the winner of the big cash prize that currently remains unclaimed has successfully matched all 5 main numbers and 1 of the Lucky Stars. The ticket holder might be biding their time before collecting their winnings, but they should be aware that they have until 23:00 GMT on Wednesday July 11th to grab their cash or it will slip from their grasp.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Should the prize remain unclaimed after that date, then the cash and any interest it has generated will join the other €27 billion that has already been generated for Good Causes within the UK. So either way the money will go toward brightening somebodies day! All we know about the winner is that the ticket was purchased in St Helens, England. Did you buy a ticket in that area?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A spokesperson for the National Lottery organisers in the UK said: “We''re desperate to find this mystery ticket holder and unite them with their winnings – this amazing prize could really make a huge difference to somebody''s life. We''re urging everyone to check their old tickets again or look anywhere a missing ticket could be hiding.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“Try checking in the pockets of clothing, in wallets, bags and down the back of the sofa – someone out out there could literally be sitting on a fortune!”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“We have the champagne on ice and our fingers crossed that the lucky winner comes forward to claim their win”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We at <a href="http://www.euromillions.com">Euromillions.com</a> also hope to see the cash in the hands of it''s rightful owner. However we look forward in anticipation -tickets in hand- for tonight''s big €33,000,000 jackpot. Don''t worry about possibly missing out on a huge cash prize when your numbers come in, because with Euromillions.com you cannot lose your ticket. There''s just a few hours to go so buy your tickets now.</p>', 'Unclaimed Euromillions Prize', 'Euromillions Prize, Unclaimed Euromillions', 'The draw on Friday the 13th this January may turn out to be a very unlucky one for one UK ticket holder...', 2, 1328000100, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Big Euromillions Prize Unclaimed Friday 13th', '/images/news/reachskymoney.jpg', '<p>Friday the 13th of January 2012 might turn out to be an extremely unlucky day for one Euromillions ticket holder</p>', 'Unclaimed Euromillions', 'An Unclaimed Euromillions Prize', 1328000100, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (81, 67, 'en', 'euromillions_winners_31st_january', 'Euromillions Winners 31st January', '<p>Friday''s estimated jackpot of €45,000,000 comes as the result of yesterday''s 4th consecutive rollover. Statistically if the jackpot rolls over one more time it''ll have a far higher likelihood of going over the €100,000,000 mark. Ticket sales for this Friday will already see a huge increase though as there is a highly sought after prize now on offer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regardless of the <a href="http://www.euromillions.com">Euro Millions</a> jackpot going without a winner, there were still a total of 1,566,746 tickets that matched enough numbers for a cash prize. Ranging from the 863,991 people who matched 2 main numbers only to win €4.65 each, to the 3 very lucky people who missed the jackpot by 1 Lucky Star (matching every other number) to be eligible for €356,846.45 each.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the other big prize winners were the tickets that matched 5 main numbers only to win €59,474.41. As well as a respectable number of 42 people who can claim €4,248.17 for matching 4 main numbers and 2 Lucky Stars. We hope that none of these <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-prize-structure">Euromillions prizes</a> go unclaimed!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Were the numbers 9, 34, 38, 43, 45 and Lucky Stars 4 and 2 the right numbers for you? Have you checked your ticket yet? If not check the latest <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results" title="latest euromillions results">results</a> and see if you''ve won a cash prize. You should also prepare for Friday''s enormous prize by ensuring your next ticket is at the ready.</p>', 'Euromillions Winners 31st January', 'Euromillions Winners, Euromillions Prizes', 'The fourth consecutive rollover will pave the way for bigger jackpots in the coming draws', 2, 1328091646, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euromillions Winners 31st January', '/images/news/euromillions_2.jpg', '<p>Yet another draw without a jackpot winner, but have you checked your tickets yet?</p>', 'Euromillions Ticket', 'A possibly jackpot winning ticket being filled out', 1328085311, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (82, 68, 'en', 'unclaimed_millionaire_raffle_ticket_in_the_uk', 'Unclaimed Millionaire Raffle Ticket In The UK', '<p>Another £1,000,000 (€1,202,297) in Euromillions prize money might go unclaimed again in the UK as a millionaire raffle winning ticket has yet to be accounted for. The ''secret'' millionaire purchased the raffle ticket with the code <strong>NBJ899770</strong>, but may not even realise it. Maybe they purchased the ticket with no idea it was entered automatically into the raffle? Or maybe they''ve just not even bothered to check the result yet!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What we know for certain is that the ticket was purchased in the Hackney borough of London in anticipation of the draw held on Tuesday January 17th. The Euromillions numbers on that date were 12, 22, 30, 31, 44 and Lucky Stars 5 and 6, maybe that will jog the winner''s memory? If not then on Sunday the 15th July at 3pm their money and any interest it has generated will be donated directly to charitable causes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The National Lottery organisation in the UK are of course eager to find this winner, a spokesperson was quoted to say “We''re desperate to find this mystery ticket holder and unite them with their winnings – this amazing prize could really make a huge difference to somebody''s life as they start 2012.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Anyone in the UK who believes they have the winning ticket should call the National Lottery Line on 0845 910 0000.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tonight''s jackpot is a sizeable €45,000,000. You only have a few hours left to take the chance to win the prize of your life, and thankfully when you purchase your ticket online there''s no chance of your cash prize going unclaimed because you lost or forgot about your ticket! So what are you waiting for, have your ticket ready for this evenings draw!</p>', 'Unclaimed Millionaire Raffle Ticket In The UK', 'Euromillions, Unclaimed Prize, millionaire raffle', 'Another prize of over one million euros may go without a winner in the UK!', 2, 1328540756, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Unclaimed Millionaire Raffle Tickets 3rd February', '', '<p>Could more millions slip through the fingers of a careless UK ticket holder?</p>', 'Millionaire Raffle Ticket', 'An Unclaimed Millionaire Raffle Ticket', 1328268964, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (83, 69, 'de', 'freitags_jackpot_zum_vierten_mal_nicht_geknackt_wurde', 'Freitags Jackpot zum vierten Mal nicht geknackt wurde', '<p>Freitags Jackpot in der Höhe von € 45.000.000 EUR resultiert daraus, dass gestern der Jackpot zum vierten Mal nicht geknackt wurde.  Statistisch gesehen, wenn der Jackpot wieder nicht geknackt wird, hat er eine weit höhere Wahrscheinlichkeit über die € 100.000.000 EUR Grenze zu gehen. Ticketverkäufe für diesen Freitag werden enorm ansteigen, nachdem es jetzt einen begehrten Preis zu gewinnen gibt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unabhängig vom Jackpot ohne Gewinner, gab es immer noch insgesamt 1.566.746 Tickets, mit genügend passende Nummern, um einen Geldpreis zu gewinnen. Angefangen von den 863.911 Menschen, welche zwei Hauptnummern getippt hatten und jeweils € 4,65 EUR gewannen, bis zu den 3 sehr glücklichen Personen, die den Jackpot um einen Lucky Star (passend mit jeder anderen Zahlt) verpassten und jeweils € 356,846 EUR gewannen.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Einige der anderen großen Gewinner waren die Tickets, welche die fünf Hauptnummern passend hatten, zu jeweils € 59.474,41 EUR. Sowie eine beachtliche Anzahl von 42 Personen, die € 4.248,17 EUR erhalten für vier passende Hauptnummern und zwei Lucky Stars. Wir hoffen, dass niemand vergisst diese Euromillions Preise zu beanspruchen. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Wären die Nummern 9,34, 38, 43, 45 und die Lucky Stars 4 und 2 die richtigen Nummern für Sie gewesen? Haben Sie Ihr Ticket schon überprüft? Wenn nicht, tun Sie es jetzt und schauen Sie nach ob Sie gewonnen haben. Sie sollten sich auch für den enormen Preis am Freitag vorbereiten, indem Sie sicherstellen, dass Sie ihr Ticket rechtzeitig haben. </p>', 'Freitags Jackpot zum vierten Mal nicht geknackt', 'Freitag, Jackpot, Ergebnisse', 'Freitags Jackpot in der Höhe von € 45.000.000 EUR resultiert daraus, dass gestern der Jackpot zum vierten Mal nicht geknackt wurde.', 1, 1328482800, 9, 'Jenny Zimmerman', 'Freitags Jackpot zum vierten Mal nicht geknackt', '/Images/news/euromillions_4.jpg', '<p>Freitags Jackpot in der Höhe von € 45.000.000 EUR resultiert daraus, dass gestern der Jackpot zum vierten Mal nicht geknackt wurde.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1328482800, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (84, 70, 'en', 'premier_league_footballer_takes_punt_on_euromillions', 'Premier League Footballer Takes Punt On Euromillions', '<p>Friday''s <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euromillions numbers</a> of 16, 19, 20, 25, 28 and Lucky Stars 1 and 10 have pushed the jackpot up to a whopping €53,000,000. At this stage the odds are stacked in favour of the jackpot continuing to rollover and reach levels of over €100,000,000. Whether it does or not however we will now see a huge rise in ticket sales for all the subsequent draws until this big prize is won.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The mountain of cash even attracted the attention of Queens Park Rangers captain Joey Barton. The 29 year old Premier League footballer purchased £70 (€84) worth of <a href="http://www.euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> tickets during a trip to his local newsagent. Joey and team mate Jamie Mackie (26) had gone to their shop to buy their newspapers and confectionery but ended up splashing out on many chances to win the €46 million.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A witness at the shop in West London said: “Joey put down a pile of notes and asked how many tickets it would buy, Jamie was laughing as they waited for the tickets to print out. Joey was chatty and polite. You''d think he wouldn''t need the money”. The footballer who who earns over €7237 each week did not win the big jackpot, but we''re curious to know if any of his winning tickets were among the 3,116,343 cash prize winners in Friday''s draw.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Friday''s winners include 10 people who successfully matched 5 main numbers and 1 Lucky Star to earn a substantial €185,085 each. In third place another 10 people will be claiming cash prizes of €61,695 each, then in fourth place winning a sweet €8,337 each are 37 ticket holders. A massive 1,984,640 lucky people managed to double their money by matching just 2 main numbers.</p>', 'Premier League Footballer Takes Punt On Euromillions', 'Joey Barton, Euromillions Winners', 'Queens Park Ranger''s captain and midfielder Joey Barton takes his chance to win €46 million', 2, 1328546285, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Joey Barton tries to win Euromillions', '', '<p>A great deal of winners in Friday''s draw but the jackpot goes unclaimed, even by famous QPR midfielder.</p>', 'Joey Barton Euromillions', 'Queens Park Rangers Captain Joey Barton', 1328522224, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (85, 71, 'en', 'uk_winner_bags_massive_euromillions_rollover', 'UK Winner Bags Massive EuroMillions Rollover', '<p>No-one has claimed the rollover prize yet but it will be the seventh highest UK winner ever and would make them as rich as the famous actor Hugh Grant. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The lucky numbers for Tuesday nights draw were 3, 15, 17, 28 and 33, with the Lucky Stars 2 and 4.\r\nThe <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/207/life-lottery-winners-chris-colin-weir">highest ever EuroMillions Jackpot</a> of €185 Million was won by the Scottish couple Colin and Chris Weir, from Largs in Ayrshire. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The second largest ever UK winner was an anonymous ticket holder with £113m and the third highest was Angela Dawes, from Cambridgeshire who scooped £101m last October. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>A spokesman for Camelot, who organise the EuroMillions lottery in the UK said: ‘We look forward to paying out this lucky ticket-holder and of course have the champagne on ice’. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>‘It is fantastic news to have another UK winner so soon after Gareth and Catherine Bull from Mansfield won £40million. \r\n‘These big draws help raise the £30million the National Lottery generates for good causes every week.’ Next Fridays EuroMillions Jackpot will be still a cool €15m so don’t miss out and get your tickets today. </p>', 'UK Winner Bags Massive EuroMillions Rollover', 'UK Winner 8th February', 'Once again a lucky EuroMillions player from the UK has scooped the Jackpot, a whooping  € 54 Million.', 2, 1328702336, 3, 'Alison Davis', 'UK Winner Bags Massive EuroMillions Rollover', '/Images/news/euromillions_4.jpg', NULL, 'Euromillions UK', NULL, 1328702336, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (86, 72, 'de', 'britischer_gewinner_sackt_riesigen_euromillionen_jackpot_ein', 'Britischer Gewinner sackt riesigen EuroMillionen Jackpot ein', '<p>Wieder einmal hat ein glücklicher Euromillionen Spieler aus Großbritannien den Jackpot gewonnen, unglaubliche € 54 Millionen Euro.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bis jetzt hat noch keiner den Jackpot für sich beansprucht, aber es wird der siebthöchste britische Gewinn sein und die glückliche Person so reich machen wie den berühmten Schauspieler Hugh Grant.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Die Glücks-Nummern für die Ziehung am Dienstag Abend lauten 3, 15, 17, 28 und 33, und die Lucky Stars lauten 2 und 4.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Der größte jemals gewonnene EuroMillionen Jackpot in der Höhe von € 185 Millionen Euro, wurde von dem schottische Ehepaar Colin und Chris Weir, aus Largs in Ayrshire, geknackt.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Der zweitgrößte britische Gewinn in der Höhe von £ 113 Millionen Pfund ging an einen anonymen Ticketinhaber und der dritthöchste Gewinn wurde im Oktober letzten Jahres von Angela Dawes, aus Cambridgeshire, in der Höhe von £ 101 Millionen Pfund gewonnen.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Ein Sprecher vom Camelot Unternehmen, welches die EuroMillionen Lotterie in Großbritannien organisiert, sagte: „ Wir freuen uns darauf dem glücklichen Ticketbesitzer seinen Gewinn auszuzahlen und selbstverständlich werden wir mit gekühlten Champagner anstoßen .“</p>\r\n\r\n<p>„Es ist eine fantastische Nachricht, dass wir so kurz nach dem Gareth und Catherine Bull, aus Mansfield, £ 40 Millionen Pfund gewonnen haben, einen weiteren Gewinner aus Großbritannien haben.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>„Diese großen Ziehungen tragen dazu bei, dass die Nationale Lotterie jede Woche 30 Millionen Pfund für gute Zwecke generiert.“</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Der Jackpot nächsten Freitag wird in der Höhe von tollen € 15 Millionen Euro sein, also verpassen Sie ihn nicht und kaufen Sie sich Ihr Ticket noch heute.</p>', 'Britischer Gewinner sackt riesigen EuroMillionen Jackpot ein', 'Britischer Gewinner, Euromillions, Euromillionen, Gewinner, 7 Januar', 'Wieder einmal hat ein glücklicher Euromillionen Spieler aus Großbritannien den Jackpot gewonnen, unglaubliche € 54 Millionen Euro.', 1, 1328721965, 9, 'Jenny Zimmerman', 'Britischer Gewinner sackt riesigen EuroMillionen Jackpot ein', '/Images/news/euromillions_2.jpg', NULL, 'Euromillionen Großbritannien', NULL, 1328721962, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (87, 71, 'es', 'ganador_del_bote_euromillones_del_sorteo_del_7_de_febrero_2012', 'Ganador del bote Euromillones del sorteo del 7 de febrero 2012', '<p>El ganador todavía no ha reclamado el premio del bote pero representa la séptima mayor ganancia del Reino Unido en la lotería Euromillones y volverá el ganador tan rico como el famoso actor <i>Hugh Grant</i>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>La combinación ganadora del sorteo Euromillones del martes 7 de febrero fue <b>03 - 15 - 17 - 28 - 33</b> con las estrellas <b>2 - 4</b>. El mayor bote ganado desde el lanzamiento de la lotería Euromillones alcanzaba €185 millones y estuvo ganado por la pareja escocesa Colin y Chris Weir, de Largs, en Ayrshire.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>La segunda ganancia más importante del Euromillones en el Reino Unido fue un ganador de 113 millones de libras (134 900 943€) y decidió permanecer en el anonimato. La tercera ganancia más importante en el Reino Unido era la de Angela Dawes, de Cambridgeshire, que ganó en octubre pasado un bote de 101 millones de euros.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Un portavoz de <b>Camelot</b>, que organiza la lotería Euromillones en el Reino Unido, dijo: “Esperamos a devolver el dinero al afortunado titular del boleto ganador, y por supuesto, tener el champán en el hielo”.\r\n\r\n<p>"Es una noticia fantástica tener otro ganador de bote en el Reino Unido tan pronto después de Gareth y Toro Catalina de Mansfield  que ganaron 40 millones de libras.” (47 752 546€) “Estos grandes sorteos ayudan a alcanzar los 30 millones de libras que la Lotería Nacional genera para buenas causas cada semana." </p>\r\n\r\n<p>El siguiente sorteo de la lotería Euromillones tendrá lugar este viernes 10 de febrero de 2012 y propone un bote de €15 millones así que no se lo pierdan y consiguen ya sus entradas.</p>', 'Ganador Euromillones 7 Febrero 2012', 'euromillones, ganador euromillones, bote euromillones.', 'En el sorteo Euromillones del martes 7 de febrero un participante acertó todos los números y ganó el bote de €54 millones', 2, 1331193305, 6, 'David Bonnici', 'UK Winner Bags Massive EuroMillions Rollover', '/Images/news/euromillions_4.jpg', '<p>El bote Euromillones de 54 000 000€ estuvo ganado por un boleto sellado en el Reino Unido.</p>', 'Ganador del bote Euromillones', 'Ganador del bote Euromillones del 7 de febrero 2012', 1328726225, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (88, 73, 'en', 'euromillions_winners_powerball_millions', 'Euromillions Winners & Powerball Millions', '<p>The latest big Euromillions winners are another couple from Nottingham. Their names will be known later as they plan to hold a press conference to go public. Be sure to bookmark this page for updates on the new winners of €53,000,000. This win puts the new couple 7th in the UK Euromillions rich list. Just ahead of the last big jackpot winners <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/218/winners-of-fridays-euromillions-jackpot-go-public">Gareth & Catherine Bull</a> who had won €50 million 2 weeks previously.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While we wait for their press conference it will be interesting for many of you to know that Tuesday''s draw created lots of other big cash winners.In fact 9 lucky ticket holders will be in with a chance to claim €135,771.91, and another 11 in third place stand to become €37,028.70 richer. The total number of cash prize winners for the <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euromillions numbers</a> 03, 15, 17, 28, 33 and Lucky Stars 02 and 04 is a staggering 13,444,092.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In other EuroMillions news a further <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-uk-millionaire-raffle">millionaire raffle</a> ticket from the draw on November 25th remains unclaimed. The ticket purchased in Wealdon has the winning raffle code WT537436 and must be claimed before 11pm on May 23rd. Worth exactly £1 million, if the prize is not claimed by that date it will go directly to charity along with any interest it has generated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A Valentines ad is set to run in Friday''s Eastbourne Herald in an effort to find the mysterious lucky winner.”It is one of the more unusual steps we have taken to unite the owner of an unclaimed ticket with their win” said a lottery spokesperson “but we hope it will have the desired effect”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“Many people meet their life partners this way, so why not their life fortune!”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The ad is looking for a “Long lost love” to come forward “for a life changing experience”. The ad will be hoping for “a match made in heaven”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the other side of the world a Powerball jackpot with a cash value of roughly €145 million is up for grabs. Ordinarily this prize would only be available to residents of America but nowadays people from all over the world are purchasing Powerball tickets. If you want to have a chance at winning the big Powerball Jackpot this Saturday then buy your tickets <a href="http://ads.playukinternet.com/tracking.php/text/3451/12885/3929003/8502" link rel="nofollow" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>', 'Euromillions Winners & Powerball Millions', 'Euromillions Winners, Unclaimed Euromillions Prizes, Powerball', 'Tuesday''s draw saw the huge rollover come to an end, now the winners are set to go public. But is the Powerball''s €145 million more pressing news?', 2, 1328797273, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euromillions Winners & Powerball Millions', '/images/news/euromillions_3.jpg', '<p>The UK gets ready to meet it''s latest huge Euromillions winners, while £1 million still goes unclaimed and the Americans offer an enormous prize</p>', 'Winning Euromillions Ticket', NULL, 1328792638, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (89, 74, 'en', 'cassey_and_matt_euromillions_winners', 'Cassey and Matt Euromillions Winners', '<p>The winners of €53,000,000 are 22 year old Cassey Carrington and Matt Topham of Mansfield Nottinghamshire. They have gone public and talk about their story today at a press conference. The pair join other major winners in their area Gareth and Catherine Bull who won €50,000,000 just three weeks previously. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The amazing news is that the couple had purchased their ticket online. This gave them the security and peace of mind that their ticket couldn''t be lost. In fact Cassey had only set up the online account to buy the tickets four days before the win. Admittedly Cassey doesn''t play the lottery game much, “I have only played the lottery about half a dozen times, when I am feeling lucky, and had already won £10 twice”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The night before they contacted Camelot nerves were running high, Cassey said “By this point we had seen the prizes, we were sure we had the right numbers and we were constantly thinking we can do this or buy that”, “We didn''t get much sleep at all.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Matt Topham who is currently a painter and decorator with his family''s company said that helping friends and family would be a top priority for the couple: “We can help friends get a house, it is so difficult thee days to get a deposit and mortgage so it''s great we can help them”. “Also dad can finally hang up his paintbrushes and relax”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not only do the young couple plan to pay off the mortgages of both of their parents, but have a far more generous budget for their impending wedding in September. “I had made the invitations and I was starting work on the centre pieces, all to save money” said Cassey, “We can now get a big firework display and some entertainment in the evening. It will be our dream day” she continued.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally they plan to build their very own dream home and do lots of travelling, and Cassey admits that she “really wanted an Aston Martin”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“I have often painted these huge houses and wondered what it would be like to live in one. Now I can find out” said Mr Topham.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With more and more big winners in the UK we can''t help but feel we''re overdue a winner from somewhere else in the world. Friday''s €15,000,000 could be yours, if you''ve got your ticket ready</p>', 'Cassey and Matt Euromillions Winners', 'Euromillions Winners, ', 'The latest enormous prize winners from the UK go public and talk more about their win', 2, 1328805144, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Cassey and Matt Euromillions Winners', '', '<p>Read more about the latest huge Euromillions winners</p>', 'Euromillions Winners Cassey And Matt', NULL, 1328800795, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (90, 75, 'de', 'euromillionen_45_millionen_pfund_gewinner_hat_nur_ein_paar_mal_gespielt', 'EuroMillionen: 45 Millionen Pfund Gewinner hat nur ein paar Mal gespielt!', '<p>Eine junge Frau aus Nottingshamshire, welche den 45 Millionen Pfund EuroMillionen Jackpot gewonnen hatte, sagte sie habe davor nur ein halbes dutzend Mal Lotto gespielt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cassey Carrington und Matt Topham, beide 22 Jahre alt und aus Stapleford, spielten EuroMillionen online und gewannen bei der Jackpot Ziehung am Dienstag 45.160.170,00 Pfund.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Frau Carrington sagt, Sie spürte das Glück, nachdem Sie in der Arbeit einen großen Bonus erhalten hatte, und registrierte ein Online Konto. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Es ist der zweite große EuroMillionen Gewinn in Großbritannien innerhalb von nur drei Wochen. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Gareth und Catherine Bull, aus Mansfield, gewannen bei der Ziehung am 20. Jänner £ 40 Millionen Pfund. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Freunde und Familie</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Frau Carrington, die als Filialleiterin einen Supermarkt beaufsichtigte, sagt, dass Sie sich online für die EuroMillionen Lotterie registriert hatte nachdem Sie 10.000 Pfund für gute Verkaufszahlen erhalten hatte. Sie nahm an der Freitagsziehung der EuroMillionen und der Samstagsziehung der Lotterie teil, jedoch ohne Erfolg. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>„Ich hatte das Gefühl, dass Ich gewinnen würde“: sagt Sie.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>„Ich hatte nur zirka ein halbes Dutzend Mal Lotto gespielt, als ich das Glück spürte, aber hatte bereits zweimal 10 Pfund gewonnen.“</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Allerdings glaubte das Paar Ihr Glück sei vorbei, als am Dienstag Ihr Computer und die Waschmaschinen am selben Tag aufhörten zu funktionieren. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Herr Topham sagt, das Paar dachte gerade besorgt darüber nach wie sie die Sachen ersetzen könnten, wobei auch die Zahlung für die bevorstehende Hochzeit noch zu ausständig war, als Frau Carrington entschied ihr Ticket zu überprüfen. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Frau Carrington sagt, sie zögerten anfangs noch davor zu feiern, da sie ihren Sieg erst am nächsten Tag um 8 Uhr bestätigen lassen konnten als die Lotterien wieder öffneten.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>„Ab dem Zeitpunkt, als wir den Gewinnbetrag gesehen hatten, waren wir uns sicher, dass wir die richtigen Zahlen hatten und wir waren ständig damit beschäftigt darüber nachzudenken was wir mit dem Gewinn machen und kaufen könnten.“</p>\r\n\r\n<p>„Wir haben überhaupt nicht viel Schlaf bekommen“</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Herr Topham, ein Maler und Dekorateur mit einem Familienunternehmen, sagt das Paar freue sich darauf mit dem Gewinn Freunden und Familie zu helfen!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>„ Wir können Freunden dabei helfen ein Haus zu bekommen, heutzutage ist es so schwer eine Anzahlung und Hypothek zu erhalten, es ist einfach großartig ihnen zu helfen“; sagte er.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>„Auch Vater kann endlich seinen Pinsel an den Nagel hängen und entspannen“</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Traumhaus</strong>\r\n\r\n<p>Zusätzlich zur Abzahlung der Hypothek ihrer Eltern, sagt Frau Carrington und Herr Topham, werden sie ihr Budget für ihre Hochzeit im September vergrößern!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>„Ich hatte all die Einladungen selbst gemacht und begann am Mittelstück zu arbeiten, alles nur um Geld zu sparen“, sagte Miss Carrington.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>„Jetzt können wir ein großes Feuerwerk und Unterhaltung für den Abend einplanen. Es wird unsere Traumhochzeit.“</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Herr Topham sagt, die beiden möchte jetzt ihr Traumhaus bauen und Reisen, Frau Carrington sagt, sie „wollte unbedingt einen Aston Martin“</p>\r\n\r\n<p>„Ich habe oft diese riesigen Häuser angestrichen und mich gefragt, wie es wohl wäre, in einem zu leben, jetzt kann ich es herausfinden!“, sagte Herr Topham.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Der Gewinn ist der siebtgrößte in Großbritannien, sagte Camelot.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ein Sprecher sagte: „Es ist eine großartige Nachricht, einen weiteren Gewinner aus Großbritannien zu haben, nachdem Gareth und Catherine Bull aus Mansfield zuvor £ 40 Millionen Pfund gewonnen hatten. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Herr und Frau Bull gewannen mit einem Lucky Dip Ticket, bei dem die Zahlen zufällig per Computer ausgewählt werden.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Der größte EuroMillionen Jackpot war in der Höhe von £ 161 Millionen Pfund und wurde von Colin und Chris Weir aus Largs, Schottland letzten Juli gewonnen</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Neun Länder – das Vereinigte Königreich, Die Republik Irland, Spanien, Portugal, Frankreich, Belgien, Luxemburg, die Schweiz und Österreich – nehmen an den EuroMillionen teil.</p>', 'EuroMillionen: 45 Millionen Pfund Gewinner hat nur ein paar Mal gespielt!', 'Euromillionen Gewinner, Matt, Cassey, Nottinghamshire, 45 millionen', 'Cassey Carrington und Matt Topham beschreiben, wie sie herausfanden, dass sie den Jackpot geknackt hatten. ', 1, 1328876111, 9, 'Jenny Zimmerman', 'EuroMillionen: 45 Millionen Pfund Gewinner hat nur ein paar Mal gespielt!', '/Images/news/cassey_matt.jpg', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1328876111, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (91, 76, 'es', 'euromillones_sorteo_del_viernes_10_de_febrero_de_2012', 'Euromillones - Sorteo del viernes 10 de febrero de 2012', '<p>En el último sorteo Euromillones del viernes 10 de febrero de 2012 no hubo acertante de primera categoría. Por lo tanto, el bote se renovará en el próximo sorteo Euromillones que tendrá lugar el martes 24 de febrero de 2012. Los sorteos Euromillones se llevan a cabo cada martes y viernes en Paris, a las 21h30.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>La combinación ganadora del viernes 10 de febrero 2012 es: <strong>03 - 08 - 14 - 31 - 41 / 07 - 11</strong> y el bote Euromillones de este sorteo representaba el bote inicial de 15 millones de euros. En el próximo sorteo, el bote aumentará y se estima que alcanzará 24 millones de euros. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Si desean participar en el próximo sorteo Euromillones para tener la oportunidad de ganar este bote impresionante de 24 millones de euros ya se pueden <a href="http://play.euromillions.com/es/" title="Jugar a la lotería Euromillones en Euromillions.com">comprar entradas</a> a la lotería Euromillones.</p>', 'Sorteo Euromillones del 10/02/2012 ', 'euromillones, euromillones resultados, resultado euromillones.', 'En el sorteo Euromillones del viernes 10 de febrero de 2012 se podía ganar €15 000 000. Aprende más acerca de este sorteo.', 2, 1328907461, 6, 'David Bonnici', 'Sorteo Euromillones del 20/02/2012', NULL, '<p>En el sorteo Euromillones del viernes 10 de febrero de 2012 se podía ganar €15 000 000.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1328907229, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (92, 77, 'en', 'valentine_lotto_sweethearts_buy_cut_price_tent', 'Valentine Lotto Sweethearts Buy Cut Price Tent', '<p>Big fans of music Festivals Matt Topham and fiancée Cassey Carrington, both 22, have gone tent shopping.\r\nThey managed to find one for under 40 pounds, so they’re all ready for the up and coming V Festival after having theirs trashed at last year’s bash.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mate Phil Taylor, 24 — who’s been to many a festival — said EuroMillions winner Matt, of Stapleford, Notts, had told him about their bargain new green tent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He said: "No way they''ll be swanning off to any VIP areas. They''ll get down and dirty in the field like the rest of us. Their old tent got ripped to ribbons — and Matt said they''d just gone out and bought one for a penny under £40. \r\n"They''re just a down-to-earth couple who love each other."</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In a recent interview they also expressed their interest in a new washing machine:</p>\r\n\r\n<iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/-JMA8fg2luE" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'Valentine Lotto Sweethearts Buy Cut Price Tent', 'Euromillions, Winners, Matt, Cassey, England', 'EuroMillions jackpot Brits go bargain hunting for new £39.99 tent!', 2, 1329250804, 3, 'Alison Davis', 'Valentine Lotto Sweethearts Buy Cut Price Tent', '', '<p>EuroMillions jackpot Brits go bargain hunting for new £39.99 tent!</p>', NULL, NULL, 1329217775, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (93, 78, 'en', 'luckiest_lottery_destinations_in_the_uk', 'Luckiest Lottery Destinations in the UK', '<p align="justify">Revealed this week are the top 10 luckiest places to live in the UK....in terms of lotto wins anyway!\r\nA new study which included both <a href="http://www.euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> and National Lottery winners of over £50,000 (€60,250.28) has been carried out. The figures are startling but might give UK lotto players some food for thought when it comes to their next move.</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">The UK was broken down into its postcode divisions, and we have here the odds of winning a prize of at least £50,000 in any UK Lottery game in these areas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify"><strong>Odds Of Winning £50,000 Or More</strong></p>\r\n<p align="left"><ul>\r\n<li>1,238 to 1 – Romford</li>\r\n<li>1,378 to 1 – Enfield</li> \r\n<li>1,391 to 1 – Dartford</li>\r\n<li>1,392 to 1 – Newcastle-Upon-Tyne</li> \r\n<li>1,421 to 1 – Sunderland</li>\r\n<li>1,425 to 1 – Liverpool</li>\r\n<li>1,428 to 1 – Warrington</li>\r\n<li>1,443 to 1 – Bromley</li>\r\n<li>1,452 to 1 – Newport</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<p align="justify">Regardless of the two recent big wins in Nottinghamshire, and the biggest Euromillions win recorded being from Scotland, Romford is seen as the luckiest place to buy a ticket. Since the very beginning of the UK National Lottery in 1994 more than 300 people have won a prize of at least £50,000, this is the direct equivalent of 1 in every 1,238 adults. While these figures seem to blow away the <a href="http://www.euromillions.com/euromillions-odds">Euromillions odds</a>, the actual fact is that every ticket purchased anywhere in the world has of course the same chance of winning as any other.</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">Naturally these statistics are just a sign of the statistical deviations that are bound to happen in any system where so many transactions are made. A new thirst for the lottery may tempt people in these areas to up their ante, and continue enjoying the game. For people in other parts of the UK however, lets just say: it might not be time to move home just yet!</p>', 'Luckiest Lottery Destinations in the UK', 'euromillions, odds, lottery, luck, euro millions', 'With two enormous winners both from Nottinghamshire, you''d be forgiven for thinking that lotto wins are more than just the luck of the draw!', 2, 1375691633, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Top 10 places to live in UK for lottery luck', '', '<p align="justify"><h2>Top lottery destinations in the UK</h2></p>', 'Best Euromillions Odds', 'A map of the best places to enter the lottery in the UK', 1329389551, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (94, 79, 'en', 'euromillions_com_introducing_skrill_as_a_new_payment_option', 'Euromillions.com Introducing Skrill as a New Payment Option!', '<h3>What Is Skrill/Moneybookers</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To meet the demand of our players our site now accepts payments from Skrill, previously Moneybookers. To clear up any confusion: Skrill and Moneybookers are the same agent just with two different brandings. Skrill is one of the leading ways to make a transaction online. Their service is also known as an ''e-wallet''. Money can be transferred to accounts with them and stored safely, then used to make transactions with other sites online using money in their ''e-wallet''.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It offers a convenient service for many people who may still be having problems paying for their <a href="http://play.euromillions.com/en/">Euromillions tickets</a> by credit card, or are interested in in paying by direct bank transfer. How can you use Skrill to buy Euromillions tickets today? Our step by step guide will show you the ropes.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Step 1</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Looking to play quickly and easily with a Skrill account? Or by direct bank transfer? Then a Skrill account will be necessary first. If you haven''t already created an account then visit <a href="https://www.moneybookers.com/app/?rid=28771838" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">http://www.skrill.com</a> and create one that''s relevant for you. To sign up for Skrill you will have to supply your email address and of course your home or billing address as standard.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Step 2</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Select your Euromillions entries as usual from play.euromillions.com and click continue. From there select ''Skrill'' as your payment option before hitting confirm and contine. Now you''ll be faced with a Skrill log-in screen, or the option to pay with a wide range of credit cards. Payments can be made by card in this way whether you have a Skrill account or not.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Step 3</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>From here you can pay using: Visa, Mastercard, Diners, American Express, JCB, Delta/Visa Debit and Visa Electron. Using the secure payment page you will see the total amount payable at the top of the page. From here simply enter the desired credit card and billing information including address and email. </p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Step 4</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Alternatively if you already have a Skrill account you can instead log in from this screen and use funds already in your Skrill account to make payment for your Euromillions tickets. Wondering how you can pay by bank transfer using Skrill?</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Step 5</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Depositing money to your Skrill account is simple. Just visit <a href="https://www.moneybookers.com/app/?rid=28771838" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">http://www.skrill.com</a> and select ''upload funds''. Now you can select to deposit by credit card or bank transfer. Select bank transfer and you will be provided with all the necessary details to send money directly to the company. Skrill often have a local bank for your nation. Simply take the necessary details (account number, IBAN etc) to your bank and choose an amount to transfer. Please note the importance of including the reference number, without it Skrill may have problems allocating money transferred in this way to your account.</p>', 'Euromillions.com Introducing Skrill/Moneybookers as a New Payment Option!', 'Skrill, Moneybookers, Payment Option', 'Euromillions.com now offer their customers a safer and easier way of purchasing Euromillions tickets.', 2, 1329477234, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Skrill Payment Option', '', '<p>Euromillions.com now offer their customers a safer and easier way of purchasing Euromillions tickets.</p>', 'Skrill Moneybookers', NULL, 1329476824, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (95, 80, 'en', 'euromillions_winners_friday_17th_february', 'Euromillions Winners Friday 17th February', '<p>This Tuesday''s Euromillions jackpot is a huge €41,000,000. Giving players once again the chance to win more than double the standard prize. Is your ticket ready to test your luck? If not there''s still a day left to enter to win this fantastic cash prize. Friday''s draw of course saw no jackpot winner for the prize of €34, 279, 343, but there was plenty of other large amounts of cash won.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A total of 9 people matched 5 numbers and 1 Lucky Star and are now eligible to claim €223,466. A further 15 are entitled to €39,727 for matching just 5 main numbers. With almost 3 million people claiming Euromillions cash from Friday''s draw it can''t be said that it wasn''t a big success.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At least we hope that many prizes are claimed; there''s already a number of substantial unclaimed prizes in the UK at the moment, be sure to check the latest <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euromillions Result</a>. In Port Talbot, Wales, €156,017 remains unclaimed a full two weeks after the draw. Elsewhere in Wales there''s still a <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-uk-millionaire-raffle">Millionaire Raffle</a> ticket from the 23rd of December unclaimed, the winner from Cardiff has the code FXV864819 on their ticket.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Scotland the winner of a prize of €303,040 actually waited more than a fortnight before claiming their prize! Their ticket was purchased on January 31st and they managed to match 5 main numbers and 1 Lucky Star. This gives hope for the unclaimed prizes out there as maybe people just aren''t in such a rush to get rich!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With so many regular winners and your first ticket bought with us risk free, now is as good a time as any to enter the <a href="http://www.euromillions.com">Euromillions online</a>!</p>', 'Euromillions Winners Friday 17th February', 'Euromillions Winners, Euromillions Results', 'Friday''s jackpot goes without a winner so we take a closer look at some of the other prizes won', 2, 1329733468, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euromillions Winners Friday 17th February', '/images/news/euromillions_3.jpg', '<p>Friday''s lack of jackpot winner is nothing to worry about as 2,958,991 people can still claim Euromillions cash</p>', 'Euromillions Ticket', 'The Ticket Of A Euromillions Winner', 1329729275, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (96, 81, 'en', 'tuesdays_jackpot', 'Tuesday''s Jackpot', '<p>2012 has seen three Euromillions jackpots being claimed so far and for some high amounts. The minimuim jackpot of €15,000,000 has yet to be won once. In it''s stead there were two winners who split between them a prize of €73,113,564 on Friday 6th January, one in France and one in Spain. Both of those winners chose to remain anonymous. The other two big prizes won were by Gareth and Catherine Bull of the UK who two weeks later on the 20th January laid claim to €48 million.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lastly -our most recent winners- Gareth and Catherine Bull the young couple from Nottinghamshire (as were the Bulls) have claimed a prize of €54 million. These are some very high Euromillions amounts by any standard, but we all know the jackpot can roll over as high as €190,000,000. Tonight''s jackpot is a more than respectable €41,000,000 and we''re excited to see if it will rollover a fourth time or if once again the jackpot will be won at this high amount.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There''s still a few hours left to be in with a chance of winning the fourth Euromillions jackpot of 2012 and with such a great prize on offer why wouldn''t you? Remember if this is your first time buying a ticket and it doesn''t win we will refund the cost straight back to you to play again.</p>', 'Tuesdays Jackpot', 'Euromillions Jackpot', 'Tonight''s jackpot has reached €41 million, and with only a few hours left to buy a ticket we look at 2012''s other winners', 2, 1329824108, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Tuesday''s Jackpot 21st February', '/images/news/euromillions_1.jpg', '<p>Only 3 jackpot prizes have been won in 2012, will tonight be a fourth rollover or will the 4th prize of the year be claimed?</p>', 'Tuesday''s Jackpot', NULL, 1329824108, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (97, 82, 'en', 'euromillions_winners_tuesday_21st_february', 'Euromillions Winners Tuesday 21st February', '<p>Continuing the trend we''ve seen since the start of 2012 the Euromillions jackpot has rolled over for the fifth time again. This Friday''s jackpot is an estimated €55 million, an amount that will see ticket prices climb. When last the jackpot reached such high amounts, a young couple from the UK -Cassey Carrington & Matt Topham- were the ones to lay claim to this fortune. Will there be yet another UK winner of this marvellous prize? Is it time for one of the other nations to win a big jackpot? Or will it keep rolling over into the hundreds of millions?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regardless the <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euromillions Result</a> for 21/02/2012 of 11, 14, 24, 25, 29 and Lucky Stars 7 and 11 created some significant prize winners. While only 2 people successfully matched 5 numbers and 1 Star to be entitled to €567,892 each, there was a full 14 winners of €27,042. The 15 Euromillions winners who matched just 5 main numbers won''t be turning their nose up at that life changing prize. In total there were over 1.9 million winners. 1.2 million of whom only matched 2 main numbers to win the minimuim prize of €4.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other significant prize winners include 39 winners of €4,854 and an enormous 921 winners of €180. All of these people will certainly be glad they made an entry in the <a href="http://www.euromillions.com">Euromillions lottery</a>. Number 14 which is the fourth most occurring number in the game has made it''s 56th appearance. The rarest Lucky Star number 11 was drawn yesterday for the 18th time since the game''s change in May 2011. The question on everyone''s mind though is what will become of the €55 million prize available on Friday? If you''d like to get your hands on it then you''ll have to purchase a ticket, but what''s €2.35 investment to win €55 million? Not much at all.</p>', 'Euromillions Winners Tuesday 21st February', 'Euromillions Winners, Euromillions Rollover', 'The fifth consecutive rollover will see Friday''s prize reach dizzying amounts yet again', 2, 1329904538, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euromillions Winners Tuesday 21st February', '/images/news/euromillions_4.jpg', '<p>While yesterday''s draw saw plenty of cash prizes being won, the jackpot has rolled over yet again</p>', 'Euromillions Winners', NULL, 1329904320, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (98, 83, 'en', 'prizes_unclaimed_and_claimed', 'Prizes Unclaimed And Claimed', '<p>The bonus game available only to Irish Euromillions players has created yet another winner of €500,000. Euromillions Plus is available on all Euromillions tickets purchased in Ireland at the cost of an extra €1 per line entered. The game enters your 5 main numbers into a second draw to win €500,000. The ticket that was sold on Friday the player had chosen <a href="http://www.euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euromillions numbers</a> 1, 2, 31, 37 and 48. We doubt the winner will be too unhappy that these numbers didn''t match a single one of the drawn Euromillions numbers for that date.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A full five days later however and the ticket holder has yet to come forward to claim their cash. Moriarty''s Centra was the shop who sold the winning ticket.  The lucky store in Faranfore has previously sold a ticket that brought it''s owner home a huge €350,000. Since the store is only an hour from the airport, speculation is that the winner may be a tourist, but rumour has it that they could be more local. The owner of the store Mike Moriarty said “There''s been plenty of rumours that the winner is local but nobody really knows to be honest”. Mike went on to explain how just an hour after the draw, the Euromillions organisers phoned him to let him know he had sold a huge prize winning ticket.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He went to the press straight away saying “Obviously it''s great publicity for us but we also want to advertise it because we don''t want someone to have washed it away so we want everyone who bought a ticket to check it out” he continued “It''s hard to believe that this draw is all over Europe, in Germany or France or wherever, and it ends up being sold in Faranfore”. While tickets aren''t ordinarily sold in Germany, German players may enter the Euromillions online with Euromillions.com.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In other exciting news the <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/238/euromillions-winners-friday-17th-february">Euromillions winner</a> of €156,017 in Port Neath Wales has finally come forward after over a month since the draw. The winner may have come forward to claim their money but they have yet to decide on if they want to go public or not. A National Lottery spokeswoman said “We''re delighted that the winner of this amazing prize has now come forward” and continued “It would have been awful if they had missed out”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Remember when you purchase your ticket online you''ve no chance of losing it or forgetting to check the numbers. Your ticket is held safely and all of our winners are contacted by email when their ticket matches the numbers for a cash prize.</p>', 'Prizes Unclaimed And Claimed', 'Euromillions Prizes, Unclaimed Euromillions', 'Another huge prize might go unclaimed, but there''s a happy story for a Welsh Euromillions player who has finally been united with their prize.', 2, 1329989298, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Prizes Unclaimed And Claimed 23rd February', '/images/news/euromillions_1.jpg', '<p>Another big prize puts a small town in Ireland on the map yet again, and a prize that looked like it would be lost has been claimed</p>', 'Euromillions Prizes', NULL, 1329989298, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (99, 84, 'en', 'the_new_european_lottery', 'The New European Lottery', '<p>Europe is an enormous place made up of many different countries. There''s a national lottery in each country, and of course 9 of the European nations have combined their efforts to create the Euromillions. What about the other countries though? Why hadn''t they ever gotten together to make another multi-national lottery? Well now they have. Starting on the 23rd of March there will be a brand new pan-European lottery consisting of 9 other ''rival'' EU nations. This new game will be called the Euro Jackpot, and it''s prizes, rules and odds of winning look set to give the Euromillions some serious competition. What this means for you lotto lovers is that there''s a brilliant new game to choose from that will offer better odds to win tens of millions of Euro''s from the comfort of your own home.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What Is The Euro Jackpot</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The <a href="http://www.playeurojackpot.com">EuroJackpot</a> is the brainchild of the 6 European nations, Germany, Netherlands, Finland, Estonia, Slovakia and Denmark. In November 2011 these nations met in Amsterdam to discuss the possibility of a huge new lottery game, and the result is the Euro Jackpot, which will hold it''s first draw on the 23rd of March 2012. With more favourable jackpot odds and comparable top prizes this game looks set to give the <a href="http://www.euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> a run for it''s money.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The draws will take place once every week on a Friday, held live in Helsinki, and there will be a minimuim jackpot guarantee each draw of €10,000,000. The odds of putting your hands on this incredible amount are good at 1 in 59,325,280. This is almost double the chance you have of winning the Euromillions jackpot, but not half the minimuim prize value! With such odds, we will be expecting far fewer rollovers especially as the game''s organisers expect approximately 50 million players each week. As such the rollover prize cap has been set to €90,000,000.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So how do they create such favourable winning odds? Well like the Euromillions, players will be required to select 7 numbers total. 5 main numbers from one pool and 2 bonus numbers from another. What drops the odds considerably is that while players still choose 5 from a pool of 1-50 they choose their 2 bonus numbers from a reduced pool of only 1-8. This small difference from the Euromillions makes a big change for the players!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So what''s the catch? There quite simply isn''t one. Can I play online from anywhere in the world? Yes! Ticket sales will begin on the 23th of March, and you''ll be able to buy them at Play Euro Jackpot. Bookmark the page and mark the 10th March in your diary, as this lottery promises to well worth your entry.</p>', 'The New European Lottery', 'Euro Jackpot, EuroJackpot', 'A new European lottery is coming that will rival the Euromillions, haven''t you heard about the Euro Jackpot yet?', 2, 1331657446, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'The New Eurojackpot Lottery', '', '<p>The next big thing in European lotteries is on it''s way. Read everything there is to know about it here</p>', 'Eurojackpot', 'The Eurojackpot Lottery', 1330074763, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (100, 85, 'en', 'third_consecutive_uk_euromillions_jackpot_winner', 'Third Consecutive UK Euromillions Jackpot Winner', '<p>For the third consecutive draw the winner of the Euromillions jackpot is from the UK. Once again  the prize amount is enormous, with the ticket holder coming forward yesterday to claim €54,897,476. All that remains to be seen now is if the winner is going to make themselves known to the public. The UK is certainly in an enviable position but surely the next big jackpot can''t go there again? National Lottery organisers in the UK were are stunned but delighted, one spokesperson said “It''s unbelievable that we have had a third huge EuroMillions win here. The UK is clearly enjoying a run of amazing luck. We have plenty of champagne on ice and look forward to welcoming the lucky ticket-holder into the National Lottery Millionaires'' club”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The EuroMillions numbers 3, 7, 12, 26, 34 and Lucky Stars 8 and 10 brought plenty of cash to lots of fortunate winners worldwide. In total there were 3,545,101 winners, a number of those for some significant amounts of money. 8 people matched 5 of their main numbers and 1 Lucky Star and will be entitled to €244,617. A further 16 people who matched just 5 main numbers should be claiming prizes of €40,769 each. Other big cash prizes include €5,623 which 58 winners will receive, and €182 which 1567 people will each be claiming. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>Tomorrows jackpot is of course reset to €15,000,000. The odds are that if the prize is won it''s set to go to any other country apart from the UK. If you''re feeling lucky -wherever you are in the world- then tickets are available here at Euromillions.com</p>', 'Third Consecutive UK Euromillions Jackpot Winner', 'Euromillions Winner, Euromillions jackpot', 'For the third time in a row a huge rollover jackpot has been won by a UK ticket holder', 2, 1330338985, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Third Consecutive UK Euromillions Jackpot Winner', '/images/news/luckmap.jpg', '<p>The hot streak of Euromillions luck in the UK continues</p>', 'UK Euromillions Winners', NULL, 1330338797, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (101, 86, 'de', 'eurojackpot_lotterie', 'EuroJackpot Lotterie', '<p>Europa ist ein riesengroßer Ort der sich aus vielen verschiedenen Ländern zusammensetzt. In jedem Land gibt es eine nationale Lotterie, und sechs der europäischen Nationen haben ihre Bemühungen vereint um Euromillions zu schaffen. Aber was ist mit den anderen Ländern? Warum haben sich diese nie zusammengeschlossen um eine weitere multinationale Lotterie zu kreieren? Nun haben sie! Ab dem 23. März wird es eine neue pan-europäische Lotterie, bestehend aus sechs anderen „rivalisierenden EU-Staaten geben. Diese neue Lotterie wird <a href="http://playeurojackpot.com/de/" title="EuroJackpot Lotterie">EuroJackpot</a> genannt werden, und die Gewinnbeträge, Regeln und Gewinnwahrscheinlichkeiten könnten diese Lotterie zu einem ernsthaften Konkurrenten für Euromillions werden lassen. Das bedeutet für euch Lotto-Liebhaber, dass es ein neues geniales Lottospiel gibt das bessere Chancen bietet um Millionen von Euros komfortabel vom eigenen zu Hause zu gewinnen.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Was ist der EuroJackpot?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Der Euro-Jackpot ist eine Idee von den sechs europäischen Ländern, Deutschland, Niederlande, Schweden, Norwegen, Finnland, Estland und Dänemark. Im November 2011 trafen sich diese Nationen in Amsterdam um die Möglichkeit eines neuen riesigen Lottospiels zu diskutieren. Das Ergebnis ist der Euro-Jackpot.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Die erste Ziehung wird am 23.März 2012 stattfinden. Mit besseren Jackpot Wahrscheinlichkeiten und vergleichbaren Hauptpreisen dürfte diese Lotterie der Euromillions Lotterie kräftig Konkurrenz machen. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Wie schaffen Sie es so gute Gewinnchancen anzubieten? Nun, wie bei Euromillions, müssen die Spieler insgesamt sieben Zahlen auswählen. Fünf Hauptzahlen aus einem Zahlenpool und zwei weitere Zusatzzahlen aus einem anderen Zahlenpool. Was die Wahrscheinlichkeit erheblich verbessert ist, dass während die Spieler immer noch die fünf Hauptzahlen aus einem Zahlenpool 1-50 wählen, werden die zwei Zusatzzahlen aus einem reduzierten Pool von nur 1-8 ausgewählt. Dieser kleine Unterschied von Euro-Jackpot zu Euromillions (2 aus 11) führt zu einer großen Veränderung für die Spieler!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also, wo ist der Haken? Ganz einfach, es gibt keinen! Kann Ich online von überall auf der Welt spielen? Ja! Der Ticketverkauf wird am 10.März beginnen und du wirst in der Lage sein sie auf PlayEuroJackpot zu kaufen. Speichern Sie diese Seite unter Ihren Favoriten und markieren Sie sich den 10. März in Ihrem Terminkalender, es wird sich lohnen.</p>', 'EuroJackpot Lotterie', 'EuroJackpot, Euro Jackpot, Jackpot, Euro', 'Der neueste Trend der Europäischen Lotterien ist auf dem Weg. Lesen Sie alles, was Sie darüber wissen müssen hier.', 1, 1331657402, 9, 'Jenny Zimmerman', 'EuroJackpot Lotterie', '/images/news/eurojackpot.png', '<p>Der neueste Trend der Europäischen Lotterien ist auf dem Weg. Lesen Sie alles, was Sie darüber wissen müssen hier.</p>', 'Eurojackpot', NULL, 1330414201, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (102, 87, 'de', 'die_gluecksstraehne_der_spieler_aus_grossbritannien_setzt_sich_fort', 'Die Glückssträhne der Spieler aus Großbritannien setzt sich fort', '<p>Wieder einmal war der Jackpot Betrag enorm, der Ticketinhaber der sich gestern gemeldet hat erhält € 54.897.476 Euro. Es bleibt abzuwarten ob sich der Sieger der Öffentlichkeit preisgibt. Das Vereinigte Königreich ist sicherlich in einer beneidenswerten Lage, aber der nächste große Jackpot kann doch nicht mehr dort hingehen? Nationale Lotterie Organisatoren in Großbritannien waren fassungslos, aber auch sehr erfreut, sagte in Sprecher: „Es ist unglaublich, dass wir einen dritten großen EuroMillions Gewinn hier haben. Das Vereinigte Königreich genießt offensichtlich eine erstaunliche Glücksserie. Wir haben genug Champagner eisgekühlt und freuen uns darauf den Ticket Inhaber im National Lotterie Millionär Klub zu begrüßen. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Die Zahlen 3, 7, 12, 26, 34 und die Lucky Stars 8 und 10 bedeuten sehr viel Geld für vielen glückliche Gewinner weltweit. Insgesamt gab es 3.545.101 Millionen Gewinner, ein Teil davon gewann beträchtliche Geldmengen. Von acht Personen stimmen 5 ihrer Hauptzahlen und 1 Lucky Star mit den Gewinnzahlen überein und sie haben jeweils € 244.617 Euro gewonnen. Weitere 16 Personen, die nur die 5 Hauptzahlen richtig getippt haben werden jeweils einen Gewinn von € 40.769 Euro erhalten. Andere große Geldpreise erhalten 58 Gewinner mit € 5.623 Euro und 1567 Menschen erhalten jeweils € 182 Euro.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Der morgendliche Jackpot ist natürlich auf € 15 Millionen Euro zurückgesetzt. Die Chancen stehen gut, dass wenn der Jackpot geknackt wird, er an einen Spieler aus einem anderen Land außer Großbritannien geht. Wenn sie ein Glücksgefühl verspüren, wo auch immer Sie in der Welt sind, dann erhalten Sie die Tickets hier bei Euromillions.com.</p>', 'Die Glückssträhne der Spieler aus Großbritannien setzt sich fort', 'Großbritannien, Gewinner, Euromillionen, Euromillions', 'Bereits zum dritten Mal in Folge kommt der Sieger des Euromillions-Jackpot aus dem Vereinigten Königreich von England.', 1, 1330414507, 9, 'Jenny Zimmerman', 'Die Glückssträhne der Spieler aus Großbritannien setzt sich fort', '/images/news/luckmap.jpg', '<p>Bereits zum dritten Mal in Folge kommt der Sieger des Euromillions-Jackpot aus dem Vereinigten Königreich von England.</p>', 'großbritannien', NULL, 1330414507, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (103, 88, 'en', 'another_uk_euromillions_winner', 'Another UK Euromillions Winner', '<p>Of all the 3,094,990 winners in last Friday''s draw the ticket holder who will be putting their hands on the fantastic €26,670,951 jackpot prize will once again be from the UK. That''s right, for the fourth consecutive time the Euromillions jackpot has been won by a ticket purchased in the UK. This newest winner joins couples join Gareth and Catherine Bull as well as Cassey Carrington and Matt Topham who both one over €40 million in quadruple rollovers, and live just 20 miles from each other in Nottingham.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Friday''s Euromillions result</a> generating a UK jackpot winner will create a stir among players in the other European host nations. A spokesman for UK Lottery organisers Camelot said “It''s amazing to have another big winner here in the UK – we''ve been extremely lucky in recent years". The second prizes available were also much higher than normal, making 3 lucky players who matched 5 numbers and 1 Star eligible to claim €875,321 each. A further 7 players who only matched 5 numbers are claiming a larger than average third prize of €83,364. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Friday''s drawn numbers of 5, 6, 11, 30, 44 and Lucky Stars 2 and 6 also created almost 100 winners of €3,071 each, and 1546 winners of €165. Both amounts are a more than respectable return for their €2.35 ticket price. In other Euromillions news a teenger from Penicuik in Scotland, found two large prize winning Euromillions tickets in his messy room! The 19 year old''s mother, Susan, had naturally been telling her son for weeks to clean up his act before the boy finally cracked and started to tidy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the task was done the teenager named Ryan discovered he had come across 12 old Euromillions tickets. One was a winner of €4 however the other will see the young Scottish Euromillions enthusiast €64,489 richer! Speaking publicly he said “I was about to bin them [the tickets] but at the last minute I got this strange feeling I should get them checked. Next time my mum nags me to tidy my room, I won''t need telling twice.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Already the 19 year old has a plan with his money, and he speaks only of selfless uses for it “I love being part of First Response. It''s a great charity and I''m planning on donating some cash to them. They do great work so I want to keep volunteering with them.” He also wants to help his brother, Sean, put a deposit down on his very first car, as well as send his parents off on a sunny holiday.</p>', 'Another UK Euromillions Winner', 'Euromillions Winners, Euromillions Jackpot', 'Yet another UK player claims the Euromillions jackpot. While a 19 year old discovers a Euromillions fortune tidying his room', 2, 1330942325, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euromillions News 05/03/2012', '', '<p>Friday''s draw creates another UK Euromillions jackpot winner, and one teenager finds more than he bargained for when tidying his room</p>', 'UK Euromillions Winner', NULL, 1330941885, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (104, 89, 'de', 'schon_wieder_geht_der_euromillionen_jackpot_nach_grossbritannien', 'Schon wieder geht der Euromillionen Jackpot nach Großbritannien', '<p>Von all den 3.094.990 Gewinnern der Ziehung vom vergangenen Freitag kommt der glückliche Besitzer des Lottoscheins ,der den fantastischen Jackpot von € 26.670.951 Euro gewonnen hat ,wieder einmal aus dem Vereinigten Königreich. Das ist richtig, zum vierten Mal in Folge wurde der <a href="http://euromillions.com/de">EuroMillionen</a> Jackpot von einer Person gewonnen, die ihren Lottoschein in dem Vereinigten Königreich gekauft hatte. Der neueste Gewinner wird sich in einem Kreis mit Gareth und Catherine Bull, sowie Cassey Carrington und Matt Topham, die beide über €40 Millionen Euro in einem vierfach Jackpot gewonnen haben und noch dazu nur 20 Meilen von einander in Staple Ford Nottingham wohnen, wiederfinden. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dass der Jackpot-Gewinner der <a href="{{lottery_url::latest}}">EuroMillionen Ziehung</a> eine Person aus Groß-Britannien ist, wird für eine Überraschung in den anderen europäischen Gastländern sorgen. Ein Sprecher der UK Lotterie Organisatoren Camelot sagte: „ Es ist erstaunlich einen weiteren großen Gewinner aus Großbritannien zu haben – wir hatten in den letzten Jahren sehr viel Glück!“ Die weiteren Geldpreise waren auch viel höher als in den Jahren zuvor, so dass drei glückliche Spieler, die fünf Zahlen und einen Lucky Star richtig getippt hatten, jeweils einen Betrag von € 875.321 Euro erhielten. Weitere sieben Spieler, die nur 5 Zahlen richtig getippt hatten, erhielten einen mehr als durchschnittlichen Geldbetrag von € 83.364 Euro. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Die Zahlen der Freitagsziehung 5, 6, 11, 30, 44 und die Lucky Stars 2 und 6 bedeuteten für fast 100 Gewinner jeweils € 3.071 Euro und 1546 Gewinner jeweils € 165 Euro. Beide Beträge sind eine mehr als respektable Rendite gemessen an € 2,35 Euro für den Lottoschein. Weitere <a href="{{news_url::latest}}">EuroMillionen Nachrichten</a> ereigneten sich in Penicuik, Schottland, wo ein Teenager einen Lottoschein, im Gegenwert eines hohen Geldbetrages, in seinem unordentlichen Zimmer gefunden hatte. Die Mutter des 19-Jährigen, Susan, hatte ihren Sohn seit Wochen dazu aufgefordert sein Zimmer aufräumen, bevor er es schlussendlich machte.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nachdem er seine Aufgabe erledigt hatte, fiel dem Teenager namens Ryan auf, dass er zwölf alte <a href="http://play.euromillions.com/de/">EuroMillionen Lottoscheine</a> in seinen Händen hielt. Ein Lottoschein war nur über einen Gewinn von € 4 Euro, aber die anderen werden den schottischen EuroMillionen Enthusiasten € 64.489 Euro reicher machen. Er sagte öffentlich: „Ich war kurz davor die Lottoscheine wegzuwerfen, als ich im letzten Moment das seltsame Gefühl bekam ich sollte sie doch überprüfen. Das nächste Mal wenn meine Mutter nörgelt und sagt ich solle mein Zimmer aufräumen, wird Sie es mir nicht zweimal sagen müssen!“</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Der 19-Jährige hat bereits einen Plan für seinen Gewinn, er spricht nur von einer selbstlosen Verwendung des Geldes, er sagte: „Er liebt es Teil der wohltätigen Organisation First Response zu sein.“ Es ist eine großartige Wohlfahrtseinrichtung und ich plane daher einen Teil des Gewinns an sie zu spenden. Sie vollbringen großartige Arbeit und deshalb möchte ich ein ehrenamtlicher Mitarbeiter sein und meinen Teil leisten.“ Des Weiteren möchte er seinem Bruder Sean helfen, indem er die Anzahlung für sein aller erstes Auto bezahlt und seine Eltern auf einen sonnigen Urlaub schickt.</p>', 'Schon wieder geht der Euromillionen Jackpot nach Großbritannien', 'Gewinner, Euromillions, Großbritannien', 'Schon wieder geht der Euromillionen Jackpot nach Großbritannien', 1, 1331023211, 9, 'Jenny Zimmerman', 'Schon wieder geht der Euromillionen Jackpot nach Großbritannien', '/images/news/euromillions_uk.jpg', '<p>Ein weiterer Euromillions Gewinner aus Großbritannien</p>', 'Euromillions Großbritannien', NULL, 1331022601, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (105, 90, 'en', 'euromillions_winners_start_spending', 'EuroMillions Winners Start Spending', '<p>Friday''s Euromillions Results saw saw no winner of the €26,508,061 prize. This means that on Tuesday there will be an estimated €33 million available for you to win. Other prizes from Friday''s draw weren''t as numerous as in previous draws, but still enough to have made it a more than worthwhile endeavor for many ticket holders. In total there were 2,461,176 cash prize winners claiming prizes from €5 all the way up to €575,403.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The winner of €26,670,951 from Friday the 2nd of March has still yet to come forward. The ticket holder is the 4th in a row from the UK to win the Euro Millions jackpot, but it appears the 4th time isn''t a charm for the UK as the winner has still to claim their cash.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Meanwhile, Matt Topham and Cassey Carrington winners of €53 million have been making use of their huge windfall. They''ve both already purchased their dream cars; an €83,544 Jaguar XK for Matt and a €33,410 Range Rover Evoque for Cassey. The couple have chosen to purchase a very modest home of only €297,099. Their new home is far from a luxury mansion, and is actually a former council house. The property which has been on the market since 2009 has not been terribly sought after by neighbours in their area, one has said of the property “They''ll have to make sure they draw their curtains otherwise people will be able to see straight into their bedroom”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Despite their spending beginning in earnest, the couple have already been using their cash to help friends and family. They''ve given away €1.5 million to their best friend Eddie Smith who is studying web development. A friend of the couple has said “It''s a fantastic gesture that proves Matt and Cassey don''t intend to leave their friends behind despite their mountains of cash. They''ve both been friends of Eddie for years – they call him their ''bestest'' friend.”</p>', 'EuroMillions Winners Start Spending', 'Euromillions Jackpot, Euromillions Winner', 'Tonights jackpot is for a huge €33 million, but what of the last two jackpots won this year?', 2, 1331632803, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euromillions Winners Start Spending', '/images/news/euromillions_4.jpg', '<p>Tonights jackpot is for a huge €33 million, but what of the last two jackpots won this year?</p>', 'Euro Millions Winning Ticket', NULL, 1331632803, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (106, 91, 'en', 'euromillions_winners_tuesday_15th_march', 'EuroMillions Winners Tuesday 15th March', '<p>Tuesday''s Euromillions result of 1, 10, 25, 43, 47 and Lucky Stars 8 and 9 has created another rollover, meaning that Friday''s jackpot will be  a truly grand prize of €45,000,000. This prize will be available for all lotto enthusiasts from anywhere in the world to win, when you buy your tickets with Euromillions.com.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In a rare occurrence the UK winner of €26.5 million from the draw on the 2nd of March has chosen to remain anonymous. The lucky winner waited over two weeks to claim their prize, and unlike the previous recent big UK Euromillions winners, the player is keeping their identity a secret. The prize has now been issued and no further information will be revealed!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other notable Euromillions wins include the five people from Tuesday''s draw who are going to become €218,703  richer, and a further 5 who will win €72,901. The power of syndicate play has shown itself to 31 members of a syndicate made up of Berlino’s Steak House and Berwick Rotary Club members. The syndicate winners are all based in Berwick in the UK and the lucky 31 will be splitting €1,200,000.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“It was a lovely surprise” said the Rotary Club manager Allan Collett ““I thought Jim Gladstone (the syndicate leader) was pulling my leg when he phoned on Sunday night to tell me because I’d missed the last couple of rotary meetings”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other excited members of the syndicate include Bruce Dodds who found out about his big cash windfall on his 74th Birthday -”I got a phone message from Jim on Sunday morning to say we had won the lottery, but then after half an hour I phoned back to see if he was joking because it was my birthday”</p>', 'EuroMillions Winners Tuesday 15th March', 'Euro Millions Winners', 'Another big rollover prize will be up for grabs this Friday, thanks to a lack of winner on Tuesday. Plenty of other prizes have been won however...', 2, 1331831579, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euromillions Winners Tuesday 15th March', '/images/news/euromillions_1.jpg', '<p>Another big rollover prize will be up for grabs this Friday, thanks to a lack of winner on Tuesday. Plenty of other prizes have been won however...</p>', 'Euromillions Ticket', NULL, 1331831579, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (107, 92, 'en', 'eurojackpot_a_short_comparison_to_euromillions', 'Eurojackpot, a short comparison to Euromillions', '<p>On March 17th 2012 tickets will go on sale for the next big thing in lottery games; the <a href="http://www.playeurojackpot.com">EuroJackpot</a>. Created by an accord between several European nations this game looks set to give serious competition to the lottery juggernaut known as <a href="http://euromillions.com/">Euro Millions</a>. Already the game looks set to have a more competitive set of rules and winnings odds than the existing pan-European lottery. However with the popularity and awareness of the Euromillions already at a worldwide stage how much competition can the Euro Jackpot really provide.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Let''s make some direct comparisons between the two games shall we? Firstly we''ll look at the all important rules and odds. As you may know the Euromillions game is played by selecting 5 numbers from a field of 1-50 and 2 numbers from a field of 1-11, by contrast the Euro Jackpot doesn''t vary much: You pick 5 numbers from a field of 1-50 and 2 numbers from a reduced field of 1-8. To the untrained eye the differences between how the two games are played, however with a closer look at how the rules reflect upon the odds of winning the size of the difference becomes obvious.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the game of Euromillions the odds of matching all your numbers for a jackpot win are approximately 1 in 117 million, the same result in the EuroJackpot has odds of approximately 1 in 59 million. This enormous difference in the odds of winning might put the Euro Jackpot in the lead, if it wasn''t for the prize amounts available. Twice every week the Euromillions guarantees a minimuim €15 million jackpot, whereas the EuroJackpot will be guaranteeing only a €10 million minimuim jackpot, which for the time being will only take place once a week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To compound matters the maximuim rollover allowed in the Euromillions is €190,000,000 but in the Euro Jackpot it''s only €90,000,000. What we''re going to see is a lot more people winning jackpot prizes more often in the Euro Jackpot than in the Euromillions, but to the tune of less money each time. Even the game''s excellent odds of a jackpot win will help drastically in cutting back on persistent rollovers that plague the Euromillions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ultimately the success or not of the Euro Jackpot over the Euromillions will boil down to how many people are playing the game. In the 9 Euromillions host nations there is an approximate population of 205,714,830 and the average ticket sales each draw since the very beginning of the game has been 63,064,759. The greatest number of tickets sold in any single draw was 191,594,630. The Euro Jackpot will initially only involved 7 countries; Germany, Italy, Finland, Estonia, Denmark, The Netherlands and Slovenia. Iceland, Norway and Sweden are thought to be joining within months of the first draw. While the the total population of the host nations is only 171,739,884 the organisers expect approximately 50 million players each draw.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It''s arguable that the high sales figures of the Euromillions is directly related to the enormous jackpots that are offered during particularly high rollovers, with prizes of €100 million and upward available on certain occasions. Without such truly incredible rollover amounts available to EuroJackpot players it will be interesting to see how well the Euro Jackpot with it''s great winning odds.</p>', 'Eurojackpot, a short comparison to Euromillions', 'Eurojackpot, Euro Jackpot, Euromillions, Euro Millions', 'How will the new pan-European lottery measure up the Euromillions?', 2, 1331895247, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Eurojackpot, a short comparison to Euromillions', '/Images/news/eurojackpot.png', '<p>How will the new pan-European lottery measure up to the Euromillions?</p>', 'Eurojackpt lottery', NULL, 1331892038, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (108, 92, 'de', 'eurojackpot_eine_kurze_gegenueberstellung_zu_euromillionen', 'Eurojackpot - eine kurze Gegenüberstellung zu Euromillionen', '<p>Ab dem 17. März 2012 werden die Lottoscheine für das nächste große Ding im Lotteriespiel, bekannt als <a href="http://www.playeurojackpot.com/de/">Euro Jackpot</a> verkauft. Entstanden durch eine Übereinkunft zwischen mehreren europäischen Ländern, scheint diese Lotterie aller Voraussicht nach eine ernsthafte Konkurrenz für das Lotto Schwergewicht <a href="http://euromillions.com/de/">EuroMillionen</a> zu werden. Bereit jetzt scheint das Lotto-Spiel eine Reihe an wettbewerbsfähigeren Regeln und Gewinnwahrscheinlichkeiten als die bestehende paneuropäische Lotterie zu haben. Doch mit der weltweiten Popularität und Bekanntheit von EuroMillionen, wie viel Konkurrenz kann der EuroJackpot wirklich bieten.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lassen Sie uns zuerst einige direkte Vergleiche zwischen den beiden Lotterien anstellen? Als erstes wollen wir die wichtigen Regeln und Gewinnwahrscheinlichkeiten  näher betrachten. Wie Sie vielleicht wissen, spielen Sie EuroMillionen indem Sie fünf Zahlen aus einem Set 1-50 und zwei Zusatzzahlen aus einem Set 1-11 tippen, davon weicht EuroJackpot nicht wirklich ab. Sie entscheiden sich auch für fünf Zahlen aus einem Set 1-50 und zwei Zusatzzahlen aus einem Set 1-8. Für das ungeübte Auge scheint der Unterschied sehr gering zu sein, jedoch mit einem genaueren Blick darauf wie die Regeln die Gewinnwahrscheinlichkeiten beeinflussen, wird der Unterschied deutlicher.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bei der EuroMillionen liegt die Chance das alle Zahlen mit den Gewinnzahlen des Jackpots übereinstimmen bei ungefähr 1 zu 117 Millionen, bei EuroJackpot liegen die Chancen auf das gleiche Ergebnis bei circa 1 zu 59 Millionen. Dieser enorme Unterschied in den Gewinnchancen könnte EuroJackpot in Führung bringen, wenn es nicht um die möglichen Jackpot Beträge gehen würde. Zweimal pro Woche garantiert EuroMillionen einen minimalen Jackpot von € 15.000.000 Euro, während EuroJackpot nur einen € 10.000.000 Euro Jackpot garantiert, welcher vorerst auch nur einmal pro Woche stattfinden wird.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hinzu kommt die Tatsache das der maximal zugelassene Rollover Betrag bei EuroMillionen € 190.000.000 Euro beträgt, während er bei EuroJackpot nur € 90.00.000 Euro beträgt. Was wir sehen werden ist, dass sehr viel mehr Menschen bei EuroJackpot als bei EuroMillionen gewinnen werden, aber jedes Mal in Einklang mit geringen Gewinnbeträgen. Selbst die ausgezeichneten Gewinnwahrscheinlichkeiten eines Jackpots der Lotterie, werden helfen die ständigen Rollover, welche die EuroMillionen Lotterie plagen, zu begrenzen.<p>\r\n\r\n<p>Schlussendlich wird der Erflog von EuroJackpot über EuroMillionen davon abhängen wie viele Leute die Lotterie spielen. In den neun EuroMillionen Veranstaltungsländern gibt es ungefähr eine Bevölkerung von 205.714.830 Menschen und der durchschnittliche Lottoscheinverkauf pro Ziehung, und das seit Anfang an, beträgt circa 63.064.759 Stück. Die meisten Lottoscheine, die jemals für eine einzelne Ziehung verkauft wurden, waren 191.594.630 Stück. An EuroJackpot beteiligen sich zunächst nur 6 Länder: Deutschland, Italien, Finnland, Estland, Dänemark, die Niederlanden und Slowenien. Island und Norwegen werden innerhalb weniger Monate nach der ersten Ziehung beitreten. Während die Gesamtbevölkerung der Veranstaltungsländer nur bei 171.739.884 Menschen liegt, erwarten die Veranstalter rund 50 Millionen Spier pro Ziehung.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Man kann behauten, dass die hohen Verkaufszahlen der EuroMillionen Lotterie direkt mit den enormen Jackpots, die bei besonders hohen Rollover Jackpots zu Gewinnbeträgen von € 100 Millionen Euro und mehr an bestimmten Ereignis führen können, zusammen hängen. Mit solch wirklich unglaublichen Rollover Jackpot-Beträgen die den Spielern von EuroMillionen zuwinken, wird es interessant zu sehen wie gut sich EuroJackpot mit seinen hohen Gewinnwahrscheinlichkeiten schlagen wird.</p>', 'Eurojackpot - eine kurze Gegenüberstellung zu Euromillionen', 'Euro Jackpot, Euro Millionen, Eurojackpot, Euro Millionen', 'Eurojackpot - Wie schlägt sich diese neue paneuropäische Lotterie im Vergleich zu Euromillionen', 1, 1332070321, 9, 'Jenny Zimmerman', 'Eurojackpot, a short comparison to Euromillions', '/Images/news/eurojackpot.png', '<p>Wie schlägt sich diese neue paneuropäische Lotterie im Vergleich zu Euromillionen</p>', 'EuroJackpot', NULL, 1331898632, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (109, 93, 'en', 'euromillions_jackpot_won_by_syndicate', 'Euromillions Jackpot Won By Syndicate', '<p>The fifth consecutive Euro Millions jackpot has been won by a ticket purchased in the UK. The huge rollover jackpot of €45 million isn''t going to just one lucky winner though, but 12 individuals playing as a syndicate. Each of the 12 syndicate members are set to become €3,750,000 richer, an amount that will surely change their lives over night. The Euro Millions Syndicate winners are of the Corby area of Northamptonshire England, and are reportedly all local bus drivers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A DJ in the area, Jerry Wright, posted to Twitter “12 Corby based bus drivers scoop the Euromillions last night, the whole town is talking about it, try getting a bus in corby today! Lol" Naturally getting a bus in Corby wasn''t so easy on Saturday after the holders of the winning ticket came forward" All Camelot will confirm is that a single ticket has come forward from that area on Saturday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A driver working at the nearby Kettering bus depot has said "We worked out who they were though because seven of them... never turned up for work, and to be fair I don''t blame them." Reports in UK newspapers claim that one of the drivers even walked out halfway through his shift after discovering he''d won just over €3 million.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What can be said without doubt is that the winners all enjoyed far better odds because they played in a syndicate. Given the enormous rollover prizes players can still become millionaires despite the prize being split between 12 people. </p>', 'Euromillions Jackpot Won By Syndicate', 'EuroMillions Syndicate, EuroMillions WInners', 'Thanks to this Friday''s big rollover jackpot there are 12 new multi-millionaires in the UK', 2, 1332074823, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euromillions Jackpot Won By Syndicate', '/images/news/euromillions_4.jpg', '<p>Thanks to this Friday''s big rollover jackpot there are 12 new multi-millionaires in the UK</p>', 'EuroMillions Syndicate Winners', NULL, 1332074823, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (110, 94, 'en', 'euromillions_syndicate_winners_speak_out', 'Euromillions Syndicate Winners Speak Out', '<p>The 12 winners of the latest <a href="http://euromillions.com/">EuroMillions</a> jackpot have come forward to discuss their plans for their new found fortunes. The total prize they are splitting is a whopping €45,758,710, meaning each lucky entrant will receive approximately €3,813,226 each. In actuality only 11 of the 12 winning syndicate members have chosen to come forward to talk about their prize, while one is choosing to remain quiet and anonymous.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The stories of the 12 bus depot staff from Northamptonshire range from the generous to the hilarious. 11 of the 12 all met today to celebrate the big win at the Best Western Rockingham Forest hotel in Corby. Charlie Gillion (65) joked that he had to borrow £1 from his wife this morning to buy the newspaper. In a show of great generosity though Charlie plans to buy his daughter and her two children their own home with his winnings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the moment his daughter Marianne Gillion (44) is living alone with her two sons of 14 and 16 in rented accommodation, but she has already started viewing four bedroom homes for her family. A smiling Marianne said yesterday of the win “I am absolutely over the moon. I didn''t think anything like this in a million years would ever happen. It is something you dream of. I have always said I wouldn''t be in a position to buy a house”. The local supermarket worker will also have her father to thank for the car he plans to buy her too. Of her father she said “He is putting other people first, which it what he does all the time”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Charlie Gillion is a father of three, a grandfather to ten, and a great grandfather to six, and he''s keen to use his new found riches to help his huge family. “The first thing for us to do is to help the family out, we have to make sure everyone is comfortable” said the 65 year old. His wife Penelope, also 65 years old, said the win is “the perfect retirement present”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While the former bus depot workers were being treated to their luxury lunch with lottery operators Camelot, one member (40 year old Charles Connor) turned down the caviar offered to him stating “I am a working class lad – I am not going to turn into some Lord Fauntleroy”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tragically a female worker named Hazel Loveday had apparently only left the £2 a week syndicate just 6 months ago, and has now missed out on a share of this big win. Her luckier colleagues refused to discuss her position in depth but did say “We all like Hazel, she''s a good friend”. Unsurprisingly none of the syndicate members made it to their place of work on Saturday said Camelot.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 11 syndicate members who have come forward are Derek Wilson, 51, Ally Spence, 57, Charlie Connor, 40, Alex Robertson, 57, Neil Tayton, 58, Dave Mead 54, Charlie Gillion, 65, Jim Paton, 55, John Noakes, 49, Chris Smith, 34 and Stephen Derrick, 53. Of these men already 5 have handed in their notice to their employer. The syndicate leader Chris Smith said “We started the syndicae about three years ago and everyone chose a set of numbers – it''s only £2 each in the pot every week. “I always try to watch the draw show live, or record it, and check off all our numbers.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“On Friday my partner checked half our numbers and I checked the other half – she just passed the winning ticket over and paused the TV on the numbers. We kept looking at it and passing it between each other about four or five times. We couldn''t really believe they all matched” he added “Times have been very tough for everyone – we were facing up to shifts being cut, which can really hit you in the pocket. This win means so much and is life-changing for everybody – people can live their dreams and help out their families”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>“This couldn''t have happened to a better bunch of blokes. We are all friends as well as colleagues and I am happy that we have all won together”.</p>', 'Euromillions Syndicate Winners Speak Out', 'Euromillions Winners, Euromillions Syndicate', 'The twelve winners of Friday''s enormous jackpot celebrate their win and speak publicly', 2, 1332276303, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euromillions Syndicate Winners Speak Out', '', '<p>The twelve winners of Friday''s enormous jackpot celebrate their win and speak publicly</p>', 'Euromillions Syndicate Winners', NULL, 1332254818, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (111, 95, 'en', 'euro_jackpot_first_draw', 'Euro Jackpot First Draw', '<p>The Euro Jackpot has gotten off to a strong start, but has in it''s first draw refused to relinquish it''s jackpot prize. This means that on Friday the 30th March the rollover jackpot of €11,000,00 will be available with odds of only 1 in 59 million! </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Even the game''s second place prize of approximately €250,000 has eluded a winner! The third prize however has been won by two people who have successfully matched 5 main numbers only. These two ticket holders will receive a fantastic €42,755 each! Just behind that a full 12 people managed to match 4 main numbers and 2 extra numbers with the draw and will be receiving an excellent fourth place prize of €6,577.70 each.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The number of winners increases dramatically with Friday''s 5th place Euro Jackpot prize. A full 245 people can claim €255 each, for matching 4 main and 1 extra number. A further 302 people matched just 4 main numbers for a great prize of €130.60 and in 7th place an enormous 706 winners can claim €73.20.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What can be said of the Euro Jackpot is that the chance to return hundreds of Euro''s for a €2 ticket cost is as far improved over the Euro Millions as the jackpot odds are. Next Friday''s draw will almost certainly see a winner, but if not there will still be plenty of people lining their pockets with Euro Jackpot cash.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In a development both hilarious and tragic, depending on which side you see it from, 302 Danish players received an email shortly after the draw claiming that they had won billions of Danish Crowns. An hour and a half later however each player received another email revealing that each player had won various others amounts from €8.40 to €73.20. Thomas Rorsig, spokesperson for Danish Euro Jackpot organiser "Danske Spil" said, "All won prizes but not billions of crowns".</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He said it was all done to simple human error when Dansk Spil employees were emailing Danish cash prize winners. Thomas Rorsig added "Nothing like this has ever happened before, and I hope it never does again."</p>', 'Euro Jackpot First Draw', 'EuroJackpot, First Draw, Euro Jackpot First Draw', 'The first result of the new European lottery has made a lot of people much better off', 2, 1332744005, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euro Jackpot First Draw', '/images/news/eurojackpot.png', '<p>The first result of the new European lottery has made a lot of people much better off</p>', 'Euro Jackpot result', NULL, 1332668224, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (112, 96, 'en', 'french_euro_millions_jackpot_winner', 'French Euro Million''s Jackpot Winner', '<p>Tonight''s jackpot has been reset to the minimum €15,000,000 after one lucky ticket holder is entitled to Friday''s enormous prize of €26,096,499. The winner is based in France and has managed to break the run of consecutive jackpot winners based in the UK. All that is known of this anonymous ticket holder is that their ticket was purchased in Pas de Calais and that they only have 60 days to claim their prize. In an effort to retain the anonymity of the winner the Francais De Jeux will not reveal the particular city the player bought their ticket in.</p>\r\n\r\n<P>Where the next jackpot is going nobody can be sure. However while the UK has recently been celebrating it''s 5th consecutive win, the French are still on top having had a huge 68 jackpots distributed to <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/255/french-euro-millions-jackpot-winner">French Euromillions winners</a> since the beginning of the game.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euromillions numbers</a> 9, 15, 23, 31, 50 and Lucky Stars 8 and 11 brought more than just the jackpot to France, as many more people have won cash prizes. In fact 7 people from Friday''s draw managed to match 5 numbers and 1 star to make themselves €237,782 richer. Behind them were a further 11 people who have won €50,439 and then 43 people who can claim €6,451.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tickets are still available online for tonight''s draw, and you''ve got to be in it to win it.</p>', 'French Euro Million''s Jackpot Winner', 'Euromillions Winner, French Euromillions Winner', 'Finally the run of Euro Million''s jackpots being won in the UK comes to a close', 2, 1332928696, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'French Euro Millions Jackpot Winner', '/images/news/franceflag.png', '<p>Finally the run of Euro Million''s jackpots being won in the UK comes to a close</p>', 'French Euromillions Winner', NULL, 1332836406, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (113, 97, 'en', 'euromillions_winners_tuesday_27th_march', 'Euromillions Winners Tuesday 27th March', '<p>Last nights Euromillions jackpot had no chance to rollover yesterday as one ticket is confirmed to have matched all of the numbers drawn. While no information has been released with regards to the owner of the ticket we hope they come forward quickly to claim their €15,000,000 prize. The <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euromillions Result</a> of 24, 27, 29, 34, 36 and Lucky Stars 7 and 8 failed to create a winner in the second prize tier; nobody matched 5 numbers and 1 star.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are however 8 tickets that match 5 main numbers only and the ticket holders in this prize category stand to gain  life altering €154,453.22 when they come forward to claim their winnings. Other great <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-prize-structure">Euromillions Prizes</a> include the 24 winners of €6,435.55 and 577 winners of €234.22, all of whom will be grateful they invested just a few Euro in their ticket.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/255/french-euro-millions-jackpot-winner">French Euromillions Winner</a> of Friday has still yet to come forward to claim their €26 million. In France the prizes will only wait for 60 days before being turned over to good causes so the player had best act fast! Another big Euro Millions winner from Limerick, Ireland has also still to claim their prize from last Tuesday''s draw.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The prize waiting for the denizen of Limerick is a highly desirable €468,877 and yesterday spokespeople from the Irish lottery organisers confirmed it remains unclaimed. “It is still unclaimed, which is very unusual because it is a substantial prize”, the spokesperson continued “We haven''t hear from anyone with regard to that ticket but whoever has it has 90 days to come forward and claim it. It is unusual but there is still tons of time”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The owner of the local Spar shop where the ticket was sold, Mike Gleeson, has no idea who the lucky player is, “There has not been a peep s to who the winner is”. Mike''s shop has a record of selling  €2.1 million ticket back in 2006.</p>', 'Euromillions Winners Tuesday 27th March', 'Euromillions Winners, Unclaimed Euromillions Prizes', 'Yesterday''s jackpot could go very quickly as one ticket matches the necessary numbers', 2, 1332927854, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euromillions Winners Tuesday 27th March', '/images/news/euromillions_4.jpg', '<p>Yesterday''s jackpot could go very quickly as one ticket matches the necessary numbers</p>', 'Euromillions Winners', NULL, 1332921202, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (114, 98, 'en', 'french_euro_millions_winner_claims_prize', 'French Euro Millions Winner Claims Prize', '<p>The €15 million jackpot won in Tuesday''s draw is confirmed to be the rightful property of another French winner. This is the second consecutive jackpot won by a ticket purchased in France following the <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/255/french-euro-millions-jackpot-winner">French Euromillions winner</a> of €26,000,000 on Friday, who has now come forward and is of Wimereux in the North of France. The citizen of Wimereux will have to wait just a little bit longer while the Francais De Jeux confirm the winning ticket.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Meanwhile the still unknown winner of Tuesday''s €15,000,000 Euromillions Prize has 60 days to make themselves known to the Francais De Jeux. All that is known for sure at this stage is that they are from the Maritime Alps near the border with Italy. This makes three French winners in total in 2012 as in January a man from the Calvados region pocketed a huge rollover jackpot of €36 million.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Eyes are now on Friday''s upcoming <a href="http://www.euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euromillions results</a> which may distribute another €15,000,000 to one lucky winner. With Euromillions.com you''ve got your chance to claim this jackpot from anywhere in the world, so why wait to purchase your ticket?</p>', 'French Euro Millions Winner Claims Prize', 'Euromillions Winner, French Euromillions Winner', 'The French Euromillions winner of €26,000,000 has claimed their prize almost a week after the draw', 2, 1333014878, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'French Euro Millions Winner Claims Prize', '/images/news/euromillions_1.jpg', '<p>The French Euromillions winner of €26,000,000 has claimed their prize almost a week after the draw</p>', 'French Euromillions Winner', NULL, 1333012908, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (115, 99, 'en', 'mega_millions_jackpot_record', 'Mega Millions Jackpot Record', '<p>The largest lottery jackpot in the history of the world is now available for lotto enthusiasts every where to take the chance at winning. The Mega Millions lottery in the U.S is advertising a a prize of approximately $540,000,000 -€377,000,000. This gargantuan prize is sky rocketing Mega Million''s ticket sales, as players from all over American queue outside of their local retailers for their chance at the big time. The Mega Millions Prize advertised is of course only the annuity jackpot value, meaning it''s the amount you''ll receive if you choose to receive the money as 26 annual installments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Taken as a lump sum payment however the prize is still a world record. If you manage to match all 5 main numbers that you choose from 1-56, and the 1 bonus number that''s chosen from 1-46, then you can claim a lump sum payment of $389,000,000 -€291,000,000. Click for more information about how to play Mega Millions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The big question on the minds of people all over the world now is “Can I play Mega Millions outside of the U.S?”. Thankfully the answer to this is yes! Due to our partnership with some of the biggest and most trusted online lottery ticket purchasing services you can play purchase a Mega Millions ticket and be in with your chance of winning the prize by clicking <a href="http://ads.playukinternet.com/tracking.php/text/3451/12959/3929003/8503\r\n" link rel="nofollow" target=_"blank">here</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In case you should happen to win the jackpot from outside of the U.S by playing the <a href="http://megamillions-online.com/" target=_"blank">Mega Millions Online</a> then be aware that you will only be able to claim the prize as a lump sum. While the annuity payments won''t be available to you, the prize will still make you the riches lottery winner in history! Now that you''ve got the ability to play Mega Millions online what are you waiting for?</p>', 'Mega Millions Jackpot Record', 'Mega Millions, Biggest Jackpot', 'The biggest lottery jackpot in history is available now with the Mega Millions', 2, 1333098042, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Mega Millions Jackpot Record', '', '<p>The biggest lottery jackpot in history is available now with the Mega Millions</p>', 'Mega Millions Jackpot', NULL, 1333097704, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (116, 100, 'de', 'usa_im_lottofieber', 'USA im Lottofieber', '<p>Der höchste Jackpot aller Zeiten in Höhe von 540 Millionen US-Dollar (~377 Mio. Euro) wird heute bei den „MegaMillions“ ausgespielt. Die hohe Gewinnsumme hat einen Ansturm auf die Lottoannahmestellen ausgelöst. Die Ziehungen der Mega Millions finden dienstags und freitags statt. Da seit 18 Ziehungen der Jackpot nicht geknackt wurde, hat sich die riesige Jackpotsumme angesammelt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bei den MegaMillions kann ein Tipp für 1 Dollar erworben werden. Um den Jackpot zu knacken, müssen 5 Zahlen von 1 bis 56 ausgewählt werden, und dann noch die Zusatzzahl („The Megaball“) von 1 bis 46. Wenn alle 6 Zahlen mit dem Ziehungsergebnis überein stimmen hat man den Hauptgewinn! Klingt einfach, jedoch beträgt die Chance 1 zu 176 Millionen. Auch bei fünf Richtigen wird eine Gewinnsumme ausbezahlt, die sich auf 250.000 US-Dollar (~ 187.000 Euro) beläuft.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bei der Gewinnausschüttung kann sich der Gewinner aussuchen ob er die gesamte Summe als lebenslange Ratenzahlung ausgezahlt haben möchte, oder als einmalige Auszahlung, bei der allerdings nur ein Teil des Jackpots ( 389 Millionen US Dollar = ~ 291 Millionen Euro) ausgeschüttet wird.</p>', 'USA im Lottofieber', 'Megamillions, Mega Millions, Lotto, Lotterie, Jackpot, 540 Millionen', 'USA Megamillions Lottofieber. Der höchste Jackpot aller Zeiten in Höhe von 540 Millionen US-Dollar (~377 Mio. Euro) wird heute bei den „Mega Millions“ ausgespielt', 1, 1333098964, 9, 'Jenny Zimmerman', 'USA im Lottofieber', '', '<p>Der höchste Jackpot aller Zeiten in Höhe von 540 Millionen US-Dollar (~377 Mio. Euro) wird heute bei den „Mega Millions“ ausgespielt.</p>', 'Megamillions Höchsten Jackpot', NULL, 1333098964, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (117, 101, 'en', 'megamillions_biggest_jackpot_winners', 'Megamillions Biggest Jackpot Winners', '<p>Saturday''s <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/258/mega-millions-jackpot-record">Mega Millions</a> jackpot will go down in lotto history as being one of the greatest prizes ever offered or distributed by any world lottery game. The colossal prize of $640 million -€480 million- had been sought after by record breaking numbers of lotto players, and all of America has been in the grip lottery fever. Who can blame these lotto enthusiasts for trying to grab some of the worlds biggest cash prize? Even with winning odds of only 1 in 175 million. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Regardless of those odds, there is now a total of three winning tickets eligible for the jackpot prize. These three tickets beat all the odds and managed to successfully match the numbers 2-4-23-38-46 and the Mega Ball 23, to make their owners very rich people. Each ticket is in line to claim a whopping $213 million (€160 million) fortune.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So what of the three ticket holders? So far none have come forward, so the hunt is on. Journalists all over the States are desperately trying to find some information on the winners, and they''re narrowing their search. For certain we know that the first lucky winner purchased their ticket in the small town of Red Bud in Illinois, the retailer at the shop where the ticket was sold can also reveal that the numbers on the ticket were chosen at random by machine in the “quick pick” option!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The owner of the store in Red Bud will receive $500,000 for selling the winning ticket, and was naturally delighted saying “All day yesterday I was selling tickets and hoping someone from Red Bud would win. Never in  my wildest dreams did I think this. I''m just tickled pink!”. Denise Metzger the manager of the MotoMart shop also said “It''s just unbelievable. Everyone is wanting to know who it is”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The next winner to have all their numbers match Saturday''s draw purchased their ticket in Maryland. The 7 Eleven where the ticket was sold has already faced swarms of reporters desperate to know more about the winner. The manager of the store has repeatedly denied interviews, but will be receiving a bonus of $100,000 for selling the winning ticket. In Maryland, winners have the right to stay anonymous with their big cash prize.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The final ticket was purchased in Kansas in the north-east. In Kansas again the winner has no obligation to make themselves known. Dennis Wilson, the Kansas lottery authority Director, said of the unknown ticker holder “we sure want to meet the winner, but we want to tell them, sign the back of the ticket and secure it”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Due to the enormity of the prize pool created during this epic lottery draw many more people are still much wealthier despite missing out on the jackpot. At least 3 other ticket holders can be expected to win millions of dollars, while hundreds more will be collecting other very substantial winnings. A total of 158 people who missed the main prize by failing to match the Mega Ball, will receive $250,000 (€187,254) each.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The hunt will continue discover the identities of Saturday winners of the enormous <a href="http://megamillions-online.com/mega-millions-prizes/" target="_blank">Mega Millions prizes</a>. All eyes will be on them should they choose to go public after claiming their cash.</p>', 'Megamillions Biggest Jackpot Winners', 'Megamillions, Megamillions jackpot, megamillions winners', 'Saturday marks the end of the biggest lottery jackpot in history, as several Mega Millions tickets will make many people very rich', 2, 1333351616, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'megamillions biggest jackpot winners', '', '<p>Saturday marks the end of the biggest lottery jackpot in history, as several Mega Millions tickets will make many people very rich</p>', NULL, NULL, 1333342142, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (118, 102, 'de', 'groessten_lotto_jackpot_in_der_geschichte_der_lotterie_gewonnen', 'Größten Lotto-Jackpot in der Geschichte der Lotterie gewonnen', '<p>Der bisherige Rekordjackpot der <a href="http://megamillions-online.com">Mega Millions</a> Lotterie in der Höhe von $ 380.000.000 Dollar wurde am Samstag vom angekündigten $ 640 Millionen Dollar Jackpot gänzlich übertroffen. Der enorme Mehrfachjackpot, auch Rollover genannt, wurde von drei glücklichen Lottoscheinbesitzer mit den richtigen Zahlen 2, 4, 23, 38, 46 und dem Mega Ball 23 (Zusatzzahl) geknackt und der Gewinn jetzt gleichermaßen unter ihnen aufgeteilt. \r\nDie erfolgreichen Spieler haben noch keinen Anspruch auf ihren Gewinn gestellt, aber wir wissen, dass sie aus Red Bud Illinois, North-East Kansas und Maryland sind. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Was für eine bahnbrechende Ziehung war das? Nun zum einen haben die Ladenbesitzer, welche die Lottoscheine verkauft haben mehrere hunderttausende Dollar an Boni erhalten, nur für das Erschaffen der drei Gewinner. Jeder Gewinner erhält jeweils $ 213 Millionen Dollar, während drei weitere nicht-Jackpot Gewinner immer noch erwarten können Millionäre zu werden und weitere 158 Menschen werden immer noch pro Person $ 250.000 gewinnen! Die Wahrscheinlichkeit von 1 zu 175 Millionen zu schlagen war kein Problem für den Gewinner aus Red Bud, der eine Maschine nach dem Zufallsprinzip die Zahlen für seinen Lottoschein auswählen ließ.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Der Mega Millions Jackpot war in den Köpfen vieler Lotto Enthusiasten auf der ganzen Welt. Alle Augen waren auf diesen rekordbrechenden Jackpot gerichtet – dem größten Jackpot Betrag in der Lotto Geschichte. Diese Ziehung war so populär, alleine in Amerika wurden insgesamt fast $ 1.5 Milliarden Dollar für Lottoscheine ausgegeben. Der angekündigte Jackpot Betrag ist als einmalige Auszahlung $ 470 Millionen Dollar wert und nach Steuern immer noch enorme $ 347 Millionen Dollar. Ob Jahresrente oder nicht, der Mega Millions Jackpot vom Samstag ist immer noch einer der höchsten die jemals gesehen wurden. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Der Jackpot Betrag war so episch, sodass sogar der mächtigste Mann der Welt seine Mitarbeiter aufforderte, sie sollten versuchen das Geld für seine politische Kampagne zu gewinnen. Barack Obamas Fundraising-Team sendete eine Massen-E-Mail an ihre Unterstützter mit dem Betreff „Jackpot“ und den Worten: „Ja, wir haben auch nicht gewonnen. Also sind wir noch immer dabei!“</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Die Zahlen sind sicherlich atemberaubend, aber jetzt richten sich die Augen der Welt auf die drei richtigen Lottoscheine. Wer wird als erstes seinen riesigen Geldregen beanspruchen! Werden sie sich der Öffentlichkeit bekannt geben? Der Gewinner aus Red Bud hat keine andere Wahl außer an die Öffentlichkeit zu gehen, aber was ist mit den Lottoscheinbesitzer aus Kansas und Maryland? Eines ist jedoch sicher, im Laufe der Zeit werden weitere Nachrichten bekannt werden.</p>', 'Größten Lotto-Jackpot in der Geschichte der Lotterie gewonnen', 'Megamillios, Mega Millions, Lotto, Jackpot', 'Der Mega Millions Jackpot war in den Köpfen vieler Lotto Enthusiasten auf der ganzen Welt.', 1, 1333435829, 9, 'Jenny Zimmerman', 'Größten Lotto-Jackpot', '', '<p>Der Mega Millions Jackpot war in den Köpfen vieler Lotto Enthusiasten auf der ganzen Welt. Alle Augen waren auf diesen rekordbrechenden Jackpot gerichtet – dem größten Jackpot Betrag in der Lotto Geschichte.</p>', 'Megamillions', NULL, 1333435578, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (119, 103, 'en', 'euro_millions_winners_april_4th', 'Euro Millions Winners April 4th', '<p>Not one single ticket is eligible to claim yesterday''s <a href="http://www.euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> jackpot. On Friday this means that players will be aiming for a huge €32,000,000 prize. Will this be the start of another enormous €100,000,000 rollover or will it be you jumping for joy after you match all seven numbers on Friday? The only way to be in with a chance is to have your ticket ready for the draw.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Three players did manage to match 5 of their main numbers and 1 Lucky Star to give them the ability to claim €335,817.62 each. More big prizes were won by 13 people who matched only 5 main numbers, these ticket holders are now due €25,832.12 each. Last of the big prize winners were a full 33 people who have won €5,088.15 by matching 4 numbers and 2 Lucky Stars.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The <a href="http://www.euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euromillions numbers</a> 1, 8, 18, 25, 30 and Lucky Stars 9 and 10 have created 1,688,851 tickets that can be= redeemed for a cash prize. Whether it''s the 1,039,132 who will win €3.64 each, or the 1166 who will receive €90.00 each there have been a great many returns in Tuesday''s draw. All eyes are now on the €32,000,000 available on Friday, have you got your ticket ready yet? If not click here.</p>', 'Euro Millions Winners April 4th', 'Euro Millions Winners', 'With no winners of yesterdays draw, Friday''s prize is a lot to play for', 2, 1333526579, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euro Millions Winner April 4th', '', '<p>With no winners of yesterdays draw, Friday''s prize is a lot to play for</p>', 'Euro Millions Winners', NULL, 1333526579, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (120, 104, 'en', 'european_lottery_rollovers', 'European Lottery Rollovers', '<p>The two biggest lottery games in Europe, the <a href="http://www.euromillions.com">Euro Millions</a> and the <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/254/euro-jackpot-first-draw">Euro Jackpot</a> have both failed to produce winners with their Friday draws. For both lotteries this is the third consecutive jackpot roll-over and it means some big lottery prizes are up for grabs this week. In the Euro Jackpot come Friday there will be €13,000,000 to be won with some favourable jackpot odds. On Tuesday the Euro Millions has a prize of €39,000,000 to be won, however if it isn''t won then Friday''s jackpot will be over €45,000,000.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Without a jackpot winner in either lottery, millions of Euro''s worth of prizes were won by many lucky lottery players in both games. Seven Euro Million''s ticket holders are in line to win €236,476.97 each for matching 5 main numbers and 1 Lucky Star. Following them are a further 13 players who can claim €42,444.58 each.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Euro Jackpot result player matching 5 numbers and 1 extra number has landed themselves a prize of €312,639.00, and another player has won a full €81,286.20 for taking the third prize. This shows that while the jackpot prizes in the new Euro Jackpot are lower after a rollover than in the Euro Millions, the second and third place prizes can still be higher, and with better odds of being won.</p>', 'European Lottery Rollovers', 'Euromillions, Euro Jackpot, Eurojackpot, ', 'With two huge European lotteries now occurring every Friday the potential to win lots of lottery cash is increased', 2, 1334082698, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'European Lottery Rollovers', '', '<p>With two huge European lotteries now occurring every Friday the potential to win lots of lottery cash is increased</p>', 'Euromillions and EuroJackpot', NULL, 1333953241, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (121, 105, 'en', 'mega_millions_winners', 'Mega Millions Winners', '<p>Tonight''s enormous Euromillions prize of €39,000,000 might be on the minds of every Euromillions enthusiast, but in the grand scheme of things this prize is somewhat overshadowed by the news that winners of the biggest lottery prize in history has come forward. The <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/260/megamillions-biggest-jackpot-winners">Mega Millions jackpot</a> winning ticket holders have each won a third of a share of $656,000,000 -€501,119,983. The prize has one winning ticket from Kansas, one from Maryland and one from Illinois, the Kansas winner was first to produce their ticket on Friday, and now three players from Maryland in a syndicate have come forward with their ticket.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The winners purchased their ticket just outside of Baltimore (the State''s biggest city) in a 7-Eleven shop in Milford Mill, and are three all work at a local elementary school. They have dubbed themselves "the three amigos" and they purchased 20 tickets each for their syndicate in that draw. They group is composed of a woman in her 20''s, a man in his 40''s and another woman in her 50''s. They work together as a special education teacher, an elementary school teacher and an administrator. The lottery officials who could reveal some information about the winners have said that they are planning to backpack around Europe and visit Italy''s famous vineyards and wineries. The youngest member of the syndicate in her 20''s had to check all 60 tickets herself during the draw, in a statement to lottery officials she said "Once I realised one was a winner, I called my two friends right away".</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Maryland is one of the few states that allows it''s Jackpot winners the right to keep their anonymity, whereas in many other states the winner must make their identity public. They brought their ticket with all the winning numbers 2-4-23-38-46 and Mega Ball 23 to state lottery officials who have confirmed the prize. Last Friday the Kansas winner also came forward to collect their prize but kept their identity a secret too.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/207/life-lottery-winners-chris-colin-weir">Colin and Chris Weir</a> are no longer holders of the highest lottery jackpot ever and now only one Mega Millions winner from Illinois remains to claim their share of the prize. Maybe they are simply waiting for the furore over the prize to die down before coming forward, as their state lottery regulations don''t allow them to stay anonymous.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In news concerning the <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euro Millions results</a> one man from Athea in Limerick has just picked up his cheque for €50,000 after matching 5 numbers in the draw held on Friday the 23rd of March. The winner Thomas O''Mahony, a steel fitter in the small town, told local press “I wasn''t watching the draw when it happened, I checked the numbers at about 12 o''clock that night. I think I was holding the ticket in my hand for about an hour afterwards”.</p>.\r\n\r\n<p>The lucky Irish winner plans to pay off his mortgage and take his son on a trip to Disneyland Paris. If you would like to be one of the many people winning big Euro Millions prizes then make sure you have a ticket for tonight''s draw. With Euromillions.com you can enter the Euromillions lottery from anywhere in the world!</p>', 'Mega Millions Winners', 'Mega Millions Winners, Mega Millions Jackpot Winners', 'The claiming of two Mega Millions prizes almost over shadows tonight''s €39,000,000 Euro Millions rollover jackpot', 2, 1334061301, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Mega Millions Jackpot Winners', '', '<p>The claiming of two Mega Millions prizes almost over shadows tonight''s €39,000,000 Euro Millions rollover jackpot</p>', 'Mega Millions Winners', NULL, 1334043894, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (122, 106, 'en', 'unclaimed_euro_millions_prizes', 'Unclaimed Euro Millions Prizes', '<p>With the fourth consecutive rollover the Euromillions jackpot has leaped from €39,000,000 to €53,000,000. Such a staggering prize hasn''t been seen in many weeks.  The last ticket to win a prize close to this one was held by a <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/252/euromillions-jackpot-won-by-syndicate">Euromillions  Syndicate</a> of 12 bus drivers from the UK. They each won a share of €45,000,000 each and are now all happily retired. While this enormous prize could be yours after tonight, if you live in the Doncaster or Nottingham areas of the UK then you may want to have a look at some of your older tickets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On Friday the 23rd of March 2012 a EuroMillions ticket in the UK matched the raffle code LHZ360128. The ticket holder who lives in Nottingham has yet to claim their £1,000,000 prize! From a draw the next week on Tuesday 27th March there is yet another <a href="http://www.euromillions.com/euromillions-uk-millionaire-raffle">Millionaire Raffle</a> ticket winner who again is due £1,000,000. The winners have till the 19th and 23rd of September respectively to claim their prizes before they are distributed to good causes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a limit to how long a player can wait before claiming a National Lottery spokesperson has said "The clock is now ticking for these two lucky ticket-holders". Eager to ensure the Euromillions players in that area know what their ticket could be worth a million pounds the spokesperson has said "We want players to check down the back of the sofa and in coat pockets as these millions could be hiding anywhere."</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hopefully these winner''s claim their fortunes soon, but could you have the <a href="http://www.euromillions.com/euromillions-results">winning Euro Millions Numbers</a> to claim a fortune of €53,000,000 this evening? If so then make sure you buy your tickets before the countdown finishes!</p>', 'Unclaimed Euro Millions Prizes', 'Unclaimed Euro Millions Prizes', 'While the eyes of most players will be on tonight''s big prize, there are two players from the UK who should have their eye on their last tickets', 2, 1334298935, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Unclaimed Euro Millions Prizes', '', '<p>While the eyes of most players will be on tonight''s big prize, there are two players from the UK who should have their eye on their last tickets.</p>', 'Millionaire Raffle Ticket', NULL, 1334298585, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (123, 107, 'en', 'euromillions_winner_on_friday_13th_draw', 'EuroMillions Winner on Friday 13th  Draw', '<p>After 4 consecutive rollovers, last Fridays EuroMillions draw saw one winning ticket worth €53,763,217. This is the highest EuroMillions Jackpot since <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/243/third-consecutive-uk-euromillions-jackpot-winner">an anonymous winner from the UK</a> scooped a mouth watering €54,897,476 on 24.02.2012.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Recent polls have shown a surge in <a href="http://online-lottos.com">online lotto</a> sales of 18%, proving that more lottery enthusiasts are moving from traditional shop sales over to the web. Our own internal poll suggests the mains reasons are convenience and that it’s impossible to lose your lottery ticket. On evidence from news from Camelot <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/265/unclaimed-euro-millions-prizes">unclaimed Euromillions tickets</a> are still a massive problem with Millions going uncollected every year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Friday the 13th proved another unlucky day for <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/250/eurojackpot-a-short-comparison-to-euromillions">Eurojackpot</a>, after its launch on 23rd March the Eurojackpot has rolled over for 4 consecutive weeks, the Jackpot now stands at €15 Million, the same as Euromillions next draw on Tuesday the 17th April.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The EuroJackpot is organised in the following countries: Denmark, Germany, Estonia, Finland, Netherlands, Slovenia and Italy.</p>', 'EuroMillions Winner on Friday 13th  Draw', 'Winner, Euromillions, Friday, 13th April', 'One Lucky Winner Bags over €53 Millions on Friday 13/04/2012', 2, 1334400389, 3, 'Alison Davis', 'EuroMillions Winner on Friday 13th  Draw', '', '<p>One Lucky Winner Bags over €53 Millions on Friday 13/04/2012</p>', 'Friday 13th', NULL, 1334400389, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (124, 108, 'en', 'portuguese_winner_of_euromillions', 'Portuguese Winner Of  EuroMillions', '<p>The enormous jackpot from Friday the 13th will be going to a winner who purchased their ticket in Portugal.  The prize of €53,763,217 will go to that one ticket in Portugal that has matched all of the numbers drawn on Friday; 8, 13, 26, 39, 43 and Lucky Stars 3 and 5. The winner of the quadruple rollover has yet to make themselves known publicly, but information on where they are from has come directly from lottery organisers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This huge <a href="http://www.euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euro Millions result</a> has also created a high number of second prize winners who will win life changing sums of money. In fact a total of 15 people managed to match 5 main numbers and 1 Lucky Star to win €142,395.47 each. A further 26 people have matched 5 main numbers only to land themselves an impressive €27,383.74. Such high numbers of second and third prize winners are not uncommon when the jackpot is at such a huge amount as ticket sales increase dramatically.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tuesday''s <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-prize-structure">Euromillions prize</a> will be reset to €15,000,000 and with Euromillions.com you could be claiming this prize from anywhere in the world!</p>', 'Portuguese Winner Of EuroMillions', 'Euromillions WInner, Euromillions jackpot winner, Portuguese euromillions winner', 'Friday''s enormous quadruple rollover has created many winners, but the top prize goes to Portugal', 2, 1334660692, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Portuguese Rollover Winner', '', '<p>Friday''s enormous quadruple rollover has created many winners, but the top prize goes to Portugal</p>', 'Portuguese Euromillions WInner', NULL, 1334564762, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (125, 109, 'en', 'euro_millions_euro_jackpot_winners', 'Euro Millions & Euro Jackpot Winners', '<p>The <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/265/unclaimed-euro-millions-prizes">unclaimed EuroMillions prize</a> of £1,000,000 in Doncaster has finally been claimed. The ticket holder had won a Millionaire Raffle prize on the 27th of March and after many weeks of the prize laying unclaimed many believed it would be lost. A spokesperson for Camelot in the UK has said “It would have been awful if the ticket-holder had missed out on this life-changing amount of money”. The winner has chosen to keep their anonymity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On Friday both of the big Pan-European lotteries the Euro Jackpot and the Euro Millions failed to create a jackpot winner. This means that both prizes will rollover to the next draw. In the case of the Euromillions there will be a €32,000,000 jackpot prize up for grabs on Tuesday. On Friday you''ll be able to take the chance at winning €16,000,000 with the Euro Jackpot. While the jackpot prizes remain without a winner there were still plenty of people made rich from Friday''s draws.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 lucky Euro Jackpot player matched 5 main numbers and 1 Euro Number to win an enormous second prize of €640,892. Second prize winners of Friday''s <a href="http://www.euromillions.com/euromillions-results">EuroMillions Result</a> were 6 lucky ticket holders who will each receive €275,784.59. In third place in the Euro Millions for matching just 5 main numbers are twelve winners of €45,964.10 each, and in the Euro Jackpot a much bigger third place prize of €166,632 will be awarded to just 1 ticket holder.</p>', 'Euro Millions & Euro Jackpot Winners Friday 20th April', 'Euro Millions Winners, Euro Jackpot Winners, ', 'The Euro Millions and Euro Jackpot grand prizes remain untouched after Friday''s draw', 2, 1335170885, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euromillions and EuroJackpot winners Friday 20th April', '', '<p>The Euro Millions and Euro Jackpot grand prizes remain untouched after Friday''s draw</p>', 'European Lottery Winners', NULL, 1335169586, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (126, 110, 'en', 'euromillions_jackpot_rolls_over_to_44_million', 'Euromillions Jackpot Rolls Over to €44 Million', '<p>After just 3 consecutive rollovers the Euromillions grand prize is now a spectacular €44,000,000. That means that this Friday you could be in with a chance of winning either this enormous amount, or the Euro Jackpot''s €16,000,000 rollover prize. In the case of the <a href="http://www.playeurojackpot.com/">Euro Jackpot</a> there has yet to be a jackpot winner in the 6 draws since the game began, which begs the question “How high will this prize be before it''s won?”</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yesterday''s <a href="http://www.euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euro Millions draw</a> will put smiles on a lot of faces as a total of 1,666,505 tickets have won cash prizes. 3 of those prize winning tickets will bring their owners a life changing €341,799.63 for matching all but 1 Lucky Star. A further 3 people have won €113,933.21 each for matching just 5 main numbers. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The hunt is also on for a <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-uk-millionaire-raffle">Millionaire Raffle</a> winner of £1,000,000 who only has days left to claim the prize from the draw on November 2nd. On the 2nd of May if the prize winner has not claimed their winnings by 23:00 GMT then the cash -plus interest since the draw- will go to good causes within the UK. The winning Millionaire Raffle code for the ticket is NSX597128.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We know for certain that the ticket was purchased in the South Lanarkshire area of Scotland. A spokesperson for Camelot in the UK has said that “Of all the unclaimed prizes we have at the moment in Scotland, this is the largest”. In an urgency to stress that this ticket could be stuffed down somebodies couch in the area the spokesperson continued: “I would encourage all our players across South Lanarkshire to have a good search for the ticket as £1 million is a life-changing sum of money”</p>', 'Euromillions News', 'Euromillions news, unclaimed euromillions prizes,', 'Another rollover see''s the Euromillions offering another enormous jackpot prize', 2, 1378212506, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'euromillions news april 25th', '', '<p>Another rollover see''s the Euromillions offering another enormous jackpot prize</p>', 'Euro Millions Winners', NULL, 1335342782, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (127, 111, 'en', 'sister_of_euromillions_winner_spends_generous_gift', 'Sister Of EuroMillions Winner Spends Generous Gift', '<p>The sister of <a href="http://euromillions.com/latest-euromillionaires-speak-publicly">Dave and Angela Dawes</a> who won a spectacular €101,203,600 in October last year has started to take advantage of a generous cash gift from her brother. Janet Marquis has not revealed just how much she received from the Euro Millions winning couple, but the 46 year old has however moved from her £220,000 semi detached home in Kent to something much more comfortable with her hubby James.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Neighbours have been talking with local news sources about the move, but say that they are bound to secrecy with regard to details. One neighbour has said this week “The money had been well deserved and I know she is spending it wisely”. After the huge <a href="http://euromillions.com/">Euro Millions jackpot</a> win in October Mr Dawes made a public pledge to make 20 of his family and friends millionaires. His half sister Janet Marquis was one of the first lucky few to feel the benefits of his generosity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dave Dawes a 47 year old -former- factory supervisor said at the time of his win “Any one who has helped us through our life, we intend to make them millionaires”. Mrs Marquis spoke directly about her brother''s generosity after she received the gift: “We have had all this thrust upon us, so it''s really all very strange at the moment.” she continued “I would prefer not to say how much he''s given me, but it is genuinely life-changing and will be very well spent”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another former neighbour of Mrs Marquis has said “We were all as surprised and as pleased as they were I think when we all found out. Janet''s brother must be a very generous man but it is well deserved”.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want to be the one making your family and friends millionaires then tonight''s enormous Euromillions rollover prize could be just what you need. Just purchase a ticket before the deadline and you could be in with a chance of winning a life changing €44,000,000!</p>', 'Sister Of EuroMillions Spends Generous Gift', 'Euromillions winners, Dave Dawes, Angela Dawes', 'In October 2011 Dave and Angela Dawes winners of €101 million promised to make 20 of their closest family and friends millionaires...', 2, 1335517086, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Sister Of Dave Dawes Spends Money', '', '<p>In October 2011 Dave and Angela Dawes winners of €101 million promised to make 20 of their closest family and friends millionaires...</p>', 'Dave & Angela Dawes', 'Euro Millions Winners Dave & Angela Dawes', 1335517086, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (128, 112, 'en', 'euro_millions_winners_27th_april', 'Euro Millions Winners 27th April', '<p>Another great fortune was won on Friday''s EuroMillions draw. The jackpot prize of €44,407,281.00 was won by a Spanish ticket holder who has yet to come forward. The ticket purchased somewhere in Spain matched Friday''s <a href="http://www.euromillions.com/euromillions-results">EuroMillions result</a> of 20, 27, 30, 36, 43 and Lucky Stars 1 and 6. These numbers were lucky for an enormous 2,638,129 ticket holders who can all claim Euro Millions cash.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Among the large number of winning tickets, 4 of them will bring the life changing sum of €432,746.40 to their lucky owners for matching 6 numbers. Another 4 tickets that have successfully matched just 5 numbers are worth €144,248.80 each. These second and third place prizes are substantially higher than average, due to the big <a href="http://www.euromillions.com">Euro Millions</a> prize fund, which was created by the triple rollover.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On Friday the Euro Jackpot hit it''s 6th consecutive rollover jackpot. The drawn numbers of 10,13,19,45 and Euro Numbers 3 and 5 created 1 winner of it''s second prize of €303,201.90. Its third prize can''t be claimed as nobody matched just 5 numbers. 11 players however did match 4 main numbers and 2 Euro Numbers for a very nice prize of €6,615.30 each.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On Tuesday the Euro Millions jackpot will be starting at €15,000,000 again. To be in with a chance of winning this huge cash sum from the comfort of your home then buy your tickets with euromillions.com now.</p>', 'Euro Millions Winners 27th April', 'Euromillions, Euro Millions Winners', 'Friday''s enormous jackpot has been won by a single ticket holder, and plenty of more people won Euro Millions cash', 2, 1335779655, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euro Millions Winners 27th April', '', '<p>Friday''s enormous jackpot has been won by a single ticket holder, and plenty of more people won Euro Millions cash</p>', 'Euro Millions Winners', NULL, 1335779655, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (129, 113, 'en', 'euromillions_winners_1st_may', 'EuroMillions Winners 1st May', '<p>Tuesday''s <a href="http://www.euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euro Millions Result</a> of 4, 5, 15, 19, 41 and Lucky Stars 9 and 11 have created many winners of large prizes. The jackpot however remains untouched, meaning that this Friday there will be an estimated €25,000,000 to play for. The biggest winner is a ticket holder of Tuesday is from Ireland, they took a Euro Millions Plus entry with their ticket and matched 5 numbers. This Ireland only extra game won this player €500,000. The player from Newbridge in Ireland bought their ticket at the Ballymany Spar store run by Dave Cullen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The winner has yet to come forward and Mr Cullen has said “The winner hasn''t made him or herself known to us” then continuing “They don''t need to – all they have to do is make themselves known to the lotto. This is our first Euromillions win, we had a lotto plus winner who won €350,000 once. We are celebrating the win but we would celebrate in style if we had some of it” he joked.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>More substantial sums of money were won by two ticket holders who matched all their numbers except for 1 Lucky Star. These winners will be claiming €425,249.23 each. In the third prize category was a total of nine winners of €31,499.94 each for matching just 5 main numbers. The last substantial <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-prize-structure">Euro Millions prizes</a> were won by a full 28 people who matched 4 main numbers and 2 Lucky Stars. These winners will receive €5,062.49.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Friday offers two substantial jackpot prizes. The first is the Euro Jackpot, with more favourable odds than the Euro Millions to win €18,000,000. The second is of course the €25,000,000 offered by the Euro Millions. To play in the Euro Jackpot draw for Friday click <a href="http://www.playeurolotto.com/en/registration/eurojackpot/">here</a>, for the Euro Millions click <a href="http://www.play.euromillions.com">here</a>.</p>', 'EuroMillions Winners 1st May', 'Euro Millions, Euro Millions Winners', 'Despite the lack of a jackpot winner plenty of people won some substantial amounts of money in Tuesday''s Euromillions draw.', 2, 1336030967, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euro Millions WInners 1st May', '', '<p>Despite the lack of a jackpot winner plenty of people won some substantial amounts of money in Tuesday''s Euromillions draw.</p>', 'Euro Millions WInning TIcket', NULL, 1336030905, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (130, 114, 'en', 'unclaimed_prize_goes_to_charity', 'Unclaimed Prize Goes To Charity', '<p align="justify">A £1,000,000 <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-prize-structure">Euro Millions prize</a> has today gone to charitable causes. The prize was won by a Millionaire Raffle ticket on the 4th of November 2011, but nobody came forward to claim it. The six months waiting period has passed, and now the cash (plus any interest generated) has gone to good causes within the UK. The ticket was purchased in South Lanarkshire, Scotland and at 11pm on Wednesday the deadline for claiming the prize ended.</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">A spokesperson for Camelot said: “I can confirm that the ticket holder did not come forward within the deadline to claim their prize, and has now sadly missed out on this substantial amount of money” he continued “To avoid this situation happening again, I would urge all Lottery players to check their tickets on a regular basis. We have tried very hard to find the ticket holder and it''s a real shame that they have missed out, but there is still one winner – the nation.”</p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">There may even be a second Scottish winner missing out on the same prize! Another winning <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-uk-millionaire-raffle">UK Millionaire Raffle</a> ticket that was purchased in North Ayrshire expires in 19 days. With so much lottery cash going unclaimed the case for purchasing your ticket online is as strong as ever. Purchase your <a href="http://euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> ticket for Fridays draw online now and receive an email when you win a prize! Click <a href="http://www.play.euromillions.com">here</a> to pick your numbers online.</p>', 'Unclaimed Prize Goes To Charity', 'Unclaimed EuroMillions Prize, Euromillions Good Causes', 'The news may be grim for one mystery Euromillions ticket holder in the UK today, but it couldn''t be better for Euromillions Good Causes', 2, 1377244583, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'unclaimed millionaire raffle ticket goes to charity', '', '<p align="justify">The news may be grim for one mystery Euromillions ticket holder in the UK today, but it couldn''t be better for Euromillions Good Causes</p>', 'Unclaimed Euromillions Prize', NULL, 1336116001, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (131, 115, 'en', 'euromillions_winners_3rd_may', 'euromillions-winners-3rd-may', '<p align="justify">The <a href="http://www.euromillions.com/euromillions-results">EuroMillions numbers</a> for Friday produced a staggering 2,338,618 winners in places all over the world! Five of these lucky tickets were held by players matching 5 main numbers plus 1 Lucky Star. They will each be awarded €329,061.76. These 5 <a href="http://euromillions.com/">Euromillions</a> tickets came closest to taking the jackpot which has rolled over again. Our first jackpot this week will be for an estimated €32,000,000. Could this be the start of another enormous prize in the hundreds of millions?<p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">For matching 5 main numbers only, 4 winners have won themselves €137,109.07. The result of the draw 3, 26, 39, 40, 41 and Lucky Stars 1 and 2 also produced 43 winners of €6,529.00. These players had matched 4 main numbers and 2 Stars. </p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">For a complete list of the prize each ticket won check out our <a href="http://www.euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euromillions prize breakdown</a></p>', 'Euromillions Winners 3rd May', 'Euromillions, Euromillions Winners, Euromillions results', 'There were a huge number of winning tickets bought for last Friday''s Euro Millions draw, some of those for some significant amounts ', 2, 1377247187, 11, 'Rory Renehan', 'Euromillions Winners 3rd May', '', '<p align="justify"><h2>Last Friday''s Euromillions draw saw many winners</h2></p>', 'Euromillions Winners', NULL, 1336377442, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (132, 116, 'en', 'how_lotteries_change_lives', 'How Lotteries Change Lives', '<p align="justify"><strong>Winning the lottery</strong> can be a life changer, both positively and negatively.  Let’s look at the example of Brad Duke - he won $ 220 Million in the American Powerball lottery and pocketed  $ 85 Million after the tax authorities took their chunk. He certainly did it right, as he’s looking financially strong 7 years after his lucky win! How did he and other winners manage the situation?</p></br>\r\n<img src="http://euromillions.com/images/Brad.jpg" alt="Brad Duke - Lottery Millionaire" /></br>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nBrad gathered a team of experienced bond jugglers around him and invested roughly half of his winnings into low risk stocks. Then, $35 Million was invested into higher risk, higher return stocks. He founded a family foundation and kept his lifestyle low profile by buying a VW Jetta.</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nOn the other hand you have the story of Michael Carroll, self-proclaimed “King of Chavs”, who won £9.7 million in the National Lottery in 2002. Michael, then 19, was unemployed and generally struggling with his life before he won the lottery.</p></br>\r\n<img width="550" src="http://euromillions.com/images/Michael-Charrol.jpg" alt="Michael Charrol - King of Chavs" /></br><p align="justify">\r\nHe immediately purchased four villas in the UK, a holiday retreat in Spain, two convertible BMWs along with two Mercedes, and threw in a couple of quads, bikes and cars to participate in private demolition derbies with. He wore lavishly expensive jewelry and spent, according to sources close to him, many thousands on illegal substances. Most of the money was gone within 18 months. His complete life story can be found in the biography entitled Careful What You Wish For by Sean Boru.</p><p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nThose are two extreme cases which received massive press coverage over the years, but what about all those winners that do not wave their winnings and new acquisitions in front of the public eye? A recent study by the Camelot Group which interviewed more than 30 big winners over the last 10 years will give you an impression of how the “average winner” changes lifestyles and where the money goes. </p><p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<a href="http://euromillions.com">Euromillions.com</a> compiled this study into a handy infographic; not just because we simply love these things, but to prepare you for the moment you want to refer to the best practices of past lottery winners.</p><p>\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nThe following statistics were compiled from 34 lottery winners (8 Male, 26 Female), with an average age of 46 - source Camelot Group PBC</p>\r\n\r\n<img width="550" height="" src="http://euromillions.com/images/inforgraph-lifestyle.jpg" alt="Infographic - Lottery Winner Lifestyles" />', 'Infograph: How Lotteries Change Lives', 'Lottery Wins, life changing, Lottery winner', 'Find out how the lottery has changed the lives of many with our fun infographic!', 2, 1377238738, 2, 'Admin Istrator', 'How Lottery Wins Changes Lives InfoGraph', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1348815242, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (133, 117, 'en', 'twitter_is_glowing_with_euromillions', 'Twitter is Glowing with #EuroMillions', '<p><strong>Last Friday, October 19th 2012, we had a stacked Jackpot with a possible win of 67 Million for five numbers and 2 stars matched.</strong><p>\r\nIt seemed like the whole of Europe played the Euromillions Last week. The Jackpot has not been claimed for the last 6 draws and everybody was hoping to be the lucky winner this time. At <a href="http://euromillions.com">Euromillions.com</a> we saw a massive increase in players again and expect this figure to rise even higher with this week’s Jackpot being a hefty 76 Million Euro. Yes that’s right, 76.000.000 Euro!</p><p>\r\nNew tweets containing the hash tags #Euromillions and #inittowinit, usually only really trafficked Tuesday and Friday afternoons, are constantly popping up every other minute. Europeans share their numbers, hopes and of course „what to do with all that money” once pocketed.</p>\r\n<img src="http://euromillions.com/images/tweets.jpg" alt="Euromillions Tweets " /></p><p>\r\nOnce the results are public each Tuesday and each Friday evening a flood of frustrated tweets could be seen, such as “not one number this time in the E<a href="http://euromillions.com">uro Millions</a>” or “better go to bed and to work tomorrow, not a millionaire yet”. \r\nWe expect to see the same pattern until the Jackpot has been won. We are closing in on a hundred Million  Euro Jackpot. Just a couple of rollovers missing. Good Luck to all our players.</p>', 'Twitter is Glowing with EuroMillions', 'Twitter, Euromillions, Euro Millions', 'The social network sees massive activity increase', 2, 1351692965, 2, 'Admin Istrator', 'Twitter is Glowing', '', NULL, 'Tweets about Euromillions', 'Euromillions on Twitter October 2012', 1350909641, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (134, 118, 'en', 'hackers_attack_french_euromillions_lottery_website', 'Hackers Attack French Euromillions Lottery Website ', '<p align="justify">A group of religious hackers named the “MoroccanGhost” defaced the <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euromillions results page</a> of the French lottery site <a href="http://fdj.fr">FDJ</a> on Sunday morning. The message, appearing in French and Arabic, blocked the FDJ homepage and branded games of chance and alcohol as ”work of the devil”. The full message read:<p>\r\n<p align="justify"\r\n"Oh you believers. Wine, games of chance, statues all augur impurity and are the work of the devil."</p>\r\n<p align="justify"\r\n<p>The group MoroccanGhost consists of "many members, all from Morocco, each with his own personal interest", as described by their 17 year-old spokesperson "King Neco" in a <a href="http://news.softpedia.es/Hackers-del-mundo-King-Neco-de-Moroccan-Ghosts-275990.html">recently published interview</a>, the youngest member of the Islamic collective . The group has been widely considered to be a white hat "hacktivist" bond which attacks official government sites in order to protect "the kingdom of Morocco". </p><p>\r\n<img src="http://www.mooslym.com/images/moroccanghosts.jpg" alt="Euromillions site attack message" />\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nThe message appeared on Sunday morning, before the website was taken down for maintenance. The security leak was identified and fixed with the site going live again on Monday morning. A spokesman of FDJ France confirmed in a statement, that the site is absolutely secure and the game or results are not being compromised. With regards to integrity of sensitive user data, such as names, addresses and credit card numbers no statement has been made yet.</p><p>\r\nThe site of the FDJ seems fully operational. A warning message has been placed on the home page to inform players of the situation. We are facing a 100 Million Euro Jackpot week and invite all players to play the Euromillions on Euromillions.com. The site complies to all the latest security standards and has been providing online lottery services to thousands of <a href="www.euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> players from across the world since 1998.</p>', 'Hackers Attack French Lottery Website ', 'FDJ, Euromillions, euro millions, morrocanghost, hackers', 'Morrocan hackers attack the French Euromillions lottery website and leave messages in French & Arabic branding gambling as work of the devil.', 2, 1375690641, 2, 'Admin Istrator', 'lottery-site-attacked', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>Hackers brand drinking and gambling work of the devil</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1351496735, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (135, 119, 'en', 'euromillions_on_twitter_this_week', 'Euromillions on Twitter this week', '<p>It was a busy week for the Euromillions on Twitter. An incredible amount of people joined the conversation over the hashtags <a href="https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Euromillions&src=typd">#Euromillions</a> an <a href="https://twitter.com/search?q=%23fingerscrossedsrc=typd">#fingerscrossed</a> last week. Some gems from last week below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>@Jordfrance just wants one little thing from Santa Claus this year.</p>\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p>I don''t even want much for Christmas. Just a winning lottery ticket for the euro millions</p>&mdash; Gotenks (@jordfrance) <a href="https://twitter.com/jordfrance/status/260066395532955648" data-datetime="2012-10-21T17:13:55+00:00">October 21, 2012</a></blockquote>\r\n<p> @LewisHesketh is dreaming about Cancun with his mates! </p>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p>If i won the Euro Millions this week.. I would book Cancun and Ibiza for the lads next year! <a href="https://twitter.com/search/%23fingerscrossed">#fingerscrossed</a></p>&mdash; LewisHesketh (@No1Hesketh) <a href="https://twitter.com/No1Hesketh/status/260044532647878656" data-datetime="2012-10-21T15:47:02+00:00">October 21, 2012</a></blockquote>\r\n<p>@concord146 Does not get much credit from her husband </p>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p>bought a <a href="https://twitter.com/search/%23euromillions">#euromillions</a> ticket. Fingers crossed. Asked hubby what he''d do if we won. His response started with ''well I''d still go to work''</p>&mdash; Laura B (@concord146) <a href="https://twitter.com/concord146/status/261902580479844352" data-datetime="2012-10-26T18:50:15+00:00">October 26, 2012</a></blockquote>\r\n<p> @hazeychris is trying to beat the system ;) </p>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p>Just bought 10 tickets for tomorrow''s euro millions <a href="https://twitter.com/search/%23fingerscrossed">#fingerscrossed</a></p>&mdash; christine hazelton (@hazeychris) <a href="https://twitter.com/hazeychris/status/261500776470425600" data-datetime="2012-10-25T16:13:38+00:00">October 25, 2012</a></blockquote>\r\n<p> We think Twitter is a great platform for lottery chatter. Come and join the conversation, follow: <a href="https://twitter.com/_lotteries">@_lotteries</a> on Twitter and shatre your dreams with us!', 'Euromillions on Twitter this week', 'Euromillions, Twitter', 'Weekly break down of #Euromillions on Twitter', 2, 1351504345, 2, 'Admin Istrator', 'Euromillions-Twitter-1012', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1351504345, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (136, 120, 'en', 'its_friday_its_euromillions_day', 'It''s Friday, it''s Euromillions day! ', '<p>The Tuesday draw featured a spectacular Jackpot of 101.000.000 € and we were sure we are going to see a lucky winner scooping the lump sum. A lot of people came close! Six people came really close by drawing the correct 5 numbers and one star. They each still receive a 280.000 € in the second prize level. In total the Euromillion paid out 2.5 Million winners across all prize catagories for a total payout of</p>\r\n<p></br>\r\nCongratulations to all the winners and good luck for the next draw to all the onmes who barely missed their chance that time.</>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Excitement is building up for the <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results?show=1">Euro Millions draw tonight</a>.  119 Million € in th3e Jackpot and nobody wants to miss it. Follow the hashtags #Euromillions, #FingersCrossed, #inittowinit to be part of the conversation.</p>\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p>£95,000,000 jackpot for <a href="https://twitter.com/search/%23Euromillions">#Euromillions</a> tonight. I don''t need all of it, just a slice. Please.</p>&mdash; Ben Peyton (@MrBenPeyton) <a href="https://twitter.com/MrBenPeyton/status/264280967437488128" data-datetime="2012-11-02T08:21:07+00:00">November 2, 2012</a></blockquote>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p>Must do <a href="https://twitter.com/search/%23euromillions">#euromillions</a> tonight, I''m feeling lucky lol.</p>&mdash; Neil Carter(@Neil_Carter) <a href="https://twitter.com/Neil_Carter/status/264288057933590529" data-datetime="2012-11-02T08:49:17+00:00">November 2, 2012</a></blockquote>\r\n\r\n<a class="twitter-timeline"  href="https://twitter.com/_lotteries" data-widget-id="264297641616220160">Tweets by @_lotteries</a>\r\n<script>!function(d,s,id){var js,fjs=d.getElementsByTagName(s)[0];if(!d.getElementById(id)){js=d.createElement(s);js.id=id;js.src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js";fjs.parentNode.insertBefore(js,fjs);}}(document,"script","twitter-wjs");</script>\r\n<p> Follow us on <a href="https://twitter.com/_lotteries">Euromillions Twitter</a>:', 'It''s Friday, it''s Euromillions day! ', 'Euromillions Friday, Euromillions Twitter', 'Euromillions Friday draw excitement is building up. 119.000.000 Euro Jackpot.', 2, 1351845256, 2, 'Admin Istrator', 'Euromillions-Friday', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1351845224, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (137, 121, 'en', 'increase_your_chances', 'Increase your Chances', '<p>The draw on Friday, the 2nd of November 2012 saw millions of savvy lottery players putting their hopes on claiming the unbelievable Jackpot that reached 119 Million Euro. Unfortunately no player matched the five correct numbers and the two complementary stars that are required to claim the prize.  12 players matched five stars and one number and are free to claim 226.000 Euro each. 15 players matched the five numbers and won 55.000 Euro each.</p><p>\r\n\r\nWe are facing a <a href="http://play.euromillions.com/en/">monster of a Jackpot</a> of 132.000.000 Euro, yes, you read correctly: one-hundred-thirty-two-million Euro, one of the biggest lottery jackpots ever. We hope one of our players can call himself a 132x Millionaire on Tuesday night.  So, we want to help by giving some basic advises on how to play the Euromillions with the highest chance of winning the full Jackpot.</p><p>\r\n\r\nWe like to clarify before:  there is no way to trick the system or predict numbers from historic data.<strong> Each number has the same chance on being drawn at any given time</strong>. The Euromillion s lottery machines are certified and continuously checked to maintain the integrity of the game. You can however increase your chances of not needing to share a win.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1.	Avoid birth dates or street numbers</h3>\r\n<P>Did you know the most bet on numbers are 1 – 12 ? This is because most people do play their birthdays or their family members birthday. The number of the month will always be between one and twelve, here and streets always have a number one, but fewer a number 50.</P>\r\n\r\n<h3>2.	Avoid number sequences</h3>\r\n<P>There is absolutely no relation between one lottery ball and the other, but statistically it is more unlikely that for example 5 numbers are drawn which are in order, like 44,45,46,47,48 or follow an algorithm,  such as  2,4,8,16,32 or  1,3,5,7,11. Your best chance is to bid random.</P>\r\n<h3>3.	Fortune Cookies</h3>\r\n<P>Chinese fortune cookies often contain “winning” lottery numbers. Please keep in mind, that those numbers are not unique to your cookie, but are probably printed in thousands. Do you want to share your Jackpot with all those other Chinese food lovers out there?</P>\r\n\r\n<h3>4.	The tale of hot and cold numbers</h3>\r\n<P>The chances of a particular number to show up are equal in every draw. Regardless of prior draws. If a number was drawn 10 times in a row, it still has the same chance to come up within the next draw, the same as any other number.</P>\r\n<h3>5.	Buy a Euromillions Ticket</h3>\r\n<P>If you do not <a href="http://euromillions.com">buy a Euromillions ticket</a>, your chances are effectively 0. Buying at least one ticket will not only give you a shot at the big win, but do good in the world. Remember lottery organizations are actively supporting charities  and are nonprofit organizations.</P>\r\n\r\n<h3>Happy Betting!</h3>', 'Increase your Chances in winning the Euromillions', 'Euromillions Chances, Euro Millions chances', 'Increase your Chances in winning the Euromillions by following some basic tips', 2, 1375683233, 2, 'Admin Istrator', 'increase your chances', 'http://albertribera.files.wordpress.com/2008/08/good-luck-clover-21.jpg', NULL, 'Increase your chances of winning', NULL, 1352111321, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (138, 122, 'en', 'euromillions_hopes_are_high_on_twitter', 'Euromillions Hopes are High on Twitter', '<p>Millions of European lottery players are trying for the 132 Million Jackpot - equivalent to three tons of gold - this Tuesday in the Euromillions draw. The Jackpot rolled over 10 times to reach this sum and is the fourth Jackpot to pass the 100 Million mark this year.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nSince the launch of the Euro Millions in 2004, 92 lucky players have won or shared a Jackpot of 100 Million or more. The latest being a Spanish player who pocketed 100 Million Euro in September this year. Who will be the next one to win such a fortune, European Twitter accounts are full of hope this morning:</p>\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p>Everyday has the potential to be the best day of your life... Hopefully today will be mine <a href="https://twitter.com/search/%23euromillions">#euromillions</a></p>&mdash; Scott Kay (@scottkay15) <a href="https://twitter.com/scottkay15/status/265714491826774016" data-datetime="2012-11-06T07:17:26+00:00">November 6, 2012</a></blockquote>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p>Back at it....keen for a <a href="https://twitter.com/search/%23EuroMillions">#EuroMillions</a> win tonite : )</p>&mdash; Peter WJP Henry (@PeeHen) <a href="https://twitter.com/PeeHen/status/265734147388100608" data-datetime="2012-11-06T08:35:32+00:00">November 6, 2012</a></blockquote>\r\n<p>It seems the first thing to do, when winning the Euromillions is quitting the job:\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p>I must win the <a href="https://twitter.com/search/%23euromillions">#euromillions</a> jackpot tonight! ... This life of slavery and servitude is not for me lol</p>&mdash; Barry (@Bazboi82) <a href="https://twitter.com/Bazboi82/status/265734627656859648" data-datetime="2012-11-06T08:37:27+00:00">November 6, 2012</a></blockquote>\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p>RT @<a href="https://twitter.com/jayce12">jayce12</a>: Think work should be banned!! Seriously need to win this Euro Millions tonight!!</p>&mdash; Elizabeth Thompson (@Elizabeth_Rocks) <a href="https://twitter.com/Elizabeth_Rocks/status/265733149194088448" data-datetime="2012-11-06T08:31:34+00:00">November 6, 2012</a></blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p> Good luck to all of the players. <a href="https://twitter.com/_lotteries">Follow Euromillions on Twitter</a>', 'Hopes are high on Twitter', 'Euromillions Twitter', 'Europeans embrace Twitter to post their hopes on winning the Euromillions', 2, 1352187953, 2, 'Admin Istrator', 'Hopes-are-high', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1352187953, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (139, 123, 'en', 'russian_players_of_the_euromillions', 'Russian players of the Euromillions', '<p>Russian lottery players love the Euromillions. Unfortunately Russia is not participating in the draw, so buying official tickets for the Euro Millions in lottery stores can be a lot of hassle for Russian players and mostly it proves to be an impossible task.  </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Can you play the Euromillions from Russia? </h3><p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Yes, You can! </strong>\r\nOn Euromillions.com you can <a href="http://euromillions.com">play the Euromillions</a> from anywhere in the world. You can buy tickets, get automatic notifications of the results. Prizes are added to your account balance and can be withdrawn from any location in Russia or in the world. And you will be in good company! Did you know, that russian lottery players make up over 10% of our player base on Euromillions.com?</p>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://euromillions.com/play"><img width="570" height="" src="http://euromillions.com/images/mainbanner_en.jpg" alt="Play Euromillions" /></a>\r\n\r\n<h3>How can you play Euro Millions from Russia?</h3><p>\r\n\r\nEuromillions.com works as a messenger service on  your behalf. The ticket virtually played by you will be physically purchased, printed and archived on your behalf. In case of a win your account will receive the amount as part of your account balance. You can then withdraw it using your preferred method of payment.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Can anybody from Russia participate in a Euro Millions draw?</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nIn general: Yes, anybody, regardless of location! If you are over 18 years of age and can provide a valid proof of identity, you can play the Euromillions on Euromillions.com . The Euro Millions Tickets are the same prize for you as for any other European. On Euromillions.com, we are proud to be able to offer the cheapest tickets available online. In case of special enquiries or syndicate requests you can always ask us on <a href="http://twitter.com/_lotteries">Twitter</a> or send us an Email at support(AT)euromillions.com</p>', 'Euromillions in Russia', 'Euromillions Russia', 'How to play the Euromillions online from Russia or any other non participating country.', 2, 1352298412, 2, 'Admin Istrator', 'Russia-Euromillions', '', NULL, 'Euromillions Tickets', 'Euromillions tickets and a pen', 1352297869, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (140, 124, 'en', 'euromillions_jackpot_rolls_over_again', 'Euromillions Jackpot Rolls Over Again', '<p align="justify">The Euromillions featured one of its biggest Jackpots ever in last week’s Friday draw. Millions of Euromillions players from all European countries put their hopes high for Friday’s draw. We even saw a record number of players from countries which are not participating in the Euro Millions purchasing tickets in hope for the big win. Lottery players from countries like <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/285/Euromillions-in-Russia">Russia</a>, Romania, Germany and from all over the world were hoping for their share of the big Jackpot.</p>\r\n<p align="justify"> The jackpot, which rolled over 11 times before, was stacked with 152 Million € up for grabs and was waiting for a lucky winner more than five weeks already. It will have to wait longer. Nine players were able to match five numbers and one star each, but missed the second star. They secured a respectable 336,582 € each. A total of fourteen players matched the five correct numbers, but missed both stars and scooped 72,125 € each.</p>\r\n<p align="justify"><a href="http://euromillions.com">The Euromillions Jackpot</a> will feature mind blowing 164 Million € on Tuesday, 13th November 2012 and is waiting to change lifes of the lucky winners.</p> \r\n<h3>How big can the Euromillions Jackpot get?</h3>\r\n<p align="justify">The Jackpot will continue to roll over until a maximum of 190 Million € has been reached. If by then no one bet on the right numbers and stars, it will rollover only once more before the Jackpot will be passed over to the lower tiers the next draw. Theoretically, five numbers and one star can make you a millionaire then.</p>\r\n<p align="justify"> For the latest <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euromillions results</a> and a weekly chance to win free tickets: <a href="https://twitter.com/_lotteries">follow @_lotteries on Twitter</a></p><p align="centre">\r\n<img src="https://pbs.twimg.com/media/A7K5qlZCYAIWONM.jpg:large" width="570" alt="Euromillions on Twitter" />', 'Euromillions Jackpot Rolls Over Again', 'Euromillions Rollover', 'The Euromillions Jackpot rolls over to 164 Million Euros ', 2, 1377246196, 2, 'Admin Istrator', 'Euromillions Jackpot Rolls Over Again', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1352712861, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (141, 125, 'en', 'euromillions_hot_topic_on_twitter', 'Euromillions: Hot Topic On Twitter', '<p align="justify">A 121 Million Jackpot was more than enough to get the conversation going last week. Thousands of tweets containing the hash tag #Euromillions were sent. One of our tweets got mentioned nearly 400 times and re-tweeted by avid <a href="http://euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> players worldwide.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p>Retweet and Follow @<a href="https://twitter.com/_lotteries">_lotteries</a> to win 5 <a href="https://twitter.com/search/%23Euromillions">#Euromillions</a> Tickets. Jackpot:152 Million € / £121 Million. <a href="https://twitter.com/search/%23Freebies">#Freebies</a> <a href="http://t.co/ghU5swC6" title="http://twitter.com/_lotteries/status/266479469202661376/photo/1">twitter.com/_lotteries/sta…</a></p>&mdash; Euromillions (@_lotteries) <a href="https://twitter.com/_lotteries/status/266479469202661376" data-datetime="2012-11-08T09:57:11+00:00">November 8, 2012</a></blockquote>\r\n<script src="//platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" width="620" charset="utf-8"></script>\r\n<embed tweet>\r\n<p align="justify">The number of tweets kept increasing to a record high on Friday afternoon, with countless people expressing their hopes for the big win.</p>\r\n<img src="http://25.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_mddiue7QyQ1rv9cuqo1_1280.jpg" alt="Euromillions Trend Graph" width="620" /><p align="justify">\r\nOn Saturday we saw another peak in mentions, once people checked their results.</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nAt Euromillions.com we expect more and more people to join the conversation, as the Jackpot keeps rolling over to 168.000.000 € for Tuesday, 13th November 2012.</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n<a href="https://twitter.com/_lotteries">Follow us on Twitter</a></h3>', 'Euromillions: Hot Topic On Twitter', 'Euromillions on Twitter, Follow Euromillions', 'Euromillions is a hot topic on Twitter at the moment.', 2, 1377245648, 2, 'Admin Istrator', 'Euromillions: Hot Topic On Twitter', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1352718483, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (142, 126, 'en', 'mega_euromillions_jackpot_goes_to_french_winner', 'Mega Euromillions Jackpot goes to French winner', '<p align="justify">The weeks passed and nobody seemed to be able to bet on the right numbers. The Jackpot kept rolling and rolling until it reached approximately 169.000.000 € this Tuesday. Shortly after 10 pm yesterday it was clear – <strong>We have a winner!</strong></p><p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nOne lucky French individual scoops it all. The identity remains unknown yet, but the winning tickets was sold in the French-Alps region in Southern France. Besides the outrageous amount that he will receive in Paris from the official French Lottery organizer FDJ, the winner will be treated to a ride in a limousine to Paris, a free dinner and an overnight stay in one of the Paris Palace hotels. The bills will be paid by the French Lottery.</p><p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nThe French news picked up on the story this morning and congratulate the winner. The <a href="http://euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> winner will be the 226th richest person in France. Not a bad return on his two Euro investment. Well played! The winner has 60 days to claim his win before receiving the check in private and off camera.</p><p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nThis win of EUR 169 837 010 is the third largest amount won, since the Euromillions started in 2004. Two UK winner scooped a little more with 190 000 000 on 10th August 2012 and 180 million Euro on 12th July 2011.\r\nIn eight years, more than 260 European winners, including 72 French, 58 Spanish and 57 British players have won the pot which is at least a guaranteed 15 Million for every draw.</p>', 'Mega Euromillions Jackpot goes to French winner', 'Euromillions winner, Millionaire', 'French lottery player wins 169 Million Euro on Euromillions Tuesday draw 13th November 2012', 2, 1377244348, 2, 'Admin Istrator', 'Mega Euromillions Jackpot goes to French winner', NULL, '<p align="justify">€169,000,000 Euromillions jackpot goes to French winner.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1352892629, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (143, 127, 'de', 'franzoesischer_euromillions_spieler_gewinnt_169_millionen_jackpot', 'Französischer Euromillions Spieler gewinnt 169 Millionen Jackpot', '<p>Der Euromillions Jackpot ist in den vergangenen Wochen bis zu einem unglaublichen Betrag von 169.000.000 Euro angestiegen. Am Dienstag dieser Woche wurde der Jackpot endlich geknackt. Ein besonders glücklicher französischer Lottospieler hat auf die richtigen fünf Zahlen und zwei Extra Sterne gesetzt und kann den Betrag bald sein Eigen nennen. Der Gewinne rist noch nicht namentlich bekannt.</p>\r\n<p>\r\nDas Gewinnticket mit den Zahlen 11-16-21-24-29 und den Zusatzzahlen 2  und 6 wurde in der Region französische Alpen erstanden, soviel ist sicher. Der Gewinner hat nun 60 Tage Zeit den Gewinnschein in Paris der Staatslottery Frankreich, FDJ, vorzulegen und den Gewinn einzulösen. </p><p>\r\nSollte sich der Neu-Millionär in den nächsten Tagen melden, stehen Ihm einige interessante Serviceleistungen zur Verfügung. Ihm wird eine Limosine gestellt, die Ihn nach Paris zum Hauptsitz der Euromillionen chauffiert. Vor Ort wird er auf Kosten der Lotterieorganisation in einem der Fünf-Sterne Paläste Paris’ nächtigen und kann sich auf ein Abendessen in einem Sternerestaurant freuen. Die Gewinnsumme wird unter Ausschluss der Öffentlichkeit in Form eines Checks an Ihn oder Sie überreicht.</p>', 'Französischer Euromillions Spieler gewinnt 169 Millionen Jackpot', 'Euromillionen, Euromillions Jackpot Gewinn', '169 Millionen Euro gehen an einen französischen Lottospieler. Er hat auf die richtigen Zahlen gesetzt', 1, 1352991003, 2, 'Admin Istrator', 'Spieler gewinnt 169 Millionen Jackpot', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1352991003, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (144, 128, 'es', 'super_bote_ganado_por_un_frances', 'Super Bote Ganado por un Francés ', '<p>Las semanas pasaron y nadie tuvo la suerte de ganar el gran premio de Euromillones. El bote ha crecido hasta llegar a los 169 millones de euros este martes, pero el 13 de noviembre a las 23:00 UTC +1, estaba claro - <strong>POR FIN, HABIA UN GANADOR!</strong></p>\r\n<p>El afortunado es un francés, y se lo lleva todo! Todavía la identidad del ganador queda en un misterio, pero sabemos que la apuesta ha sido comprada en los Alpes, en la región de Haute-Savoie. A parte de la suma gigante que recibirá en Paris de la Organización de las loterías Francesas, nombrado FDJ, al ganador se le ofrece una cena en uno de los mejores restaurantes de la capital francesa y pasará la noche en un  Palacio!</p><p>\r\nEl día siguiente del sorteo de Euromillones, el ganador ha sido felicitado por toda Europa. Será la 226ta persona más rica de Francia. Ganar 169 millones de euros por haber invertido 2,00€ es un buen negocio! \r\nEl afortunado tiene 60 días para reclamar sus ganancias, supuestamente, la transacción se hará en Paris con total discreción.</p><p>\r\nLos 169.000.000 € es el tercer bote mas grande nunca ganado desde la creación de Euromillones en 2004. Dos británicos llevaron unos 190.000.000 € el 10 de agosto de 2012 y 180.000.000 € el 12 de Julio de 2011. \r\nEn ocho años el Euromillion ha tenido 260 ganadores europeos que han ganado cada uno un bote superior a 15 millones de euros. En el podium, 72 franceses, 58 españoles y 57 ingleses.</p>', 'Super Bote Ganado por un Francés ', 'Premio Euromillones, Ganador', 'Jugador Francés gana 169 millones de Euros en el sorteo Euromillones martes 13 de noviembre. ', 2, 1353397345, 2, 'Admin Istrator', 'Super Bote Ganado por un Francés ', NULL, '<p>Las semanas pasaron y nadie tuvo la suerte de ganar el gran premio de Euromillones. El bote ha crecido hasta llegar a los 169 millones de euros este martes.</p>', NULL, NULL, 1353397073, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (145, 129, 'en', 'belgium_does_it_again', 'Belgium does it again', '<p align="justify">The Belgium National Lottery confirmed a Belgian player won the <a href="http://euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> jackpot. He bet on the correct five numbers and two lucky stars: 28-30-42-45-49 5 + 10 to win 22 Million Euros. Last week a French player pocketed 169 million Euros, which caused a Jackpot reset, the 22 million is still an impressive amount and will be the highest Jackpot won this week in Europe. The Eurojackpot will feature a 14 Million this Saturday, the national lotteries all feature smaller Jackpots below 10 million Euro.</p><p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nThese 22.7 million Euro are the second biggest win in Belgium this year, after the 79 million won in  June. The largest amount for a EuroMillions ticket validated in Belgium is 100 million won in February 2007. </p><p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nAnother Belgian player secured a win at rank 2 and leaves with 1.2 million for putting down five numbers and one star correctly. The Jackpot will consequently reset to 15 million € for the Friday draw of Euromillions. </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n</br>\r\n<p>Watch a video of the Euromillions Tuesday draw:</p>\r\n</br>\r\n\r\n<object id="flashObj" width="565" height="316" classid="clsid:D27CDB6E-AE6D-11cf-96B8-444553540000" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=9,0,47,0"><param name="movie" value="http://c.brightcove.com/services/viewer/federated_f9?isVid=1&isUI=1" /><param name="bgcolor" value="#FFFFFF" /><param name="flashVars" value="videoId=1980435933001&linkBaseURL=http%3A%2F%2Fnl-video.national-lottery.co.uk%2Fvideos%2Fview%2Ftuesday-euromillions-draw&playerID=796512125001&playerKey=AQ~~,AAAAuPCt6kE~,1959EwdtDB5zbir3IXaK5NNqj2Qti4NE&domain=embed&dynamicStreaming=true" /><param name="base" value="http://admin.brightcove.com" /><param name="seamlesstabbing" value="false" /><param name="al