INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (178, 156, 'en', 'what_do_lottery_winners_spend_their_money_on', 'What do lottery winners spend their money on?', '<img src="http://cdn.theweek.co.uk/sites/theweek/files/styles/theweek_gallery_main_image/public/2_dorset_-_emporio.jpg" width="280" height="180" align="left" alt="Millionaire property" />\r\n<p align="justify">The million  dollar question is, <strong>what do lottery winners spend their newly won  cash on</strong>? Since the beginning of the UK National Lottery in 1994,  over three thousand people have been made millionaires and many  different ways of spending their fortune has emerged. Curious cases  include undergoing <strong>plastic surgery, toy collecting, investing in  farmland and farm animals, and buying a gold Reliant Robin  three-wheeler</strong>, amongst others. Many have frittered away their  lottery winnings whilst others have generously spent it on loved ones  or donated a large portion to charity. Despite the variation in  spending habits there are a certain few things that have proven  popular amongst all the newly-made millionaires as demonstrated  below: </p>\r\n<p LANG="en-US" ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><strong>Total  winnings: </strong>Over<strong> </strong>8.5  billion</p>\r\n<p LANG="en-US" ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><strong>Property</strong> -  Many commonly spent a large portion of their winnings on property.  82% moved home corresponding to  8,000 new places purchased in the  UK. Sold for an average £900,000, these flash new pads accounted for  a whopping £3.3 billion. <img src="http://platea.pntic.mec.es/~mmotta/web10cdl/audirojo.jpg" width="280" height="180" align="right"  alt="Audi" /> They were also furnished with top luxury  items such as hot tubs, electric gates, walk-in-wardrobes and games  room with 30% of lottery winners employing maintenance staff. <BR>\r\n</p>\r\n<p LANG="en-US" ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><strong>Investing</strong> – As can be expected many invested some of their lottery money for  the future. Corresponding to £2.2 billion it comprises the second  most popular expenditure choice. A further £1.16 billion was spent  on future investments for their children and £1.7 billion accounted  for lottery money used to purchase gifts for friends and family. </p>\r\n<p LANG="en-US" ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><strong>Businesses  - </strong>15% of lottery millionaires invested their winnings in a new  business and 9% assisted others in setting up their own business. In  addition, although fortunate winners hit it big (average 2.8 million  win), 19% continued to work or carried out unpaid voluntary work  whilst 59%, understandably, gave up work.</p>\r\n<img src="http://www.caribbeanescapesrealty.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/Caribbean-beach2-1024x809.jpg" width="280" height="180" align="left" alt="Caribbean" />\r\n<p LANG="en-US" ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><strong>Cars</strong> – New cars accounted for over £460 million of lottery winner  expenditures. An <strong>Audi, Range Rover and BMW </strong>featured amongst  the most popular brands. <strong>Mercedes and Land Rovers</strong> were also  popular choices with the average car purchased costing around £46,000  and the number of luxury vehicles bought reaching approximately  £17,000. You do the maths! </p>\r\n<p LANG="en-US" ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><strong>Holidays</strong> – Finally, naturally many spent some of their winnings on a luxury  holiday away. The <strong>USA, Caribbean, Dubai and Canary Islands</strong> feature amongst the most popular destinations. 5-star hotels  comprised the major expenditures for 68% of winners whilst 10%  invested in a caravan generating a whopping £7.4 million in UK  caravan sales. The total amount of lottery winnings spent on luxury  cars and holidays corresponded to £0.68 billion. <BR>\r\n</p>\r\n<p LANG="en-US" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">So, if you  won the <a href="www.euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> what would you spend the money on? </p>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'What do lottery winners spend their money on?', 'lottery, winners, spend, winnings', 'Find out how newly-made millionaires have spent their lottery winnings over the years!', 2, 1374732119, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'lottery, winnings, spent', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>How lottery winners have spent their millions.</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1366875561, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (179, 157, 'en', 'euromillions_numbers_for_friday_the_26th_of_april_2013', 'Euromillions numbers for Friday the 26th of April 2013', '<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Last Friday was a good  day for many as one lucky millionaire raffle player scooped the  coveted <strong>32 million euro grand prize (£27.33 million) </strong>whilst  others bagged a generous cash sum in the lower tiers.  Congratulations! This means that this <strong>Tuesday, 15 million euro  (£12,000,000) </strong>is up for grabs so <a href=http://play.euromillions.com/en/ rel="nofollow">play Euromillions now</a>, because you never know, luck could be on your  side! In the meantime, here are the <strong>winning Euromillions numbers  for Friday the 26</strong><strong>th</strong><strong> of April 2013</strong>. </p><p align="center">\r\n  <span class="greenball">11</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">16</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">24</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">38</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">40</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">2</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">5</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nFor futher information on the <strong>winning Euromillions results and corresponding prizes</strong> consult the <A HREF="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euromillions  prize breakdown</A>. In addition, find out the many <A HREF="http://euromillions.com/news-article/332/9-advantages-of-playing-euromillions-online">advantages of playing with Euromillions.com</A>. Finally, don''t forget to take  part in our <strong>weekly twitter contest </strong>where we give away free  Euromillions tickets to followers every Friday!\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n</p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><strong>Watch Friday''s Euromillions draw:</strong><BR>\r\n</p>\r\n<iframe width="580" height="320" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/WB4pN1mJH58?feature=player_detailpage" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/p