INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (180, 158, 'en', 'euromillions_lottery_winners_and_good_causes', 'Euromillions Lottery Winners and Good Causes ', '<img src="http://www.gamblingkingz.com/img/euromillions-claimed-356.jpg"  width="320" height="210" align="left" alt="Euromillions.com" />\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nEvery time you <a href=http://play.euromillions.com/en/ rel="nofollow">buy a Euromillions lottery ticket</a>, not only do you get the chance to win a huge amount of cash but, you are also helping to change lives. All the millions of unclaimed prizes or money generated from unscooped jackpots are promptly donated to good causes and distributed accordingly to make things better for many across the country. In addition, although your typical newly-made <A HREF="http://euromillions.com/news-article/335/what-do-lottery-winners-spend-their-money-on"> millionaire spends their money on</A>  a new house, cars, holidays and launching a new business, amongst others, there are a rare few who give a little of their large fortune to make the world a much better place. <br></br>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>Unclaimed Euromillions Jackpot Prizes</strong><br></br>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nThe largest <a href="www.euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> jackpot to go unclaimed amounted to a whopping £63.8 million pounds. Whilst it was a huge shame for the unknowing winner, the money has been put to good use by being donated to the <strong>UK National Lottery Good Causes</strong>. \r\n<img src="https://si0.twimg.com/profile_images/3120117173/5d938c6078a3193aa6b63c9117a34b3e.png" align="right" width="250" height="210" alt="Big Lottery Fund" />\r\nAlthough Euromillions can be played by millionaire raffle hopefuls across the world, UK good causes was the lucky recipient because the unclaimed ticket was purchased in the UK. With an 80-day deadline lottery players are letting huge amounts of money slip through their fingers!<br></br>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nFrom 2011 to 2012 alone, a massive £105 million in prize money went unclaimed, only adding to the already substantial sum of over £30 million generated from National Lottery ticket sales per week, whilst the total amount of money donated to Good Causes corresponded to £1.8 billion. All thanks to you! In addition, since the launch of the UK National Lottery, <strong>figures show that more than £1.4 billion, an average £75 million a year, has gone unclaimed</strong> with a total of more than £29 billion going to Good Causes. The money has been contributed to improve health, education and the environment, as well as sports and art. Funds have also been donated to charities and UK heritage thus benefiting more than 400,000 projects across Britain to date. Further information on how your money has helped is available on the <A HREF="http://www.biglotteryfund.org.uk/" rel="nofollow"> Big Lottery Fund</A> website. <br></br>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>Good Deeds by Euromillions Jackpot Winners</strong><br></br>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<img src="http://img.thesun.co.uk/multimedia/archive/01346/Colin_and_Chris_We_1346061a.jpg" width="300" height="200" align="left"  alt="Chris and Colin Weir" />\r\n<strong>Chris and Colin Weir</strong> -This fortunate couple scooped the biggest Euromillions jackpot in the history of the UK with a whopping £161 million win. We know lottery winners <A HREF="http://euromillions.com/news-article/207/life-lottery-winners-chris-colin-weir"> Colin and Chris Weir</A>  have a big account however, they are now proving they have a big heart with their recent donation to various good causes and decision to give £5 million to set up the “Weir Charitable Trust”.  Hats off to them!!<br></br>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>Dave and Angie Daws</strong> - This fortunate couple was the lucky winner of a whopping £101 million, the third largest jackpot prize in British history. Proving generous as well, they have their sights set on donating money to children''s charities and have promised to make 20 of their close friends and family millionaires. <br></br>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Euromillions Lottery Winners and Good Causes ', 'euromillions, lottery, winners, good, causes', 'Discover where your money goes when you play Euromillions and how it changes lives for the better!', 2, 1374732219, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'lottery, winners, charity', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>Where your Euromillions ticket money goes and how it changes lives</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1367310343, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
