INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (183, 161, 'en', 'top_5_biggest_uk_euromillions_jackpot_winners', 'Top 5 Biggest UK Euromillions Jackpot Winners', '<img src="http://i4.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article99698.ece/ALTERNATES/s615/colin-and-chris-weir-pic-pa-882880778.jpg" width="300" height="200" align="left"alt="Chris and Colin Weir" />\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nSince the launch of the <a href="www.euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> international lottery in 2004, the lives of many across the world have been changed for ever. At least one UK millionaire raffle player has won a guaranteed £1 million every week since 2009 and superdraws, as a result of <strong>Euromillions rollovers</strong>, have produced several notable wins immediately catapulting the fortunate lottery hopefuls into the National Lottery rich list and earning them a place amongst the country''s wealthiest. The years 2011 and 2012 in particular saw the <strong>largest lottery prizes ever paid out in the UK</strong> with the following lottery players featuring amongst the <strong>Top 5 Biggest UK Euromillions Jackpot Winners</strong>.<p></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>Chris and Colin Weir - 161,653,000 (€185,000,000)</strong><p></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nOn the 12th of August 2011,<A HREF="http://euromillions.com/news-article/207/life-lottery-winners-chris-colin-weir">Chris and Colin Weir</A> , from Lars in north Ayrshire, became not only the <strong>UK''s but also Europe''s biggest lottery winners</strong>. Twelve rollovers failed to produce a winner thus by the 13th week the prize had reached the <A HREF="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-rules">Euromillions Jackpot Pool Cap</A> corresponding to <strong>€185,000,000</strong>. Following a further rollover after the 13th week''s Euromillions draw saw no first prize winner, a UK winner was finally found bagging themselves the <strong>largest sterling jackpot in the history of the Euromillions lottery</strong>. <img src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-YxRNFMoNT3I/UCzHAo_OmOI/AAAAAAAAEvA/v_DHj5pf0mQ/s1600/adrian-gillian-bayford_560x280.jpg" width="320" height="180" align="right" alt="Gillian and Adrian Bayford" /> Occupying 1st place on the UK National Lottery rich list, this fortunate couple now features amongst the country''s wealthiest.<p></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>Gillian and Adrian Bayford - £148.656,000 (€190,000,000)</strong><p></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n\r\nThe Friday draw held on the 10th of August 2012 produced the country''s second largest win. <A HREF="http://euromillions.com/news-article/306/Statistics-2012-Euromillions">Gillian and Adrian Bayford</A> from Haverhill in Suffolk scooped  <strong>£148.656,000 (€190,000,000)</strong>, slightly less than Chris and Colin Weir due to the difference in the exchange rate. It comprised the seventh Euromillions jackpot to be won  in 2012 following a remarkable year of luck for millionaire raffle hopefuls in the UK. <p></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>Anonymous - £113,019,926 (€129,818,431)</strong><p></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nOn the 8th of October 2010 a lucky millionaire raffle player scooped <strong>£113,019,926 (€129,818,431)</strong> in prize money however, the fortunate Euromillions winner preferred to keep their identity secret.<p></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>Dave and Angela Daws - £101, 203,600 (€117,705,979)</strong><p></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<img src="http://www.cambridge-news.co.uk/imagelibrary/Client%20Images/Client00004/ResizeCache/00162000/00162287%20-%20440x260.jpg" width="320" height="200" align="left" alt="Dave and Angela Daws" />\r\nOn the 7th of October 2011 the lives of <A HREF="http://euromillions.com/latest-euromillionaires-speak-publicly">Dave and Angela Daws</A> changed forever following their huge lottery win. Despite being only the 3rd time they had ever played Euromillions, this fortunate couple from Wisbech, Cambridgeshire scooped a whopping <strong>£101, 203,600 (€117,705,979)</strong> jackpot making them the fourth biggest prize winners in the UK. <p></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>Anonymous - £84,451,321 (€100,037,101)</strong><p></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nFinally, the 5th largest Euromillions prize winner, who wished to remain anonymous, bagged a respectable <strong>£84,451,321 (€100,037,101)</strong> on the 14th of May 2010. We''re not jealous at all......<p></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nSo, if you would like the chance to win some serious money then <a href=http://play.euromillions.com/en/ rel="nofollow">play Euromillions</a>  because remember, you have to be in it to win it. <strong>Good luck!</strong> \r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Top 5 Biggest UK Euromillions Jackpot Winners', '5, top, biggest, winners, lottery, euromillions, uk', 'Discover the 5 biggest Euromillions winners in the UK and how much lovely money they won!', 2, 1374732351, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'top-5-euromillions-winners', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>The top 5 largest lottery prizes paid out in the UK</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1367915715, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
