INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (186, 164, 'en', 'uk_players_overseas_blocked_from_playing_uk_lottery', 'UK players overseas blocked from playing UK lottery', '<img src="http://onlinecasinoinuk.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/Lottery-Ad-Banned.jpg" width="280" height="120" align="left" alt="Overseas players banned" />\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Back in 2009, <strong>UK National Lottery operator Camelot</strong> did away with UK players'' privilege of playing the lottery when on holiday overseas. The  gaming rules stipulated that all UK players must physically be in Britain or the Isle of Man to purchase a valid ticket. “<i>If you are not physically in the UK or Isle of Man you are prohibited from playing National Lottery Games</i>”. (UK National Lottery Help) The move came after research showed that <strong>many countries prohibited the purchase of foreign lottery tickets</strong>, leading operator Camelot to introduce the ban. The website showed a warning message asking players to confirm that they are inside the UK or Isle of Man before they could continue. In addition, several emails were reportedly sent to online players every year explaining the situation and stipulating that tickets purchased abroad are invalid due to individual national laws.\r\nHowever, the National Lottery operator was criticised for allowing tickets to be purchased abroad even though players would not be entitled to claim any winnings thus, <strong>sparking controversy over the unclear rules of the game</strong>. <img src="http://www.tirage-euromillions.net/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/euromillions-espagne-grille-jeu.jpg" width="230" height="210" align="right" alt="Euromillions tickets" />\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">\r\nIn addition, when questioned Camelot was unable to provide a concrete list of countries that ban playing foreign lotteries due to constantly changing laws thus, leaving players responsible for finding out whether their purchased ticket was valid or not. </p>\r\n\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">\r\nThe aforementioned ban also applied to Euromillions. Despite being a transnational lottery, UK residents currently <strong>may not purchase a Euromillions ticket from overseas on the Camelot-run website</strong>, which Chris Jones from Whitley Bay, Tyne found out when he <a href=http://play.euromillions.com/en/ rel="nofollow">played Euromillions online</a> whilst on holiday in Majorca in 2009.</p>\r\n\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">\r\nUnaware of the new UK National Lottery overseas gaming rules, he purchased his weekly <a href="www.euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> lottery tickets as usual. He later received a congratulatory email from Camelot informing him of his £5,148 win and was asked to phone them. On discovering that he had purchased his winning Euromillions ticket in Spain they refused to hand over his prize stating that participating in foreign lottery draws is illegal under Spanish law. \r\n<img src="http://i.telegraph.co.uk/multimedia/archive/01959/majorca_1959083c.jpg" width="250" height="180" align="left" alt="Majorca" />\r\nWhile he attempted to settle the matter, he purchased further Euro million tickets in Spain where he won £96.  The money was automatically paid into his account without any further problems. Mr Jones claimed that he was a frequent user of the UK National Lottery website and had never seen an email informing him of the ban. </p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">\r\nTo avoid confusion, calls were then made for Camelot to introduce location software preventing UK residents overseas from playing the National Lottery from abroad. Finally,  in 2012, after <strong>3 years of selling lottery tickets to overseas players that can not win</strong>, the National Lottery has stopped players with a foreign internet service provider from accessing the website.</p>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'UK Players Abroad Blocked From UK National Lottery Website ', 'national lottery, blocked, overseas, players, camelot, euromillions, euro millions', 'In 2012, Camelot finally put an end to confusion by introducing location software blocking UK players overseas.', 2, 1374732523, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'uk-players-blocked-national-lottery-website', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>Overseas players finally blocked from the UK National Lottery website</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1368521243, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
