INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (189, 167, 'en', 'winning_powerball_player_scoops_600_million', 'Winning Powerball Player Scoops $600 Million', '<img src="http://media.azfamily.com/images/470*264/5-17-13-POWERBALL-LARGEST-JACKPOT-MGN.jpg" width="260" height="160" align="left" alt="Powerball" />\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nOne very fortunate Powerball player in the United States scooped a staggering <strong>$590.5 million</strong> on <strong>Saturday the 18th of May 2013</strong>, the largest jackpot in the history of the Powerball lottery.</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nPowerball comprises a multi-state American lottery game. The minimum guaranteed Powerball jackpot is $40 million whilst the first prize can reach as many as nine figures, all of which winners winners may claim in 30 installments (annuity option) or in one lump sum at the cost of a substantial deduction. Powerball draws are held twice weekly, on Wednesdays and Saturdays, and to win the Powerball jackpot, players must match 5 main numbers from 59, and a powerball number from 35. The Powerball game is played in 43 states, as well as in the District of Columbia and the U.S Virgin Islands. It costs $2 per play and $3 for the Power Play option, which in the event of a win increases the prize money. </p>\r\n<img src="http://sphotos-d.ak.fbcdn.net/hphotos-ak-prn1/p480x480/923466_10151428596523931_888599377_n.jpg" width="200" height="200" align="right" alt="Powerball 600M dollar jackpot" />\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nThere is a <strong>1 in 175,223,510.00</strong> chance of scooping the coveted Powerball jackpot. However, despite the almost impossible odds, many lottery hopefuls remain undeterred and, on Saturday the 18th of May 2013, one lucky winning ticket holder beat them all by matching Saturday night''s winning numbers consequently scooping themselves a whopping <strong>$590.5 million jackpot prize (cash value of $370.9 million)</strong>. The single winner, currently waiting to be identified, purchased their ticket in a supermarket located in Zephryhills near Tampa in Florida, where two people have struck it rich by bagging more than $10m over the past few years. The winning combination from Saturday is as follows;</p><p align="left">\r\n<strong>10, 13, 14, 22 and 52, with a Powerball of 11.</strong></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<img src="http://a.abcnews.com/images/Business/gty_powerball_nt_130322_wg.jpg" width="260" height="160" align="left"  alt="Powerball tickets" />\r\nThis hundreds of millions of dollars windfall breaks all previous Powerball records including the (now) second largest Powerball win in the history of the game. Worth <strong>$587.5 million</strong>, the second largest Powerball jackpot was won by two fortunate players from Arizona and Missouri. However, the <strong>largest lottery jackpot in U.S history</strong> to date still corresponds to a <strong>$656 million prize</strong> in the Mega Millions game last March 2012, which was split three ways between winning ticket holders from Illinois, Maryland and Kansas. </p> \r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Winning Powerball Player Scoops $600 Million Jackpot', 'powerball, 600 million dollars, jackpot, florida', 'The $600 million Powerball jackpot went to a single player who bought their winning ticket in Florida.', 2, 1369138839, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'powerball-winner-scoops-$600-million', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>Lottery Player Wins Largest Powerball Prize in History</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1369137365, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
