INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (192, 170, 'en', 'euromillions_100m_euro_super_draw_this_7th_of_june', 'Euromillions 100M Euro Super Draw This 7th of June!', '<img src="http://www.prlog.org/10515368-euromillion-superdraw-friday-05-february-2010.jpg"  width="320" height="160" align="left" alt="Euromillions Super Draw" />\r\n<p align="justify"> A <strong> guaranteed 100 million euro Super Jackpot</strong>  is up for grabs this <strong> Friday the 7th of June</strong>  for <a href="www.euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> hopefuls across the world. Hurrah! Every year, one or several <strong> Euromillions Super Draws</strong>  are held in the 11 participating countries, whereby the minimum guaranteed amount is set at a life-changing 100 million euro regardless of the expected jackpot.</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nThe previous Super Draw, held on <strong> Tuesday the 22nd of March 2013</strong>, saw no winner. As a result all the lovely money rolled over to the consecutive draws, with Friday the 29th of March''s draw, producing a fortunate French winner who scooped a staggering <strong>£112,017,541 (€132 486 744)</strong>! Similarly, this Friday''s Super Draw failing to produce a winner will result in the money rolling right over to next Tuesday''s draw. </p>\r\n<img src="http://www.cyprusupdates.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/euros-546x387.jpg" width="250" height="150" align="right" alt="Money" />\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nLast week a <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/347/euromillions-winner-scoops-81-million-pound-jackpot">UK player pocketed a respectable £81,381,673.30 (€95 372 874,00)</a> Euromillions rollover jackpot. Featuring the joint 908th wealthiest person in the UK, this Euromillions winner, who opted to remain anonymous, now ranks 6th place on the National Lottery Rich List thanks to their unexpected windfall, just behind an anonymous ticket-holder who bagged <strong>£84,451,321 (€100,037,101)</strong> in 2010. Although France is record holder wi