INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (205, 183, 'en', 'common_myths_about_the_lottery', 'Common Myths About the Lottery', '<img src="http://www.freescratchcards.eu/wp-content/uploads/2011/11/Lottery.jpg" width="300" height="240" align="left" alt="Lottery Myths" />\r\n<p align="justify">There are many misleading facts about the <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-odds">\r\nlottery and odds of winning</a>. Thus, we have compiled a small list of all the major myths to do away with any doubts you may have. Enjoy!</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>1. Hot and Cold Numbers</strong></p> \r\n<p align="justify">\r\nA common misconception by superstitious players is that there are <strong>hot and cold numbers</strong>. Defined as those numbers that have appeared more and less frequently than others, it is believed that choosing or avoiding them will increase players'' chances of winning. However, this is entirely untrue. All the lottery numbers have an equal chance of being drawn. Similarly numbers that have recently been drawn have no less chance of appearing in future draws held soon after. To summarise, the odds are always the same.</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>2. Numbers between 1 and 31 are more likely to be selected by players.</strong></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nNot a myth! People who choose the numbers themselves, instead of purchasing a lucky dip, tend to select numbers which coincide with anniversaries, birthdays and other special dates. This however, doesn''t increase their chances of winning the lottery.</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>3. Playing in a group increases your chance of winning.</strong> </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nNot a myth! Each ticket has the same chance of winning however, by joining a lottery pool (participating in a group) you will have a lot more of them thus, increasing your chances of winning. The only downside is, of course, you will have to share the payout meaning that you will receive less. </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<img src="http://www.artsprofessional.co.uk/sites/artsprofessional.co.uk/files/styles/551_by_350_feature/public/lisa_brewster.jpg?itok=2mkPGvsx" width="340" height="240" align="right"  alt="Lottery Pool" />\r\n<strong>4.  You have more chance of winning when less people play.</strong></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nCompletely false! Your odds of winning remain exactly the same regardless of the number of players. A high participation rate only increases the odds of multiple winners. </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>5. Some lotteries are luckier than others.</strong></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nNo games are luckier than others, although the odds may vary from lottery to lottery based on how many winning numbers players'' have to match from a certain selection of numbers. For example, a <a href=http://play.euromillions.com/en/ rel="nofollow">Euromillions ticket</a> contains a line of 7 numbers, including 5 from a possible 50 main numbers and two lucky stars from 11 numbers. In contrast, the Lotto (UK National Lottery) ticket contains 6 numbers from a possible 49. However, the odds of winning the Lotto jackpot are 1 in 13,983,816 with the odds of winning any prize 1 in 54, whilst the chances of bagging the <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-prize-structure">Euromillions first prize</a> is 116,531,800 to 1 with the odds of winning any prize corresponding to 1 in 13. So as you can see, different lotteries and their corresponding rules vary greatly however, none are luckier than the other. The only thing certain in this case is that <strong>Euromillions boasts much bigger prizes!</strong> </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>6. Winning More Than Once is Impossible.</strong></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nThere have been cases whereby very fortunate lottery players have won more than once. For example George Traykov, living in Ilford, Essex recently went public with his second Euromilions win corresponding to £160,873. This lucky windfall brought his combined winnings to a sum total of £1.2 million. So, don''t give up, it is possible! </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<img src="http://www.dreamstime.com/lottery-numbers-thumb5322791.jpg" width="330" height="230" align="left" alt="Lottery Ticket" />\r\n<strong>7. Lucky Outlets Exist.</strong></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nUnfortunately, lucky outlets do not exist. Lottery hopefuls sometimes travel hundreds of miles to buy their ticket from a store where fortunate players have previously been made millionaires. If a particular outlet sells a higher volume of tickets than others, it would make sense that more winners will be produced. However, the reality is that you have as much chance of winning the lottery <a href="www.euromillions.com">purchasing your ticket online</a> or down at your local shop. </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>8. Lottery Draws are Not Conducted Fairly.</strong></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nFalse! In order to ensure that lottery draws are conducted fairly, they are subject to strict security measures and carried out in accordance with rigorous procedures. For example, it is common for the balls to be measured and weighed on a frequent basis. In addition, the draw machines are regularly checked to make sure that they are working properly, and all lottery equipment is safely kept in storage with limited access to avoid tampering between draws.</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>9. Lottery is a Form of Taxation.</strong> </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nPaying taxes is obligatory whilst playing the lottery is entirely voluntary. Whether it comprises an occasional participation or regular purchase, <strong>buying lottery tickets</strong> is completely down to the individual. The only drawback of not playing the lottery is missing out on a bit of fun and potentially losing a huge cash prize! </p> \r\n<p align="justify">\r\nTo conclude, all lottery draw results are completely random and can not be predicted or manipulated. <strong>Happy betting and good luck!</strong> \r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Common Lottery Myths Dispelled', 'lottery, myths, facts, dispelled, busted, euromillions, euro millions', 'There are quite a few lottery myths floating around which we have decided to lay to rest. Find out what they are with Euromillions.com!', 2, 1372852885, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'common-lottery-myths-dispelled', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>Common Lottery Myths Dispelled</h2></p>', 'Lottery Myths', NULL, 1372850507, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (206, 184, 'en', '100_uk_millionaires_guaranteed_this_july_2013', '100 UK Millionaires Guaranteed This July 2013', '<img src="http://i3.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article1158436.ece/ALTERNATES/s615/EM+100+Millionaires+(2).jpg" width="240" height="140" align="left" alt="100 UK Millionaires Draw" />\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nOn <strong> Friday the 26th of July 2013</strong>  a special Millionaire Raffle will be held whereby no less than <strong> 100 fortunate UK Euromillions players</strong>  will win a staggering £1 MILLION cash prize. Yes, in addition to the coveted <a href="www.euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> jackpot, <strong> 100 £1 MILLION cheques</strong>  will be handed out to 100 UK lottery hopefuls.</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nSo, what do you have to do to win? By simply <a href=http://play.euromillions.com/en/ rel="nofollow">purchasing a Euromillions ticket</a> in the UK you will be granted a free entry in the Millionaire Raffle. If your numbers match any one of the 100 Millionaires Raffle numbers drawn, a cool <strong> £1 MILLION</strong>  will be yours. Hurrah! </p>\r\n<img src="http://images.icnetwork.co.uk/upl/huddexaminer/jul2012/1/8/image-7-for-london-2012-olympic-opening-ceremony-gallery-812460996.jpg" width="260" height="160" align="right" alt="2012 Olympics Opening Ceremony" />\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nIt comprises the second 100 Millionaires Raffle to be held, the last of which took place on <strong> Friday the 27th of July 2012</strong> . It was held as a way of saying thank you to UK lottery players who helped raise funding for the <strong> 2012 Summer Olympics and Paralympics Games</strong>. Of course, this huge Millionaire Raffle draw coincided with the <strong> 2012 Olympics Opening Ceremony</strong> making it a very special day all round. Dubbed the largest lottery draw ever, it immediately set the record for the biggest number of newly-made millionaires in a single draw. </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong> 100 fortunate Euromillions players</strong> scooped the coveted <strong> £1 MILLION prize</strong>  last year however, only 97 winners came forward to claim the money. This <strong> 26th of July 2013''s 100 Millionaires Draw</strong>  will set a new record if this time all 100 players claim their prize! Good luck everyone, we''ll be crossing our fingers for you! </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', '100 UK Millionaires Guaranteed in 100 Millionaires Raffle This July', '100, millionaire raffle, euromillions, euro million, july, 2013, UK', '100 UK players will become millionaires this July the 26th 2013 as part of the 100 Millionaires Raffle offering 100 £1 Million cheques!', 2, 1374734928, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', '100-millionaires-raffle-july', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>100 UK Millionaires Guaranteed in July 100 Millionaires Raffle</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1373013425, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (207, 185, 'en', 'france_is_euromillions_luckiest_country', 'France is Euromillions Luckiest Country', '<img src="http://www.eagleonline.com/wp-content/uploads/lucky.jpg" width="220" height="160" align="left"  alt="four-leaf-clover" />\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nAs explained in our  fascinating <a href="{{news_url::183}}">Common Lottery Myths Dispelled</a> article, the <a href="{{article_url::discover_your_odds_of_winning_the_euromillions}}">odds of winning the Euromillions</a> are the same for each and every individual player. However, for whatever reason some people appear to have all the luck! This is quite the case for France, who out of all the <strong>13 participating  Euromillions countries</strong>, has proven to be the most fortunate to date. This year alone, 7 French players have bagged the coveted <a href="www.euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> jackpot with the following staggering wins:\r\n</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n- 1st of January 2013 – Two players won €12,677,536 each</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n- 11th January 2013 -  €34,191,508 was scooped by one player from Pas-de-Calais</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n- 25th of January 2013 - €44,297,359 was won by one player from Charente-Maritime</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n- 29th of March 2013 - €132,486,744 was bagged by one player from Seine-et-Marne</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n- 12th of April 2013 – One player won £26,258,943</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n- 28th of June 2013 – One player won €15,000,000</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n- 30th of August 2013 – One player won €12,821,111.50</p>\r\n<img src="http://www.drhdelannee.fr/uploads/Image/drhdelannee/fdj.jpg" width="260" height="100" align="right" alt="logo-française-des-jeux" />\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nThe latest first prize takes France''s accumulated winnings to a whopping <strong>€290, 410, 737.50</strong> this 2013. In addition, it marks the <strong>67th French jackpot</strong> since the <a href="{{article_url::euromillions_history}}">beginning of Euromillions in 2004</a>. Finally, France also boasts the <strong>3rd, 4th and 5th biggest single ticket jackpots</strong> ever won in the history of the game with the huge cash prize from Tuesday the 13th of November comprising the largest in the history of the country. It knocked the previous title-holder from 2011 off the top spot and immediately catapulted the fortunate player to 221st place amongst the richest people in France.  </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n- 13th of September 2011 - €162,256,622 was scooped by one player in Calvados. </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n- 13th of November 2012 - €169,837,010 was won by one player in Alpes-Maritimes. </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n- 29th of March 2013 - €132,486,744  (see above). </p>\r\n<img src="http://www.menageremag.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/05/fdj_grille_jeu_euromillions.jpg"  width="260" height="160" align="left" alt="euromillions-ticket" />\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nHowever, despite their good fortune, the UK still holds the record for the two <a href="{{news_url::161}}">biggest Euromillions jackpot winners</a>. Chris and Colin Weir won <strong>£161,653,000 (€185,000,000)</strong> in 2011 whilst Gillian and Adrian Bayford scooped a staggering <strong>£148,656,000 (€190,000,000)</strong> back in 2012. Let''s hope that the UK and France''s luck extends a little to the other participating countries, such as Luxembourg, who have yet to see a </strong>Euromillions jackpot winner.</strong> </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nIf you would like a little of your own good fortune then make sure you take a look at our handy tips on <strong>how to increase your chances of winning the Euromilions</strong> <a href="{{news_url::121}}">here</a>. Good luck! </p>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Euromillions Luckiest Country', 'euromillions, euro millions, country, luck, france', 'Discover Euromillions luckiest country, title-holder of the most Euromillions jackpots ever won in the history of the game! ', 1, 1378464172, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'euromillions-luckiest-country', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>France title-holder of most Euromillions prizes won</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1373356116, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (208, 186, 'en', 'winner_scoops_28_million_euromillions_jackpot', 'Winner Scoops £28 million Euromillions Jackpot', '<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">This time a fortunate UK Player managed to scoop the coveted <a href="www.euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> jackpot. They walked away a staggering £28,847,237 (€33,574,531) the richer following last night''s draw. Congratulations! The <strong>winning Euromillions numbers from Tuesday the 9th of July''s draw</strong> are:</p><p align="center">\r\n  <span class="greenball">16</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">18</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">31</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">38</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">49</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">4</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">10</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nAnother Euromillions winner matched 5 main numbers and a lucky star thus, bagging themselves a respectable €1,134,284.60 (no UK winners) in the second category, whilst 3 more fortunates pocketed  £84,851.80 (€126,031.60) in the third tier. It appears to have been a successful night all around for lottery hopefuls everywhere! The last £12 million (€15 million) Euromillions jackpot went to a lucky French player on the 28th of June 2013 which comprised the country''s 6th Euromillions jackpot win this year alone!  \r\n<p align="justify">\r\nHaving scooped the largest number of jackpots in the history of the game, you could say that France is the\r\n<a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/364/euromillions-luckiest-country">luckiest Euromillions country</a>. However, this may be set to change with the UK current title-holder of the\r\n<a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/340/top-5-biggest-uk-euromillions-jackpot-winners">biggest Euromillions jackpots</a> ever won and last night''s addition to the millionaire club. Finally, with the <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/363/100-uk-millionaires-guaranteed-in-100-millionaires-raffle-this-july">\r\n100 Millionaires Draw</a> this Friday July the 26th 2013, a further 100 UK Players will be £1 million the richer. Good luck everyone! \r\n</p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><strong>Watch the latest Euromillions draw:</strong><BR>\r\n</p>\r\n<iframe width="580" height="320" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/Wr2aU95-E-U?feature=player_detailpage" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Euromillions Results for Tuesday the 9th of July 2013', 'euromillions, results, numbers, winners, euro millions, jackpot', 'A fortunate UK player scooped the £28 million jackpot in last night''s draw! Read all  about it, and get the latest numbers on euromillions.com.', 2, 1373443865, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'euromillions-draw-tuesday-09-july-2013', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>A UK player scooped the £28 million jackpot</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1373443562, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (209, 187, 'en', 'euromillions_jackpot_rolls_over_to_19_million', 'Euromillions Jackpot Rolls Over to £19 Million', '<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">A staggering <strong>£19 MILLION (€22 MILLION)</strong> is now up for grabs in this Tuesday''s draw following no jackpot winner on Friday. Players also failed to match the 5 main numbers and 2 lucky stars for a huge cash prize in the second tier. However, the third tier saw a few fortunates scoop a respectable £281,686 (€412,933). Friday the 12th of July''s draw results are as follows: </p><p align="center">\r\n  <span class="greenball">18</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">26</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">32</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">33</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">42</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">2</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">3</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nCheck your numbers, because a lovely lot of money could be yours! Those UK hopefuls who just missed out on a <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results?show=1">Euromillions prize</a> may be interested to know that on the 26th of July 2013, a <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/363/100-uk-millionaires-guaranteed-in-100-millionaires-raffle-this-july">100 Millionaires Draw</a> will be held. A guaranteed <strong>100 UK players will be handed a £1 million cheque</strong> so get your <a href=http://play.euromillions.com/en/ rel="nofollow">Euromillions ticket</a> and make sure you don''t miss out. Good luck! \r\n<p align="justify">\r\n</p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><strong>Watch Friday''s draw:</strong><BR>\r\n</p>\r\n<iframe width="580" height="320" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/81n5Mv26Ut0?feature=player_detailpage" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Euromillions Results for Friday the 12th of July 2013 ', 'euromillions, results, numbers, friday, euro millions, winners', 'Tuesday''s jackpot now stands at £19 million following no first prize winner on Friday. Get your ticket on www.euromillions.com for your chance to win!', 2, 1373877651, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'euromillions-draw-friday-12-july-2013', NULL, '<p align="justify">Tuesday''s jackpot stands at £19 million!</p>', NULL, NULL, 1373877409, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (210, 188, 'en', 'winner_scoops_19_million_jackpot', ' Winner Scoops £19 Million Jackpot', '<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">The coveted <strong>£19 million (€22 million) jackpot</strong> was scooped by a fortunate Euromillions winner who managed to match all 5 main numbers and 2 lucky stars. Congratulations! Similarly, Euromillions players won a lovely lot of cash prizes in the lower tiers which you can find out in the full <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results?show=1">Euromillions Prize Breakdown</a>. In the meantime, the winning Euromillions numbers for Tuesday the 16th of July''s draw are as follows: </p><p align="center">\r\n  <span class="greenball">19</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">23</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">34</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">47</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">50</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">4</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">6</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nCheck your ticket because a huge cash prize could be yours! Further details are yet to be revealed however, the <strong>£19,201,363 (€22,078,146) jackpot</strong> didn''t go to a UK player, although lottery hopefuls managed to scoop a respectable £239,904.20 in the second tier, amongst others. Finally, excitement is really building up for the forthcoming <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/363/100-uk-millionaires-guaranteed-in-100-millionaires-raffle-this-july">100 Millionaires Draw</a> taking place at the end of this July. Find out how you could feature amongst the 100 GUARANTEED newly-made millionaires. In the meantime, for your chance to win this Friday''s £13 million (€15 million) jackpot <a href=http://play.euromillions.com/en/ rel="nofollow">play Euromillions online</a> at <a href="www.euromillions.com">www.euromillions.com</a>. Remember, you have to be in it to win it. Good luck! \r\n</p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><strong>Watch Tuesday''s Euromillions draw:</strong><BR>\r\n</p>\r\n<iframe width="580" height="320" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/fbN5GV4ur_g?feature=player_detailpage" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Euromillions Results for Tuesday the 16th of July 2013', 'euromillions, results, numbers, winners, euro millions, jackpot', 'The £19 million jackpot was scooped by a lucky Euromilions player in last night''s draw meaning that an estimated £13 million is up for grabs on Friday. Don''t miss out!', 2, 1374049264, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'euromillions-draw-tuesday-16-july-2013', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>£19 million jackpot pocketed by lucky Euromillons player</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1374048666, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (211, 189, 'en', 'lottery_misses_and_near_misses', 'Lottery Misses and Near Misses', '<img src="http://gulfnews.com/polopoly_fs/1.1018384!/image/101888413.jpg_gen/derivatives/box_475/101888413.jpg" width="300" height="220" align="left" alt="Sharon Jones" />\r\n<p align="justify">There are reportedly many places people hide their purchased lottery tickets. In their pet''s basket, under the welcome mat, on the fridge, safely in their wallet or dangerously in their trouser pockets for a guaranteed journey through the washing machine, amongst many others. One thing is certain, playing the lottery online is fast becoming the ideal choice given the many misfortunes which can occur if you carelessly misplace your winning ticket or completely forget that you bought it in the first place. In fact, we frequently hear about stories of near misses, and unfortunately complete lottery misses whereby the unsuspecting player has failed to step forward and claim a life-changing cash prize, which you can discover in Lottery Misses and Near Misses. Enjoy! \r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>Lottery Near Misses</strong>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n1. Back in 2011, Sharon Jones from Arkansas in the United States, found a discarded scratch card in the rubbish bin. She became the immediate winner of a million dollar cash prize. However, the store manager of the Super One Stop, where she found the winning ticket, claims that she shouldn''t get the money because it was found in her store. The ticket was discovered only half scratched off and with no signature on the back. Following an investigation, the local Lottery Commission awarded Sharon the million dollars however, it is currently being held in escrow pending a court order. Unlucky for her and even more unfortunate for the person who unwittingly threw away a million dollars! \r\n\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n2. A UK couple found a winning lottery ticket on the supermarket floor worth a respectable £30,000 in 2009. Unaware that they were committing a crime, Michael and Amanda Stacey immediately cashed in the prize and went on a major spending spree. They paid off their debts, treated their children and re-carpeted their house spending half of the winnings in the process. However, the real owner of the winning ticket, Dorothy McDonagh, contacted lottery operator Camelot with proof that the slip was actually hers. \r\n<img src="http://image.stirileprotv.ro/media/images/original/May2013/61324475.jpg" width="320" height="180" align="right" alt="Ricardo Cerezo" />\r\nThe remaining £15,000 was frozen by the police and the couple arrested for theft and dishonesty. Meanwhile, to get the remaining winnings Mrs McDonagh will have to launch a private cause of action. \r\n<p align="justify">\r\n\r\n3. Just recently (May 2013) Ricardo Cerezo from Illinois was facing eviction from his home when one day he found a winning ticket worth $4.85 million in an old glass cookie jar. His wife, who was apparently cleaning the kitchen, mentioned some lottery tickets which had been accumulating in the glass cookie jar in question for some time. As you can imagine, Mr. Cerezo took them to get scanned and one of them turned out to be a winner. He went online to check his numbers and found that they matched the February the 2nd 2013 Lotto drawing. He most immediate plans include paying off his home with some of the huge $4.85 million cash prize. \r\n<p align="justify">\r\n4. A man from Christchurch in New Zealand, who wished to remain anonymous, found a winning Lotto ticket in his “odds and ends” drawer this April 2013. He was reportedly a frequent player but very often forgot to check his tickets. On this occasion New Zealand was searching for the winner of a $666,667 cash prize won in November last year. So, whilst searching for some sticky tape, he came across some old lottery tickets and after hearing that there was a prize still outstanding, he checked the numbers online. The rest is history! \r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>Lottery Misses</strong>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n1. Last December 2012 saw the <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/303/one-week-left-for-british-player">biggest unclaimed prize in lottery history</a>. One unsuspecting Euromillions player in the UK had scooped themselves a staggering €64 million following a draw held in June. \r\n<img src="http://www.nypost.com/rw/nypost/2011/04/01/news/photos_stories/michael_kosko--300x300.jpg" width="240" height="220" align="left" alt="Michael Kosko" />\r\nPurchased in the Stevenage and Hitchin areas of Hertfordshire, the UK National Lottery launched widespread appeals and poster campaigns urging for the winning ticket-holder to come forward. However, the 5th of December deadline came and went thus, all winnings and accumulated interest were promptly donated to the <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/337/euromillions-lottery-winners-and-good-causes">\r\nUK National Lottery Good Causes</a>. \r\n\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n2. Michael Kosko was the extremely unfortunate man who missed out on a share of $319 million. Thus, whilst several of his work colleagues scooped a whopping $28.9 dollars each in the Mega Millions, Mr Kosko, who usually would have played in the syndicate, declined because he didn''t have any change. He reasoned that they had been playing for several months and had never won anything so, even though a colleague offered to lend him the money, he still decided not to play. Unlucky!!\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n3. The recent <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/346/winning-powerball-player-scoops-600-million-dollar-jackpot">winner of the record $590.5 million Powerball prize</a> from Zephyrhills, Florida was extremely lucky! 84-year old Gloria Mackenzie was allowed to jump the queue by Mindy Crandell who was tending to her daughter at the time. \r\nMrs Mackenzie ended up purchasing a Powerball ticket which led to her claiming the largest amount ever won in the history of the lottery. Mrs Crandell''s daughter recognised her when she went to claim the money the Wednesday following the draw. \r\n<img src="http://tribkswb.files.wordpress.com/2013/06/130605163758-gloria-mackenzie-story-top.jpg?w=640" width="320" height="200" align="right" alt="Gloria Mckenzie" />\r\nHer charitable gesture basically cost her the winning ticket worth a staggering $590.5 million or $370.8 million after tax. \r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>Wouldn''t you just kick yourself!</strong> So, why should you buy online? Firstly, we won''t lose your ticket. Your bet is safe from the clutches of the dog, washing machine, “odds and ends draw” or any other worldly danger that could cost you your huge cash prize. Secondly, at <a href="www.euromillions.com">www.euromillions.com</a> you can credit your Euromillions account with money and buy a ticket from the comfort of your own home. Change and trailing down to your local shop is not required. Finally, we send the results straight into your inbox so the deadline will seem more than enough time to claim your prize. Remember, billions of pounds go unclaimed every year. Don''t let that be you! \r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Lottery Misses and Near Misses', 'lottery, jackpot, unclaimed, misses, euro millions, euromillions', 'Lottery players have come very close to missing out on a huge cash prize. In some cases it has gone unclaimed. Read about it here on www.euromillions.com!', 2, 1375441823, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'lottery-misses-near-misses', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>Shocking lottery misses and near misses</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1374064341, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (212, 190, 'en', 'second_euromillions_jackpot_winner_in_a_week', 'Second Euromillions Jackpot Winner in a Week ', '<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Euromillions players seem to be on a lucky streak with yet another first prize winner on Friday! The lucky lottery hopeful successfully matched the 5 main numbers and 2 lucky stars making them the second newly-made millionaire in the space of a week! Friday''s winning ticket holder pocketed <strong> £12,925,500 (€15 million)</strong> whilst <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/367/euromillions-results-for-tuesday-the-16th-of-july-2013">Tuesday''s Euromillions winner scooped £19 million</a> (€22 million) respectively. Congratulations! In addition to the £12,925,500 (€15 million) jackpot, many other <a href="www.euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> players saw themselves lucky recipients of a huge cash prize. The winning numbers from Friday the 19th of July''s Euromillions draw are as follows: </p><p align="center">\r\n  <span class="greenball">3</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">16</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">24</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">26</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">35</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">2</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">5</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nCheck your ticket, you might have won something! The full Euromillions results and their corresponding prizes can be found <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">here</a>. Although the winning ticket holder''s identity has yet to be revealed, we do know that the jackpot didn''t go to a UK player. However, with the <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/363/100-uk-millionaires-guaranteed-in-100-millionaires-raffle-this-july"> 100 Millionaires Raffle"</a> taking place in no less than 4 days, the number of Brits featuring on the UK National Lottery Rich List will experience a sharp rise to say the least. Have you got your ticket?!\r\n</p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><strong>Watch the latest Euromillions draw:</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<iframe width="580" height="320" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/yEVXvMz6uTE?feature=player_detailpage" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Euromillions Results For Friday the 19th of July 2013', 'euromillions, results, numbers, winners, euro millions, jackpot', 'Friday''s Euromillions draw produced the second jackpot winner in a week!  Find out more on www.euromillions.com.', 2, 1374477434, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'euromillions-draw-tuesday-1-july-2013', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>Euromillions winner scoops £13 million jackpot!</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1374476539, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (213, 191, 'en', 'lotto_plus_5_to_be_scrapped', ' Lotto Plus 5 to be Scrapped ', '<img src="http://lotterymonitor.org/img/lottery_logos/10_profile.jpg " width="220" height="200" align="left" alt="The Lotto" />\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">As part of the changes announced by lottery operator Camelot earlier this year, not only will <a href="{{news_url::150}}">UK National Lottery ticket prices be doubling</a> and the prize structure revamped but, the side game Lotto Plus 5 is to be scrapped as well. Thus, Lotto Plus 5, which offers players another chance of winning, will be replaced by the new Lotto Raffle supposedly guaranteeing more prize winners per draw.   </p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">\r\n<strong>Lotto Plus 5</strong></p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">\r\nLotto Plus 5 comprises a side game to the Lotto which offers players a further chance of winning. Whilst it features 5 tiers like the Lotto, the Lotto Plus 5 draws are held 5 times throughout the week (everyday excluding Saturday and Wednesday) thus, the cash prizes correspond to a smaller amount. It costs an extra £1 per play however, <a href="www.euromillions.com">lottery</a> hopefuls are automatically entered into five separate lotto Plus 5 Draws. To take part, players need to play Lotto. When they complete the Lotto slip they simply select the “Plus 5” checkbox next to the Lotto line of their choice. As is the case with the Lotto, 3 or more numbers need to be matched to claim a prize which ranges from £2.50 to the top prize of £25,000.\r\n<img src="http://img.thesun.co.uk/multimedia/archive/01276/lotto380_1276598a.jpg" width="320" height="160" align="right" alt="Lotto Plus 5" />\r\nRollovers are a frequent occurrence, with no first prize winner for (sometimes) weeks, as lottery hopefuls still have to match 6 out of a possible 49 lottery numbers.  </p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">\r\n<strong>New Lotto Raffle</strong></p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">\r\nAll this is soon to change after the UK National Lottery announced the discontinuation of the Lotto Plus 5, which will be replaced by a new Lotto Raffle. The <strong>3 major differences between Lotto 5 Plus and the new Lotto Raffle</strong> are as follows:</p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">\r\n1. Similarly to the <a href="{{news_url::184}}">Euromillions UK Millionaire Raffle</a>, the new Lotto Raffle will be obligatory. You can not opt out of playing.</p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">\r\n2. Players will receive one raffle number for every line of Lotto that they purchase. Their raffle entry will automatically be selected from a pool of numbers and printed on their Lotto ticket.</p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">\r\n<img src="http://www.national-lottery.co.uk/player/i/article/lp5_info_check_step1.gif" width="280" height="180" align="left"  alt="How to Play Lotto Plus 5" />\r\n3. Finally, the received raffle number(s) will remain the same for all draws that players enter in a single transaction. For example, if a lottery hopeful plays two lines for two weeks on both Wednesday and Saturday in a single transaction then their two raffle entries will remain the same for each of the four draws. Similarly, if four Lotto lines are purchased separately then the player will receive four different Lotto Raffle numbers, one on each Lotto ticket, corresponding to four entries per Lotto Raffle draw.  </p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">\r\nAccording to the UK National Lottery, the new side game will guarantee that at least 50 players scoop a £20,000 prize per draw, whilst many more winners in the rollovers will be produced. In the meantime, Lotto Plus 5 will still be available to players up until <strong>Saturday the 5th of October 2013</strong>, when the various changes announced by the UK National Lottery finally come into effect. </p>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br>', 'New Lotto Raffle to Replace Lotto Plus 5', 'lotto plus 5, lotto raffle, side game, uk national lottery, euro millions, euromillions', 'A new Lotto Raffle, guaranteeing more prize winners, will replace the Lotto Plus 5  on Saturday the 5th of October 2013 according to the UK National Lottery.', 1, 1378284229, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'new-lotto-raffle', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>New Lotto Raffle to be launched  this Saturday the 5th of October 2013</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1374502713, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (214, 192, 'en', 'player_scoops_euromillions_jackpot', 'Player Scoops Euromillions Jackpot', '<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">The winning streak continues as yet another player strikes it lucky in the <a href="www.euromillions.com">Euromillions</a>. Last night''s draw produced the third consecutive newly-made millionaire in the last two weeks. The fortunate lottery hopeful scooped a respectable <strong>£12,907,500 (€15 million)</strong> whilst last week''s winning ticket-holders won £12,925,500 (€15 million) and £19 million (€22 million) respectively. Congratulations! Their identities have yet to be revealed. The <strong>winning Euromillions numbers</strong> from Tuesday the 23rd of July’s draw are as follows: </p><p align="center">\r\n  <span class="greenball">14</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">15</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">16</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">19</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">44</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">4</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">5</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nIf you matched 2 or more numbers then you may be entitled to a cash prize. Check the <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">Euromillions Prize Breakdown</a> to make sure! In the meantime, the excitement is really building up as the 26th of July 2013, date of the approaching <a href"http://euromillions.com/news-article/363/100-uk-millionaires-guaranteed-in-100-millionaires-raffle-this-july">100 Millionaires Raffle</a>, is almost upon us.  </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nAlso new in this autumn will be the <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/371/new-lotto-raffle-to-replace-lotto-plus-5">Lotto Raffle</a> as part of the <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/329/uk-national-lottery-ticket-price-increase">changes announced by the UK National Lottery</a>. The Lotto Plus 5 will be replaced by this new side game which guarantees at least 50 winners per draw, and more chances of scooping a cash prize in the rollovers. Playing the lottery has never been more fun! So, do you have your Euromillions ticket for this Friday''s draw? Remember, that''s a guaranteed 100 UK millionaires in the Millionaire Raffle on top of Friday''s £13 million jackpot. Make sure you don''t miss out!\r\n</p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><strong>Watch last night''s Euromillions draw:</strong><BR>\r\n</p>\r\n<iframe width="580" height="320" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/CyTbIOq1LpU?feature=player_detailpage" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Euromillions Results for Tuesday the 23rd of July 2013', 'euromillions, results, numbers, euro millions, winners, jackpot', 'Yet another player scoops the coveted Euromillions jackpot making it the 3rd consecutive win in the last two weeks! Find out more on www.euromillions.com!', 2, 1374647796, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'euromillions-draw-tuesday-23-july-2013', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>Euromillions winners pockets the £13 million jackpot!</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1374647232, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
