" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Euromillions Results for Friday the 2nd of August 2013', 'euromillions, results, numbers, friday, euro millions, winners, rollover', '£34 million is up for grabs as last Friday''s Euromillions jackpot went unclaimed. Get your tickets now on www.euromillions.com for your chance to win!', 2, 1375684902, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'euromillions-draw-friday-2-august-2013', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>Friday''s £28 million jackpot rolls over to Tuesday''s draw</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1375684567, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (218, 196, 'en', 'uk_national_lottery_ticket_sales_reach_7bn', 'UK National Lottery Ticket Sales Reach £7bn', '<img src="http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/About/General/2009/6/25/1245935789653/lottery-tickets-001.jpg"  width="270" height="170" align="left"alt="UK National Lottery" />\r\n<p align="justify">The UK National Lottery recently announced that sales for the last financial year reached an <strong>all time high of nearly £7 billion</strong>. Yes, despite the country''s current financial woes, lottery operator Camelot saw record ticket sales for the year 2012/2013, corresponding to a 6.9% increase on the previous year. As a result, the <a href="http://bit.ly/euromillionsgoodcauses">UK National Lottery Good Causes</a> received almost £2 billion to distribute amongst the 13 funders taking the total amount raised for <strong>Good Causes to a staggering £30 billion</strong> since it was launched in 1994. \r\n<p align="justify">\r\nDespite 2012/2013''s excellent sales figures Camelot Chief, Dianne Thompson, remained sceptical. “Our latest research shows that if the economic situation wasn’t as bad as it is and has been, we’d probably be selling at least another £50m, possibly £70m, of tickets a year.” Indeed, Andy Duncan, Managing Director of Camelot put the lottery''s success down to it''s broad appeal and recent developments in channels of distribution (such as playing online) thus, dismissing the theory that tough times are encouraging lottery hopefuls to rush out and play.\r\n<img src="http://cached.imagescaler.hbpl.co.uk/resize/scaleWidth/456/?sURL=http://offlinehbpl.hbpl.co.uk/News/NST/3F73C2F5-AFE6-B44D-846702A5FFEAF212.jpg" width="240" height="180" align="right" alt="Diane Thompson" />\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nIn addition to the current recession, the UK National Lottery also faced competition from the Health Lottery set up approximately a year and a half ago. Launched by the Daily Express'' Richard Desmond, it comprises a collection of regional lotteries promoted on a national level. Fortunately for the UK National Lottery, the Health Lottery proved to be less popular amongst players than predicted thus, it had no major impact on sales. However, Ms Thompson fears that their figures could be affected should 4 or 5 more lotteries emerge in future. \r\n<img src="http://www.healthlottery.co.uk/images/the-health-lottery-logo.png" width="180" height="200" align="left" alt="Health Lottery" />\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n2012 also proved to be very successful for the increasingly popular <a href="www.euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> lottery. The UK National Lottery reported <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/202/camelot-sales-increase">\r\nEuromillions tickets sales of £3.8 billion</a> on £3.2 billion recorded only 6 months previously, corresponding to an increase of almost 20%. \r\n<p align="justify">\r\nFinally, the foreseen <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/329/uk-national-lottery-ticket-price-increase">increase in lottery ticket prices</a> from £1 to £2 may pose Camelot''s biggest challenge yet. Facing declining Lotto sales, which have more than halved in a year, the UK National Lottery decided to double the ticket price some time this autumn and replace the Lotto Plus 5 side game with the <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/371/new-lotto-raffle-to-replace-lotto-plus-5">new Lotto Raffle</a>, very similar to the <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-uk-millionaire-raffle">Euromillions UK Millionaire Raffle</a>. The lottery operator claims that the hefty increase in price, amidsr amongst players and threats to boycott the game, would be offset by more winners and bigger prizes. \r\n</p>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'UK National Lottery Ticket Sales Reach £7bn', 'uk national lottery, ticket sales, good causes, euro millions, euromillions', 'The UK National Lottery recently reported that last year''s tickets sales reached an all time high of nearly £7 bn. Find out more on www.euromillions.com! ', 2, 1375797481, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'ticket-sales-7bn', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>UK National Lottery Sales Hit All Time High of Nearly £7bn</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1375796691, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
