od-causes">UK National Lottery Good Causes</a>. The hunt is on! If you played the <a href="http://euromillions.com/">Euromillions lottery</a> on the 26th of July 2013, check your ticket. You could be in the money!</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Ten 100 Millionaires Raffle Prizes Remain Unclaimed', '100 millionaires raffle, 2013, euromillions, euro millions, winners, prizes, unclaimed ', 'Ten winners of the 100 Millionaires Raffle, held on the 26th of July 2013, have yet to claim their £1 million prize. Find out more on www.euromillions.com!', 2, 1377598534, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'millionaire-raffle-prizes-unclaimed-2013', 'http://i3.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article1158436.ece/ALTERNATES/s615/EM+100+Millionaires+(2).jpg', '<p align="justify"><h2>Cut off date for 100 Millionaires Raffle prizes is January the 22nd 2014</h2></p>', '100 Millionaires Raffle', NULL, 1377592471, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (226, 204, 'en', 'euromillions_jackpot_rolls_over_to_21_million', 'Euromillions Jackpot Rolls Over to £21 Million', '<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Once again it''s a rollover as the coveted first prize went unclaimed in last night''s <a href="http://euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> draw.  Lottery hopefuls scooped €513,509.70 (no UK winners) in the second tier, whilst other fortunates saw themselves £57,123.80 (€85,584.90) the richer, amongst others. Congratulations! However, the £12,931,500 jackpot evaded players across the world who failed to match that last lucky star. This means that a staggering £21 million (€25 million) is now up for grabs in this Friday''s draw. In other news, the lucky <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/382/swiss-ticket-holder-scoops-81-million-pound-euromillions-jackpot">winner of\r\nlast Friday''s £81 million jackpot</a> has yet to come forward however, we do know that it was a Swiss ticket-holder. In the meantime, the <strong>winning Euromillions numbers from Tuesday the 27th of August 2013</strong> are as follows: </p><p align="center">\r\n  <span class="greenball">7</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">30</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">38</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">40</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">43</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">2</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">6</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>Millionaire Raffle:</strong> NFV150144</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nCheck your ticket because, if you matched more than 2 numbers a huge cash prize could be yours! The full Euromillions Prize Breakdown is available <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">here</a>. In addition, if you played Euromillions on the 26th of July 2013, when the <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/363/100-uk-millionaires-guaranteed-in-100-millionaires-raffle-this-july">100 Millionaires Raffle 2013</a> was celebrated, then check that ticket too because <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/383/ten-100-millionaires-raffle-prizes-remain-unclaimed">ten 100 Millionaires Raffle prizes still remain unclaimed</a>. Finally, if you would like the chance to win the £21 million (€25 million) jackpot up for grabs this Friday the 30th of August then get your tickets now on www.euromillions.com for £1.85 a shot. Alternatively, take part in our weekly twitter contest and free Euromillions tickets could be yours. We''ll be crossing our fingers for you! \r\n<p align="justify">\r\n</p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><strong>Watch Tuesday''s Euromillions draw:</strong><BR>\r\n</p>\r\n<iframe width="580" height="320" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/qBBqHyso7j8?feature=player_detailpage" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Euromillions Results for Tuesday the 27th of August 2013', 'euromillions, results, numbers, tuesday, euro millions, winners, rollover', 'It''s a rollover following no 1st prize winner in last night''s draw meaning that a whopping £21 million is up for grabs on Friday. Get your ticket now!', 2, 1377671745, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'euromillions-draw-tuesday-27-august-2013', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>£21 million is up for grabs in Friday''s Euromillions draw</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1377670807, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (227, 205, 'en', 'euromillions_winner_unknowing_millionaire_for_3_months', 'Euromillions Winner Unknowing Millionaire For 3 Months', '<img src="http://news.bbcimg.co.uk/media/images/69525000/jpg/_69525771_janeo%27brienruislipeuromillionsraffle280813(9).jpg" width="229" height="289" align="left" alt="jane-obrien-euromillions" />\r\n<p align="justify">Jane O''Brien, from Middlesex in the UK, walked round with a winning £1 million ticket in her handbag for 12 weeks before she realised that she was a millionaire. The Transport for London Operator said “Every so often I get a Lucky Dip. It just went in the side of my bag. I didn''t give it much thought”. \r\n<p align="justify">\r\nFortunately, her handbag became too heavy. So, last Thursday over breakfast, she decided to clean it out upon which she discovered an old <strong>Euromillions ticket</strong> amongst all the old paperwork. She then checked her <strong>Euromillions numbers online</strong> and discovered that her lucky dip ticket matched the <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-uk-millionaire-raffle">UK Millionaire Raffle</a> prize code from the 10th of May 2013. Not being able to believe her luck, she immediately called the UK National Lottery hotline who promptly confirmed her £1 million win!\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nThe newly-made millionaire was just inside the 180-day cut off point to claim her prize making it a very <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/368/lottery-misses-and-near-misses">near lottery miss</a> to say the least! In related news, ten winners from the <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/363/100-uk-millionaires-guaranteed-in-100-millionaires-raffle-this-july">100 Millionaires Raffle</a> held on the 26th of July 2013 have yet to step forward and claim their staggering £1 million prize! Full details on the winning raffle numbers are available <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/383/ten-100-millionaires-raffle-prizes-remain-unclaimed">here</a>. \r\n<p align="justify">\r\nSo ladies, let that be a lesson to you! Your handbags could be hiding all sorts of hidden treasures in their many pockets. Just to be on the safe side, play Euromillions online with <a href="http://euromillions.com">www.euromillions.com</a>. We promise we won''t lose your ticket!</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Euromillions Winner Unknowing Millionaire For 3 Months', 'euromillions, euro millions, handbag, millionaire raffle, lucky dip', 'A woman from Middlesex carried round a winning £1 m Euromillions ticket in her handbag for 3 months before she discovered she was a millionaire!', 2, 1377776694, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'unknown-millionaire-3-months', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>Woman unknowingly carries winning £1 million ticket round for 3 months</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1377774943, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (228, 206, 'en', 'two_players_scoop_21_million_euromillions_jackpot', 'Two Players Scoop £21 Million Euromillions Jackpot', '<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Last Friday the 30th of August was lucky for not one, but two <a href="http://euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> players, who suceeded in matching all 5 main numbers and two lucky stars. Thus, their share of the £21,885,637 (€25,642,223) jackpot amounts to a staggering £10,942,818.50 (€12,821,111.50) each. In addition to the exciting first prize win, other lottery hopefuls bagged a generous £81,674.50 (€122,794.80) and £23,594.80 (€35,474.00) in the second and third tiers resepectively, amongst others. The jackpot winners have yet to step forward however, we do know that one ticket was purchased in France and the other in Portugal. We will keep you updated as details emerge.</p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">This makes it the 6th Euromillions first prize landed by Portugal this 2013, and the 7th jackpot win this year for the very fortunate French players whose accumulated winnings now correspond to a staggering €290, 410, 737.50 this 2013 alone.  Consisting of the 67th French jackpot to date since the beginnings of the Euromillions lottery in 2004, France still occupies pride of place as the <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/364/euromillions-luckiest-country">Euromilions luckiest country</a>. Despite their claims, the UK is still home to the two <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/340/top-5-biggest-uk-euromillions-jackpot-winners">biggest Euromillions jackpot winners</a> in the history of the game!  The <strong>winning Euromilions numbers from Friday the 30th of August</strong> are as follows:</p><p align="center">\r\n  <span class="greenball">2</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">17</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">25</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">36</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">45</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">5</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">9</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>Millionaire Raffle:</strong> PFX349818</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nIf you matched two or more numbers, check the full Euromillions Prize Breakdown <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">here</a> because, you could be in the money. We''re crossing our fingers for you! If luck wasn''t on your side then don''t despair! With Euromillions draws held twice a week and a minimum £12 million (€15 million) guaranteed, a huge cash prize could still be yours. Finally, don''t miss out on the chance to win free Euromillions tickets every Friday in our <a href="https://twitter.com/_lotteries">weekly Twitter contest</a>. Remember, you have to be in it to win it! \r\n<p align="justify">\r\n</p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><strong>Watch Friday''s Euromillions Draw:</strong><BR>\r\n</p>\r\n<iframe width="580" height="320" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/ARP3QTsYPUc?feature=player_detailpage" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Euromillions Results For Friday the 30th of August 2013', 'euromillions, results, numbers, friday, euro millions, winners, tickets', 'Two tickets purchased in France and Portugal were winners of Friday''s £21 million Euromillions jackpot! Find out more on www.euromillions.com!', 2, 1378106767, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'euromillions-draw-friday-30-august-2013', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>Two winning tickets purchased in France and Portugal</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1378104420, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (229, 207, 'en', 'fridays_jackpot_at_estimated_21_million', 'Friday''s Jackpot At Estimated £21 Million', '<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">It''s a rollover with last night''s £12,709,500 (€15,000,000) jackpot eluding lottery hopefuls across the world. However, some players succeeded in matching the 5 main numbers and lucky star for £139,287.80 (€203,879.20), whilst others scooped €84,949.60 (no UK winners) in the 3rd tier. The full <a href="http://euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> results and corresponding prizes are available <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-results">here</a>. If you matched two or more numbers a lovely lot of money could be yours! In the meantime, the <strong>winning Euromillions numbers from Tuesday the 3rd of September</strong> are as follows: </p><p align="center">\r\n  <span class="greenball">5</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">9</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">16</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">18</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">42</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">7</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">9</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>Millionaire Raffle:</strong> QGK509937</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nFrance boasts their 7th jackpot win this year and Portugal the 6th following <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/386/euromillions-results-for-friday-the-30th-of-august-2013"> last Friday''s Euromillions draw</a>. Both feature amongst the luckiest Euromillions countries since its beginning in 2004. However, the UK still reigns supreme with the biggest Euromillions jackpot winners in lottery history with <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/207/life-lottery-winners-chris-colin-weir">Chris and Colin Weir</a>, and <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/304/190-Million-winners-flee-from-scroungers"> Adrian and Gillian Bayford</a> who scooped £161,653,000 (€185,000,000) and £148.656,000 (€190,000,000) in August 2011 and 2012 respectively. \r\n<p align="justify">\r\nIn other news, the UK National Lottery is still hunting for the <a href="http://euromillions.com/news-article/383/ten-100-millionaires-raffle-prizes-remain-unclaimed">ten 100 Millionaires Raffle winners</a> who have yet to come forward and claim their £1 million prize. If you bought a ticket for the Euromillions draw held on the 26th of July 2013, make sure you check it. You could be in the money. Finally, this Friday''s Euromillions jackpot stands at a whopping £21 million (€25 million) so if you would like the chance to win <a href=http://play.euromillions.com/en/ rel="nofollow">get your Euromillions tickets now</a> on www.euromillions.com for £1.85. Bargain! \r\n<p align="justify">\r\n</p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><strong>Watch last night''s Euromillions draw:</strong><BR>\r\n</p>\r\n<iframe width="580" height="320" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/A8SwOZt2ddc?feature=player_detailpage" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Euromillions Results For Tuesday the 3rd of September 2013', 'euromillions, results, numbers, tuesday, euro millions, winners, jackpot', 'No one managed to scoop last night''s £12 million jackpot meaning that  £21 million is now up for grabs. Play Euromillions here for your chance to win!', 2, 1378278334, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'euromillions-draw-tuesday-3rd-september-2013', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>Euromillions jackpot rolls over to £21 million</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1378277496, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (230, 208, 'en', 'new_uk_lotto_celebrated_with_two_guaranteed_10_million_prizes', 'New UK Lotto Celebrated with two Guaranteed £10 Million Prizes', '<p align="justify">The UK National Lottery has finally announced that the foreseen changes to the Lotto will come into effect on <strong>Saturday the 5th of October 2013</strong>. As a result, ticket prices will double from £1 to £2, the prize structure will undergo a complete revamp and the <a href="{{news_url::191}}">Lotto Plus 5 will be replaced by the new Lotto Raffle</a>.\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<h3>Lotto Ticket Price Increase</h3></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nAs of Saturday the 5th of October 2013, the <a href="{{news_url::150}}">Lotto ticket price will double</a> from £1 to £2. Lottery operator Camelot said that this substantial price increase will be offset by more winners and an increase in prize money which, in turn, will comprise a boost in funds received by charities across the UK. The <strong>new Lotto prize structure</strong> is as follows:</p>\r\n<p><br><p>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table class="zebraTable">\r\n	    <thead>\r\n		    <tr class="tableHead">\r\n			    <td align="left"><strong>Matching Numbers</strong></td>\r\n			   <td align="left"><strong>Old Lotto</strong></td>\r\n<td align="left"><strong>New Lotto</strong></td>\r\n\r\n                <td></td>\r\n		    </tr>\r\n	    </thead>\r\n	    <tbody>\r\n		    <tr>\r\n			    <td align="left">6 (Jackpot)</td>\r\n			    <td align="left">Sat £3.9 m</td>\r\n<td align="left">Sat £5 m</td>\r\n                <td></td>\r\n		      </tr>\r\n		    <tr>\r\n			    <td align="left">-</td>\r\n			    <td align="left">Wed £2.1 m</td>\r\n<td align="left">Wed £2.5 m</td>\r\n                <td></td>\r\n		    </tr>\r\n		    <tr>\r\n			    <td align="left">5</td>\r\n			    <td align="left">£1,500</td>\r\n <td align="left">£1,000</td>\r\n                <td></td>\r\n		    </tr>\r\n		    <tr>\r\n			    <td align="left">4</td>\r\n			    <td align="left">£60</td>\r\n <td align="left">£100</td>\r\n                <td></td>\r\n		    </tr>\r\n		    <tr>\r\n			    <td align="left">3</td>\r\n			    <td align="left">£10</td>\r\n <td align="left">£25</td>\r\n                <td></td>\r\n		    </tr>\r\n		    <tr>\r\n			    <td align="left">Raffle (50 Winners)</td>\r\n			    <td align="left">N/A</td>\r\n <td align="left">£20,000</td>\r\n                <td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n	    </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n<p><br><p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<h3>New Lotto Raffle</h3></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nSimilarly, the Lotto Plus 5 side game will be replaced by the new Lotto Raffle. Whilst the Lotto Plus 5 currently costs an extra £1 per participation, entry into the new Lotto Raffle will be automatic, and free. In addition, according to UK lottery operator Camelot, the changes foreseen in the new Lotto side game will guarantee that at least 50 players scoop a £20,000 prize per draw. Furthermore, with every jackpot rollover the number of Lotto Raffle winners of £20,000 will increase by 50, as demonstrated in the table below:</p>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<td align="center">\r\n<table class="zebraTable">\r\n	    <thead>\r\n		    <tr class="tableHead">\r\n			    <td align="left"><strong>Rollover</strong></td>\r\n<td align="left"><strong>No. Of Raffle Winners</strong></td>\r\n\r\n                <td></td>\r\n		    </tr>\r\n	    </thead>\r\n	    <tbody>\r\n		    <tr>\r\n			    <td align="left">Lotto draw</td>\r\n			    <td align="left">50</td>\r\n                <td></td>\r\n		    </tr>\r\n		    <tr>\r\n			    <td align="left">Single Rollover</td>\r\n			    <td align="left">100</td>\r\n                <td></td>\r\n		    </tr>\r\n		    <tr>\r\n			    <td align="left">Double Rollover</td>\r\n			    <td align="left">150</td>\r\n                <td></td>\r\n		    </tr>\r\n		    <tr>\r\n			    <td align="left">Triple Rollover</td>\r\n			    <td align="left">200</td>\r\n                <td></td>\r\n		    </tr>\r\n		    <tr>\r\n			    <td align="left">Quadruple Rollover</td>\r\n			    <td align="left">250</td>\r\n                <td></td>\r\n		    </tr>\r\n	    </tbody>\r\n    </table>\r\n<p><br><p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<h3>New UK Lotto Launch Events</h3></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nFinally, to celebrate the launch of the new Lotto, the <strong>two Saturday draws held on the 5th and 12th of October</strong> respectively will both feature a guaranteed £10 million jackpot. And that''s not all! A staggering 1,000 Lotto Raffle players will also scoop a guaranteed £20,000 prize each, on both nights. Hurrah!</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nNo changes to the <a href="http://euromillions.com/">Euromillions</a> lottery has been announced.</p>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br><br>\r\n</p>', 'Launch of New UK Lotto on the 5th of October 2013', 'uk , lotto, camelot, national lottery, price increase, new lotto, lotto plus 5,launch', 'The UK National Lottery has confirmed that the launch of the new Lotto will be on Saturday October 5th. It will be celebrated with two guaranteed £10M prizes!', 1, 1378292521, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'new-uk-lotto-launch', 'http://www.bingowonga.com/bingonews/wp-content/uploads/2011/03/lotto_uk_national_lottery.jpg', '<p align="justify"><h2>Two £10 million prizes and 2,000 raffle winners guaranteed in celebration of new Lotto launch</h2></p>', 'New Lotto Launch', NULL, 1378289822, 0, 1380006967, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (231, 209, 'en', 'two_players_bag_21_million_euromillions_jackpot', 'Two Players Bag £21 Million Euromillions Jackpot', '<p align="justify">Two fortunate players scooped Friday''s £21,603,767 (€25,602,948) <a href="http://euromillions.com">Euromillions</a> jackpot thus bagging themselves a respectable £10,801,883.50 (€12,801,474) each. Congratulations! The winning tickets were purchased in Spain and Ireland however, further details are yet to be revealed.</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nThis comprises Ireland''s second jackpot win this year after an <a href="{{news_url::180}}">Irish player scooped a share of the £159,559,034 (€187,937,614) jackpot</a> on the 25th of June 2013. With regards to Spain, the 2nd luckiest of the 9 participating countries, this features their first jackpot win this year but, their 54th win since the <a href="{{article_url::euromillions_history}}">beginning of the Euromillions in 2004</a> taking their accumulated prize money to a staggering €1,631 million. </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nIn addition to the coveted first prize, the second and third tiers saw lottery hopefuls bag £183,930.70 (€265,073.60) and £28,297.00 (€40,780.50) respectively. To find out if that was you, take a look at the full Euromillions Prize Breakdown <a href="{{lottey_url::results}}">here</a>. In the meantime, the <strong>winning Euromillions numbers from Friday the 6th of September''s draw</strong> are as follows: </p><p align="center">\r\n  <span class="greenball">11</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">23</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">25</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">32</span>\r\n  <span class="greenball">37</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">4</span>\r\n  <span class="redball">7</span></p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>Millionaire Raffle:</strong>  RGL908853</p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nDid you win something? We hope so. If Friday wasn''t quite your lucky day then <a href=http://play.euromillions.com/en/ rel="nofollow">play Euromillions now</a> with Euromillions.com for the chance to win Tuesday''s £12 million (€15 million) jackpot! Also, if you purchased a Euromillions ticket for the draw on the 26th of July 2013, check your numbers <a href="{{news_url::203}}">here</a> because 9 winners of the 100 Millionaires Raffle still haven''t claimed their £1 million prize yet. Good luck! </p>\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n</p>\r\n<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"><strong>Watch the latest Euromillions draw:</strong><BR>\r\n</p>\r\n<iframe width="580" height="320" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/iYsMNd1vuU0?feature=player_detailpage" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br><br>', 'Euromillions Results for Friday the 6th of September 2013', 'euromillions, results, numbers, friday, euro millions, winners, jackpot', 'Two ticket holders from Spain and Ireland scooped Friday''s £21 MILLION jackpot! Find out more on www.euromillions.com.', 1, 1378712517, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'euromillions-draw-friday-06-september-2013', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>Two winning tickets purchased in Ireland and Spain</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1378711898, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
INSERT INTO `news_details` VALUES (232, 210, 'en', 'fun_facts_about_the_euromillions', 'Fun Facts About the Euromillions', '<img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-nwpd4HI_C7k/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAAMg/BszUsc3NoWg/photo.jpg" width="250" height="250" align="left" alt="Euromillions.com" />\r\n\r\n<p align="justify">Euromillions comprises one of the world''s leading lotteries and features some of the biggest cash prizes. It has rapidly grown in popularity since it''s beginnings which you can find out why with our <strong>fun facts about the Euromillions lottery</strong>:\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>1.</strong> The <a href="http://euromillions.com/">Euromillions</a> lottery was launched in 2004 and the first Euromillions draw held on Friday the 13th of February in Paris. Initially, Spain, France and the UK were the only participating countries however, they were joined later that year by a further six countries; Austria, Belgium, Ireland, Luxembourg, Portugal and Switzerland.\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>2.</strong> The Euromillions lottery boasts the <strong>biggest cash prizes</strong> with a minimum £12 million (€15 million) jackpot guaranteed per draw. In the absence of a first prize winner, the Euromillions jackpot has the potential to grow in successive categories to  €190 million (the Jackpot Pool Cap).\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>3.</strong> The Euromillions lottery features 13 different prize levels thanks to which the <a href="{{article_url::discover_your_odds_of_winning_the_euromillions}}">odds of a Euromillions win</a> is 1 in 13. Similarly, to win the Euromillions jackpot players need to match all 5 main numbers and two lucky stars. However, matching as little as two numbers will earn lottery hopefuls a prize in the 13th tier.\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>4.</strong>Two <strong>Super Draws</strong>, featuring a guaranteed €100 million jackpot, are held every year. The very first one took place on Friday the 9th of February 2007. The special Super Draw, held on Tuesday the 10th of May 2011, marked the introduction of the Tuesday Euromillions draw and changes to the Euromillions lottery game format.\r\n<img src="http://images.mirror.co.uk/upl/m4/jul2011/9/7/colin-and-chris-weir-pic-pa-821484718.jpg" width="290" height="190" align="right" alt="Colin and Chris Weir" />\r\n<p align="justify">\r\nThey included a further prize tier (2 main numbers and no lucky stars) and 11 lucky stars instead of 9.\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>5.</strong> The largest jackpot in lottery history was scooped by <a href="{{news_url::321}}">Colin and Chris Weir</a> from Lars in North Ayrshire on the 12th of August 2011. Comprising not only the UK but, Europe''s biggest winners, their staggering windfall corresponded to a whopping €185,000,000 (£161,653,000) . It immediately catapulted them to number 1 on the UK National Lottery Rich List.\r\n<strong>6.</strong> The <a href="{{news_url::185}}">luckiest Euromillions country</a> is France with 67 jackpot wins to date. Seven French players have scooped the coveted Euromillions jackpot this 2013 alone with the latest prize corresponding to a whopping €12,821,111.50 and taking their total accumulated winnings to to a staggering €2,231 million since the beginning of the Euromillions.\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>7.</strong> The <a href="{{news_url::185}}">largest first prize ever to go unclaimed</a> comprised a €63.8 million jackpot. It was scooped by an unwitting UK player in June 2012 who, followed by widespread appeals urging them to come forward, never claimed their enormous prize. Thus, all winnings and accumulated interested was donated to the UK National Lottery Good Causes after the 5th of December 2012 deadline passed.\r\n<img src="http://i3.mirror.co.uk/incoming/article1158436.ece/ALTERNATES/s615/EM+100+Millionaires+(2).jpg" width="290" height="190" align="left" alt="100 Millionaires Raffle" />\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>8.</strong> On Friday the 17th of February 2012, an amendment was made to the <a href="http://euromillions.com/euromillions-prize-structure">Euromillions jackpot rules</a> guaranteeing further pay outs and limited rollovers. Prior to the aforementioned date, the Jackpot Pool Cap stood at €185 million and could roll over as many times as it took to produce a winner. When a player scooped the first prize, the maximum would then be increased by €5 million (in this case to €190 million). Today the <strong>Euromillions Jackpot Pool Cap</strong> is locked at €190 million and may only roll over for two consecutive draws. In the event of no winner in the third draw, the prize money is awarded to the winner in the lower prize tier who has succeeded in matching 5 main numbers and one lucky star, etc.\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<strong>9.</strong> The 100 Millionaires Raffle, held on the 27th of July 2012, set the record for the highest number of newly-made millionaires in a single draw. Nine winners of the <a href="{{news_url::185}}">100 Millionaires Raffle</a> held on the 27th of July 2013 have yet to step forward and claim their £1 million prize. If all 100 winners come forward, before the 180-day claim period ending on the 22nd of January 2014, the draw will set a new record.\r\n<p align="justify">\r\n<br></br>\r\n<a href="https://plus.google.com/109362733485861027705/posts">Anna Dobson</a>\r\n<br></br>', 'Fun Facts About the Euromillions Lottery', 'facts, euromillions, euro millions, lottery', 'Discover some fun things that you probably didn''t know about the Euromillions lottery on www.euromillions.com. Enjoy!', 1, 1378813084, 4, 'Daniel Kowalsky', 'fun-facts-euromillions', NULL, '<p align="justify"><h2>Fun things you didn''t know about the Euromillions lottery</h2></p>', NULL, NULL, 1378812122, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
